\h Jeremiah
\toc1 Jeremiah
\toc2 Jeremiah
\mt1 Jeremiah
\c 1
\p \v 1 The words of Jeremiah, the son of Hilkiah, one \x + \xo 1:1 \xt Ezek. 1:3 \x*of the priests who were in \x + \xo 1:1 \xt ch. 29:27; 32:7; Josh. 21:18\x*Anathoth in the land of Benjamin,
\v 2 to whom the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came in the days of \x + \xo 1:2 \xt See 2 Kgs. 22; 23:1-30 \x*Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah, in \x + \xo 1:2 \xt ch. 25:3; 36:2\x*the thirteenth year of his reign.
\v 3 It came also in the days of \x + \xo 1:3 \xt ch. 25:1; 36:1; See 2 Kgs. 23:34–24:6 \x*Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, and \x + \xo 1:3 \xt ch. 39:2 \x*until the end of the eleventh year of \x + \xo 1:3 \xt See 2 Kgs. 24:17–25:7 \x*Zedekiah, the son of Josiah, king of Judah, \x + \xo 1:3 \xt See 2 Kgs. 25:8-11\x*until the captivity of Jerusalem in the fifth month.
\s1 The Call of Jeremiah
\p
\v 4 Now the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me, saying,
\b
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 1:5 \xt See Isa. 44:2 \x*“Before I formed you in the womb I knew you,
\q1 and before you were born \x + \xo 1:5 \xt [John 10:36] \x*I consecrated you;
\q1 I appointed you a prophet \x + \xo 1:5 \xt [Isa. 49:6]; See ch. 25:15-29; ch. 46–51\x*to the nations.”
\b
\m
\v 6 Then I said, “Ah, Lord \nd God\nd*! Behold, \x + \xo 1:6 \xt [Ex. 4:10] \x*I do not know how to speak, \x + \xo 1:6 \xt [1 Kgs. 3:7]\x*for I am only a youth.”
\v 7 But the \nd Lord\nd* said to me,
\b
\q1 “Do not say, ‘I am only a youth’;
\q1 for to all to whom I send you, you shall go,
\q1 and \x + \xo 1:7 \xt ver. 17; Ezek. 2:7\x*whatever I command you, you shall speak.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 1:8 \xt Ezek. 2:6; 3:9 \x*Do not be afraid of them,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:8 \xt ch. 15:20; See Ex. 3:12\x*for I am with you to deliver you,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\b
\m
\v 9 \x + \xo 1:9 \xt [Ezek. 2:9] \x*Then the \nd Lord\nd* put out his hand and \x + \xo 1:9 \xt [Isa. 6:7] \x*touched my mouth. And the \nd Lord\nd* said to me,
\b
\q1 “Behold, I have put \x + \xo 1:9 \xt ch. 5:14\x*my words in your mouth.
\q1
\v 10 See, I have set you this day \x + \xo 1:10 \xt [See ver. 5 above] \x*over nations and over kingdoms,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:10 \xt ch. 18:7; 31:28; 45:4; [2 Cor. 10:4, 5]\x*to pluck up and to break down,
\q1 to destroy and to overthrow,
\q1 to build and to plant.”
\b
\p
\v 11 And the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me, saying, \x + \xo 1:11 \xt [Amos 7:8]\x*“Jeremiah, what do you see?” And I said, “I see an almond\f + \fr 1:11 \fq Almond \ft sounds like the Hebrew for \fq watching \ft (compare verse 12)\f* branch.”
\v 12 Then the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, “You have seen well, for I am watching over my word to perform it.”
\p
\v 13 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me a second time, saying, “What do you see?” And I said, “I see \x + \xo 1:13 \xt Ezek. 24:3; [Ezek. 22:21] \x*a boiling pot, facing away \x + \xo 1:13 \xt ch. 4:6; 6:1; 10:22\x*from the north.”
\v 14 Then the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [See ver. 13 above]\x*“Out of the north disaster\f + \fr 1:14 \ft The Hebrew word can mean \fq evil\ft , \fq harm\ft , or \fq disaster\ft , depending on the context; so throughout Jeremiah\f* shall be let loose upon all the inhabitants of the land.
\v 15 For behold, \x + \xo 1:15 \xt [ch. 25:9] \x*I am calling all the tribes of the kingdoms of the north, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 1:15 \xt [ch. 39:3; 43:10]\x*and they shall come, and every one shall set his throne at the entrance of the gates of Jerusalem, against all its walls all around and against all the cities of Judah.
\v 16 And \x + \xo 1:16 \xt ch. 4:12 \x*I will declare my judgments against them, for all their evil \x + \xo 1:16 \xt ch. 19:4; 22:9 \x*in forsaking me. \x + \xo 1:16 \xt ch. 7:9; 44:3 \x*They have made offerings to other gods and \x + \xo 1:16 \xt ch. 25:6, 7; Isa. 2:8; Acts 7:41\x*worshiped the works of their own hands.
\v 17 But you, \x + \xo 1:17 \xt [1 Kgs. 18:46; 1 Pet. 1:13] \x*dress yourself for work;\f + \fr 1:17 \ft Hebrew \fq gird up your loins\f* arise, and \x + \xo 1:17 \xt ver. 7 \x*say to them everything that I command you. \x + \xo 1:17 \xt ver. 8; Ezek. 3:9\x*Do not be dismayed by them, lest I dismay you before them.
\v 18 And I, behold, I make you this day \x + \xo 1:18 \xt [Isa. 50:7] \x*a fortified city, \x + \xo 1:18 \xt Rev. 3:12 \x*an iron pillar, and \x + \xo 1:18 \xt ch. 15:20; [ch. 6:27]\x*bronze walls, against the whole land, against the kings of Judah, its officials, its priests, and the people of the land.
\v 19 \x + \xo 1:19 \xt [See ver. 18 above] \x*They will fight against you, but they shall not prevail against you, for \x + \xo 1:19 \xt ver. 8; [Acts 18:9, 10]\x*I am with you, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, to deliver you.”
\c 2
\s1 Israel Forsakes the \nd Lord\nd*
\p \v 1 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me, saying,
\v 2 “Go and proclaim in the hearing of Jerusalem, Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*,
\b
\q1 “I remember the devotion of \x + \xo 2:2 \xt ch. 3:4 \x*your youth,
\q2 your love \x + \xo 2:2 \xt Ezek. 16:8, 43, 60; [Rev. 2:4] \x*as a bride,
\q1 \x + \xo 2:2 \xt Deut. 2:7 \x*how you followed me in the wilderness,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:2 \xt Deut. 8:2, 3\x*in a land not sown.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 2:3 \xt Ex. 28:36; [Ex. 19:5, 6] \x*Israel was holy to the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:3 \xt James 1:18; [Ex. 4:22] \x*the firstfruits of his harvest.
\q1 \x + \xo 2:3 \xt ch. 12:14; Ezek. 25:12, 13; [Gen. 12:3]\x*All who ate of it incurred guilt;
\q2 disaster came upon them,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\b
\p
\v 4 Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, O house of Jacob, and all the clans of the house of Israel.
\v 5 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 2:5 \xt ver. 31; Isa. 5:4; Mic. 6:3 \x*“What wrong did your fathers find in me
\q2 that they went far from me,
\q1 \x + \xo 2:5 \xt 2 Kgs. 17:15 \x*and went after \x + \xo 2:5 \xt ch. 10:15; 14:22; 16:19\x*worthlessness, and became worthless?
\q1
\v 6 They did not say, \x + \xo 2:6 \xt [Isa. 63:11-13; Hos. 13:4, 5] \x*‘Where is the \nd Lord\nd*
\q2 who brought us up from the land of Egypt,
\q1 who led us \x + \xo 2:6 \xt Deut. 8:15; 32:10\x*in the wilderness,
\q2 in a land of deserts and pits,
\q1 in a land of drought and deep darkness,
\q2 in a land that none passes through,
\q2 where no man dwells?’
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 2:7 \xt See Deut. 8:7-10 \x*And I brought you into a plentiful land
\q2 to enjoy its fruits and its good things.
\q1 But when you came in, \x + \xo 2:7 \xt Ps. 106:38; [Lev. 18:24, 25]\x*you defiled my land
\q2 and made my heritage an abomination.
\q1
\v 8 The priests did not say, ‘Where is the \nd Lord\nd*?’
\q2 \x + \xo 2:8 \xt ch. 18:18; [Mal. 2:7; Rom. 2:20] \x*Those who handle the law did not know me;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:8 \xt [ch. 5:5] \x*the shepherds\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Or \fq rulers\f* transgressed against me;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:8 \xt ch. 23:13; [ch. 5:31] \x*the prophets prophesied by Baal
\q2 and went after \x + \xo 2:8 \xt [Hab. 2:18]\x*things that do not profit.
\b
\q1
\v 9 “Therefore \x + \xo 2:9 \xt ver. 35; Ezek. 17:20; 20:35, 36 \x*I still contend with you,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:9 \xt Ex. 20:5, 6\x*with your children’s children I will contend.
\q1
\v 10 For cross to the coasts of \x + \xo 2:10 \xt See Gen. 10:4 \x*Cyprus and see,
\q2 or send to \x + \xo 2:10 \xt See Isa. 21:16\x*Kedar and examine with care;
\q2 see if there has been such a thing.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 2:11 \xt [Mic. 4:5]; See ch. 18:13-15 \x*Has a nation changed its gods,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:11 \xt ch. 16:20; Isa. 37:19; Gal. 4:8 \x*even though they are no gods?
\q1 But my people \x + \xo 2:11 \xt Ps. 106:20 \x*have changed their glory
\q2 for \x + \xo 2:11 \xt [See ver. 8 above]\x*that which does not profit.
\q1
\v 12 Be appalled, \x + \xo 2:12 \xt Isa. 1:2\x*O heavens, at this;
\q2 be shocked, be utterly desolate,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1
\v 13 for my people have committed two evils:
\q1 \x + \xo 2:13 \xt ch. 17:13 \x*they have forsaken \x + \xo 2:13 \xt Ps. 36:9 \x*me,
\q2 the fountain of \x + \xo 2:13 \xt John 4:10\x*living waters,
\q1 and hewed out cisterns for themselves,
\q2 broken cisterns that can hold no water.
\b
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 2:14 \xt [Ex. 4:22]\x*“Is Israel a slave? Is he a homeborn servant?
\q2 Why then has he become a prey?
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 2:15 \xt ch. 4:7; Isa. 5:29 \x*The lions have roared against him;
\q2 they have roared loudly.
\q1 They have made his land a waste;
\q2 his cities are in ruins, \x + \xo 2:15 \xt ch. 9:11; 46:19\x*without inhabitant.
\q1
\v 16 Moreover, the men of \x + \xo 2:16 \xt ch. 44:1; 46:14; Ezek. 30:16 \x*Memphis and \x + \xo 2:16 \xt ch. 43:7-9 \x*Tahpanhes
\q2 \x + \xo 2:16 \xt [Deut. 33:20]\x*have shaved\f + \fr 2:16 \ft Hebrew \fq grazed\f* the crown of your head.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 2:17 \xt ch. 4:18 \x*Have you not brought this upon yourself
\q2 by forsaking the \nd Lord\nd* your God,
\q2 when \x + \xo 2:17 \xt ver. 6\x*he led you in the way?
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 2:18 \xt ver. 36; Isa. 30:1, 2; 31:1 \x*And now what do you gain by going to Egypt
\q2 to drink the waters of \x + \xo 2:18 \xt Isa. 23:3 \x*the Nile?
\q1 \x + \xo 2:18 \xt [Hos. 7:11] \x*Or what do you gain by going to Assyria
\q2 to drink the waters of \x + \xo 2:18 \xt Gen. 31:21; Isa. 7:20; 8:7\x*the Euphrates?\f + \fr 2:18 \ft Hebrew \fq the River\f*
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 2:19 \xt Isa. 3:9; Hos. 5:5 \x*Your evil will chastise you,
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:19 \xt ch. 3:22; 5:6; 14:7 \x*your apostasy will reprove you.
\q1 Know and see that it is evil and \x + \xo 2:19 \xt ch. 4:18 \x*bitter
\q2 for \x + \xo 2:19 \xt ver. 13, 17\x*you to forsake the \nd Lord\nd* your God;
\q2 the fear of me is not in you,
\qr declares the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts.
\b
\q1
\v 20 “For long ago I \x + \xo 2:20 \xt ch. 5:5; 30:8 \x*broke your yoke
\q2 and burst your bonds;
\q2 but you said, \x + \xo 2:20 \xt ver. 31 \x*‘I will not serve.’
\q1 Yes, \x + \xo 2:20 \xt ch. 3:2; 17:2 \x*on every high hill
\q2 and under every green tree
\q2 you bowed down \x + \xo 2:20 \xt ch. 3:1; Isa. 1:21\x*like a whore.
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 2:21 \xt Ex. 15:17; Ps. 44:2; 80:8; Isa. 5:2 \x*Yet I planted you a choice vine,
\q2 wholly of pure seed.
\q1 \x + \xo 2:21 \xt Isa. 5:4; [Deut. 32:32]\x*How then have you turned degenerate
\q2 and become a wild vine?
\q1
\v 22 Though you wash yourself with lye
\q2 and use much soap,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:22 \xt [ch. 17:1]\x*the stain of your guilt is still before me,
\qr declares the Lord \nd God\nd*.
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 2:23 \xt ver. 35 \x*How can you say, ‘I am not unclean,
\q2 I have not gone after the Baals’?
\q1 Look at your way \x + \xo 2:23 \xt ch. 7:31, 32; 19:2, 6\x*in the valley;
\q2 know what you have done—
\q1 a restless young camel running here and there,
\q2
\v 24 \x + \xo 2:24 \xt ch. 14:6\x*a wild donkey used to the wilderness,
\q1 in her heat sniffing the wind!
\q2 Who can restrain her lust?
\q1 None who seek her need weary themselves;
\q2 in her month they will find her.
\q1
\v 25 Keep \x + \xo 2:25 \xt Deut. 29:5 \x*your feet from going unshod
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:25 \xt Ex. 17:6 \x*your throat from thirst.
\q1 But you said, ‘It is hopeless,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:25 \xt ch. 3:13; Deut. 32:16\x*for I have loved foreigners,
\q2 and after them I will go.’
\b
\q1
\v 26 “As a thief is shamed when caught,
\q2 so the house of Israel shall be shamed:
\q1 \x + \xo 2:26 \xt ch. 13:13; 32:32; [ch. 8:1]\x*they, their kings, their officials,
\q2 their priests, and their prophets,
\q1
\v 27 who say to a tree, ‘You are my father,’
\q2 and to a stone, ‘You gave me birth.’
\q1 For they have turned their back to me,
\q2 and not their face.
\q1 But \x + \xo 2:27 \xt Judg. 10:9, 10; Isa. 26:16\x*in the time of their trouble they say,
\q2 ‘Arise and save us!’
\q1
\v 28 But \x + \xo 2:28 \xt Deut. 32:37, 38 \x*where are your gods
\q2 that you made for yourself?
\q1 Let them arise, \x + \xo 2:28 \xt Isa. 45:20 \x*if they can save you,
\q2 in your time of trouble;
\q1 for \x + \xo 2:28 \xt ch. 11:13\x*as many as your cities
\q2 are your gods, O Judah.
\b
\q1
\v 29 “Why do you contend with me?
\q2 You have all transgressed against me,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 30 In vain have I \x + \xo 2:30 \xt ch. 5:3; Isa. 1:5; 9:13 \x*struck your children;
\q2 they took no correction;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:30 \xt Neh. 9:26; 1 Thess. 2:15\x*your own sword devoured your prophets
\q2 like a ravening lion.
\q1
\v 31 And you, O generation, behold the word of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1 Have I been a wilderness to Israel,
\q2 or a land of thick darkness?
\q1 Why then do my people say, ‘We are free,
\q2 we will come no more to you’?
\q1
\v 32 \x + \xo 2:32 \xt Isa. 3:20; 61:10 \x*Can a virgin forget her ornaments,
\q2 or a bride her attire?
\q1 Yet \x + \xo 2:32 \xt ch. 3:21; 18:15; Deut. 32:18; Ps. 106:21; Isa. 17:10; Hos. 8:14\x*my people have forgotten me
\q2 days without number.
\b
\q1
\v 33 “How well you direct your course
\q2 to seek love!
\q1 So that even to wicked women
\q2 you have taught your ways.
\q1
\v 34 Also on your skirts is found
\q2 \x + \xo 2:34 \xt ch. 19:4; 2 Kgs. 21:16; 24:4; Ps. 106:38 \x*the lifeblood of the guiltless poor;
\q1 you did not find them \x + \xo 2:34 \xt Ex. 22:2\x*breaking in.
\q2 Yet in spite of all these things
\q1
\v 35 you say, ‘I am innocent;
\q2 surely his anger has turned from me.’
\q1 \x + \xo 2:35 \xt Ps. 143:2 \x*Behold, I will bring you to judgment
\q2 for \x + \xo 2:35 \xt Prov. 28:13; 1 John 1:8, 10\x*saying, ‘I have not sinned.’
\q1
\v 36 \x + \xo 2:36 \xt [ch. 31:22] \x*How much you go about,
\q2 changing your way!
\q1 You shall be \x + \xo 2:36 \xt Isa. 30:3\x*put to shame by Egypt
\q2 as you were put to shame by Assyria.
\q1
\v 37 From it too you will come away
\q2 with \x + \xo 2:37 \xt 2 Sam. 13:19\x*your hands on your head,
\q1 for the \nd Lord\nd* has rejected those in whom you trust,
\q2 and you will not prosper by them.
\b
\c 3
\q1 \v 1 \x + \xo 3:1 \xt See Deut. 24:1-4 \x*“If\f + \fr 3:1 \ft Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew \fq Saying, “If\f* a man divorces his wife
\q2 and she goes from him
\q1 and becomes another man’s wife,
\q2 will he return to her?
\q1 \x + \xo 3:1 \xt ver. 9; Ps. 106:38 \x*Would not that land be greatly polluted?
\q1 \x + \xo 3:1 \xt ch. 2:20\x*You have played the whore with many lovers;
\q2 and would you return to me?
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 2 Lift up your eyes to \x + \xo 3:2 \xt ver. 21, 23; ch. 4:11; 7:29; Num. 23:3 \x*the bare heights, and see!
\q2 Where have you not been ravished?
\q1 \x + \xo 3:2 \xt Ezek. 16:25 \x*By the waysides you have sat awaiting lovers
\q2 like an Arab in the wilderness.
\q1 \x + \xo 3:2 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*You have polluted the land
\q2 with your vile whoredom.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 3:3 \xt ch. 9:12; 14:22; Deut. 28:24 \x*Therefore the showers have been withheld,
\q2 and the spring rain has not come;
\q1 yet you have \x + \xo 3:3 \xt [ch. 6:15]; See Ezek. 3:7, 8\x*the forehead of a whore;
\q2 you refuse to be ashamed.
\q1
\v 4 Have you not just now \x + \xo 3:4 \xt [Luke 15:18]\x*called to me,
\q2 ‘My father, you are the friend of my youth—
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 3:5 \xt Ps. 103:9\x*will he be angry forever,
\q2 will he be indignant to the end?’
\q1 Behold, you have spoken,
\q2 but you have done all the evil that you could.”
\s1 Faithless Israel Called to Repentance
\p
\v 6 The \nd Lord\nd* said to me in the days of \x + \xo 3:6 \xt ch. 1:2 \x*King Josiah: “Have you seen what she did, that faithless one, Israel, \x + \xo 3:6 \xt See ch. 2:20 \x*how she went up on every high hill and under every green tree, and there \x + \xo 3:6 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*played the whore?
\v 7 And I thought, ‘After she has done all this she will return to me,’ but she did not return, and her treacherous \x + \xo 3:7 \xt [Ezek. 16:46; 23:4]\x*sister Judah saw it.
\v 8 She saw that for all the adulteries of that faithless one, Israel, \x + \xo 3:8 \xt 2 Kgs. 17:18; [Hos. 1:6, 9] \x*I had sent her away with \x + \xo 3:8 \xt [Matt. 19:7; Mark 10:4]; See Deut. 24:1-4 \x*a decree of divorce. \x + \xo 3:8 \xt Ezek. 23:11 \x*Yet her treacherous sister Judah did not fear, but she too went \x + \xo 3:8 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*and played the whore.
\v 9 Because she took her whoredom lightly, she polluted the land, committing adultery with \x + \xo 3:9 \xt ch. 2:27\x*stone and tree.
\v 10 Yet for all this her treacherous sister Judah did not return to me \x + \xo 3:10 \xt Hos. 7:14\x*with her whole heart, but in pretense, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\p
\v 11 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, \x + \xo 3:11 \xt Ezek. 16:51, 52\x*“Faithless Israel has shown herself more righteous than treacherous Judah.
\v 12 Go, and proclaim these words toward \x + \xo 3:12 \xt See ver. 18 \x*the north, and say,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 3:12 \xt Prov. 28:13; See Deut. 30:1-10 \x*“‘Return, faithless Israel,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1 I will not look on you in anger,
\q2 for \x + \xo 3:12 \xt Ps. 86:5, 15 \x*I am merciful,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q1 \x + \xo 3:12 \xt Ps. 103:9\x*I will not be angry forever.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 3:13 \xt Lev. 26:40 \x*Only acknowledge your guilt,
\q2 that you rebelled against the \nd Lord\nd* your God
\q1 and scattered your favors among foreigners under \x + \xo 3:13 \xt ver. 6\x*every green tree,
\q2 and that you have not obeyed my voice,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 3:14 \xt ver. 22; Hos. 14:1 \x*Return, O faithless children,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 \x + \xo 3:14 \xt Isa. 54:5; 62:5; Hos. 2:19, 20; Mal. 2:11\x*for I am your master;
\q1 I will take you, one from a city and two from a family,
\q2 and I will bring you to Zion.
\b
\p
\v 15 “‘And \x + \xo 3:15 \xt ch. 23:4; Ezek. 34:23; [John 10:11] \x*I will give you shepherds after my own heart, \x + \xo 3:15 \xt Acts 20:28\x*who will feed you with knowledge and understanding.
\v 16 And when you have multiplied and been fruitful in the land, in those days, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, they shall no more say, “The ark of the covenant of the \nd Lord\nd*.” It shall not come to mind or be remembered or missed; it shall not be made again.
\v 17 At that time Jerusalem shall be called the throne of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 3:17 \xt Isa. 2:2, 3 \x*and all nations shall gather to it, \x + \xo 3:17 \xt Isa. 60:9\x*to the presence of the \nd Lord\nd* in Jerusalem, and they shall no more stubbornly follow their own evil heart.
\v 18 \x + \xo 3:18 \xt ch. 50:4; Isa. 11:13; Ezek. 37:21, 22; Hos. 1:11 \x*In those days the house of Judah shall join the house of Israel, and together they shall come from the land \x + \xo 3:18 \xt ver. 12; ch. 16:15; 23:8; 31:8 \x*of the north to \x + \xo 3:18 \xt Amos 9:15\x*the land that I gave your fathers for a heritage.
\b
\q1
\v 19 “‘I said,
\q2 How I would set you among my sons,
\q1 and give you a pleasant land,
\q2 a heritage most beautiful of all nations.
\q1 And I thought you would \x + \xo 3:19 \xt [Isa. 63:16]\x*call me, My Father,
\q2 and would not turn from following me.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 3:20 \xt ver. 7, 8; ch. 5:11\x*Surely, as a treacherous wife leaves her husband,
\q2 so have you been treacherous to me, O house of Israel,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.’”
\b
\q1
\v 21 A voice on the \x + \xo 3:21 \xt See ver. 2 \x*bare heights is heard,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:21 \xt ch. 31:9\x*the weeping and pleading of Israel’s sons
\q1 because they have perverted their way;
\q2 they have forgotten the \nd Lord\nd* their God.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 3:22 \xt ver. 14 \x*“Return, O faithless sons;
\q2 \x + \xo 3:22 \xt ch. 30:17; Isa. 57:18; Hos. 6:1\x*I will heal your faithlessness.”
\q1 “Behold, we come to you,
\q2 for you are the \nd Lord\nd* our God.
\q1
\v 23 Truly \x + \xo 3:23 \xt ver. 21; [Ps. 121:1, 2] \x*the hills are a delusion,
\q2 the orgies\f + \fr 3:23 \ft Hebrew \fq commotion\f* on the mountains.
\q1 \x + \xo 3:23 \xt Ps. 3:8\x*Truly in the \nd Lord\nd* our God
\q2 is the salvation of Israel.
\b
\p
\v 24 “But from our youth the shameful thing has devoured all for which our fathers labored, their flocks and their herds, their sons and their daughters.
\v 25 \x + \xo 3:25 \xt Ezra 9:6; Job 8:22 \x*Let us lie down in our shame, and let our dishonor cover us. For \x + \xo 3:25 \xt Ezra 9:7; Ezek. 2:3\x*we have sinned against the \nd Lord\nd* our God, we and our fathers, from our youth even to this day, and we have not obeyed the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* our God.”
\b
\c 4
\q1 \v 1 “If you return, O Israel,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:1 \xt Joel 2:12 \x*to me you should return.
\q1 If you remove your detestable things from my presence,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:1 \xt [1 Kgs. 14:15]\x*and do not waver,
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 4:2 \xt Deut. 6:13 \x*and if you swear, ‘As the \nd Lord\nd* lives,’
\q2 in truth, in justice, and in righteousness,
\q1 then \x + \xo 4:2 \xt Isa. 65:16 \x*nations shall bless themselves in him,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:2 \xt 1 Cor. 1:31; 2 Cor. 10:17\x*and in him shall they glory.”
\b
\p
\v 3 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* to the men of Judah and Jerusalem:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 4:3 \xt Hos. 10:12 \x*“Break up your fallow ground,
\q2 and \x + \xo 4:3 \xt Matt. 13:7, 22; Mark 4:7, 18; Luke 8:7, 14\x*sow not among thorns.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 4:4 \xt Deut. 10:16; [ch. 9:26; Rom. 2:28, 29] \x*Circumcise yourselves to the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 remove the foreskin of your hearts,
\q2 O men of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem;
\q1 \x + \xo 4:4 \xt ch. 21:12 \x*lest my wrath go forth like fire,
\q2 and burn with none to quench it,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:4 \xt Deut. 28:20\x*because of the evil of your deeds.”
\s1 Disaster from the North
\p
\v 5 Declare in Judah, and proclaim in Jerusalem, and say,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 4:5 \xt [ch. 6:1; Hos. 5:8; Joel 2:1] \x*“Blow the trumpet through the land;
\q2 cry aloud and say,
\q1 \x + \xo 4:5 \xt ch. 8:14\x*‘Assemble, and let us go
\q2 into the fortified cities!’
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 4:6 \xt [ch. 50:2; 51:12, 27] \x*Raise a standard toward Zion,
\q2 flee for safety, stay not,
\q1 for I bring disaster from \x + \xo 4:6 \xt See ch. 1:13 \x*the north,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:6 \xt [Isa. 1:28]\x*and great destruction.
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 4:7 \xt ch. 2:15; 5:6; 49:19 \x*A lion has gone up from his thicket,
\q2 a destroyer of nations has set out;
\q2 he has gone out from his place
\q1 to make your land a waste;
\q2 your cities will be ruins
\q2 \x + \xo 4:7 \xt ch. 33:10; 34:22; 46:19; Isa. 5:9; 6:11\x*without inhabitant.
\q1
\v 8 For this \x + \xo 4:8 \xt ch. 6:26; Isa. 22:12; 32:11 \x*put on sackcloth,
\q2 lament and wail,
\q1 for \x + \xo 4:8 \xt Num. 25:4; Ps. 78:49; See Isa. 13:9-13\x*the fierce anger of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q2 has not turned back from us.”
\b
\m
\v 9 “In that day, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 4:9 \xt [Ps. 48:4, 5]\x*courage shall fail both king and officials. The priests shall be appalled and the prophets astounded.”
\v 10 Then I said, “Ah, Lord \nd God\nd*, \x + \xo 4:10 \xt Ezek. 14:9; [1 Kgs. 22:22]\x*surely you have utterly deceived this people and Jerusalem, saying, ‘It shall be well with you,’ whereas the sword has reached their very life.”
\b
\p
\v 11 At that time it will be said to this people and to Jerusalem, “A hot wind from \x + \xo 4:11 \xt See ch. 3:2\x*the bare heights in the desert toward the daughter of my people, not to winnow or cleanse,
\v 12 a wind too full for this comes for me. Now it is I who \x + \xo 4:12 \xt ch. 1:16\x*speak in judgment upon them.”
\b
\q1
\v 13 Behold, he comes up like clouds;
\q2 \x + \xo 4:13 \xt Isa. 5:28 \x*his chariots like the whirlwind;
\q1 his horses are \x + \xo 4:13 \xt 2 Sam. 1:23; Lam. 4:19 \x*swifter than eagles—
\q2 woe to us, \x + \xo 4:13 \xt ch. 9:19\x*for we are ruined!
\q1
\v 14 O Jerusalem, \x + \xo 4:14 \xt Ps. 51:2, 7; Isa. 1:16; James 4:8\x*wash your heart from evil,
\q2 that you may be saved.
\q1 How long shall your wicked thoughts
\q2 lodge within you?
\q1
\v 15 For a voice \x + \xo 4:15 \xt ch. 8:16 \x*declares from Dan
\q2 and proclaims trouble from \x + \xo 4:15 \xt See Josh. 24:33\x*Mount Ephraim.
\q1
\v 16 Warn the nations that he is coming;
\q2 announce to Jerusalem,
\q1 “Besiegers come \x + \xo 4:16 \xt ch. 5:15\x*from a distant land;
\q2 they shout against the cities of Judah.
\q1
\v 17 Like keepers of a field \x + \xo 4:17 \xt ch. 6:3; See 2 Kgs. 25:1-4\x*are they against her all around,
\q2 because she has rebelled against me,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 18 Your ways and your deeds
\q2 have brought this upon you.
\q1 This is your doom, and \x + \xo 4:18 \xt ch. 2:19\x*it is bitter;
\q2 it has reached your very heart.”
\s1 Anguish over Judah’s Desolation
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 4:19 \xt Isa. 16:11; Hab. 3:16; [ch. 9:1; Isa. 22:4]\x*My anguish, my anguish! I writhe in pain!
\q2 Oh the walls of my heart!
\q1 My heart is beating wildly;
\q2 I cannot keep silent,
\q1 for I hear the sound of the trumpet,
\q2 the alarm of war.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 4:20 \xt Ezek. 7:26 \x*Crash follows hard on crash;
\q2 the whole land is laid waste.
\q1 \x + \xo 4:20 \xt ch. 10:20; 49:29\x*Suddenly my tents are laid waste,
\q2 my curtains in a moment.
\q1
\v 21 How long must I see the standard
\q2 and hear the sound of the trumpet?
\b
\q1
\v 22 “For \x + \xo 4:22 \xt Ps. 82:5; Isa. 1:3 \x*my people are foolish;
\q2 they know me not;
\q1 they are stupid children;
\q2 they have no understanding.
\q1 \x + \xo 4:22 \xt Ps. 36:3; Isa. 1:16, 17; Rom. 16:19\x*They are ‘wise’—in doing evil!
\q2 But how to do good they know not.”
\b
\q1
\v 23 I looked on the earth, and behold, it was \x + \xo 4:23 \xt Gen. 1:2 \x*without form and void;
\q2 \x + \xo 4:23 \xt Isa. 5:30\x*and to the heavens, and they had no light.
\q1
\v 24 I looked on \x + \xo 4:24 \xt Nah. 1:5\x*the mountains, and behold, they were quaking,
\q2 and all the hills moved to and fro.
\q1
\v 25 \x + \xo 4:25 \xt [Zeph. 1:3]\x*I looked, and behold, there was no man,
\q2 and all the birds of the air had fled.
\q1
\v 26 I looked, and behold, the \x + \xo 4:26 \xt Ps. 107:34 \x*fruitful land was a desert,
\q2 and all its cities were laid in ruins
\q2 before the \nd Lord\nd*, before \x + \xo 4:26 \xt See ver. 8\x*his fierce anger.
\b
\p
\v 27 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, “The whole land shall be a desolation; \x + \xo 4:27 \xt ch. 5:10, 18; 30:11; 46:28; Neh. 9:31; Ezek. 11:13\x*yet I will not make a full end.
\b
\q1
\v 28 \x + \xo 4:28 \xt ch. 12:4; Hos. 4:3 \x*“For this the earth shall mourn,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:28 \xt Isa. 50:3 \x*and the heavens above be dark;
\q1 for I have spoken; I have purposed;
\q2 \x + \xo 4:28 \xt [Num. 23:19]\x*I have not relented, nor will I turn back.”
\b
\q1
\v 29 At the noise of horseman and archer
\q2 every city takes to flight;
\q1 they enter thickets; they climb among rocks;
\q2 all the cities are forsaken,
\q2 and \x + \xo 4:29 \xt See ver. 7\x*no man dwells in them.
\q1
\v 30 And you, O desolate one,
\q1 what do you mean that you dress in scarlet,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:30 \xt [Isa. 61:10] \x*that you adorn yourself with ornaments of gold,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:30 \xt [2 Kgs. 9:30] \x*that you enlarge your eyes with paint?
\q1 In vain you beautify yourself.
\q2 \x + \xo 4:30 \xt Lam. 1:2, 19; Ezek. 23:22\x*Your lovers despise you;
\q2 they seek your life.
\q1
\v 31 For I heard \x + \xo 4:31 \xt ch. 6:24; See Isa. 13:8 \x*a cry as of a woman in labor,
\q2 anguish as of one giving birth to her first child,
\q1 the cry of the daughter of Zion gasping for breath,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:31 \xt Isa. 1:15; Lam. 1:17\x*stretching out her hands,
\q1 “Woe is me! I am fainting before murderers.”
\c 5
\s1 Jerusalem Refused to Repent
\q1 \v 1 \x + \xo 5:1 \xt [2 Chr. 16:9] \x*Run to and fro through the streets of Jerusalem,
\q2 look and take note!
\q1 Search her squares to see
\q2 \x + \xo 5:1 \xt See Gen. 18:23-32 \x*if you can find a man,
\q1 one who does justice
\q2 and seeks truth,
\q1 \x + \xo 5:1 \xt [ver. 7]\x*that I may pardon her.
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 5:2 \xt [Titus 1:16] \x*Though they say, “As the \nd Lord\nd* lives,”
\q2 \x + \xo 5:2 \xt ch. 7:9\x*yet they swear falsely.
\q1
\v 3 O \nd Lord\nd*, do not your eyes look for truth?
\q1 \x + \xo 5:3 \xt See ch. 2:30 \x*You have struck them down,
\q2 but they felt no anguish;
\q1 you have consumed them,
\q2 but they refused to take correction.
\q1 \x + \xo 5:3 \xt Ezek. 3:8\x*They have made their faces harder than rock;
\q2 they have refused to repent.
\b
\q1
\v 4 Then I said, “These are only the poor;
\q2 they have no sense;
\q1 \x + \xo 5:4 \xt ch. 8:7; Mic. 3:1\x*for they do not know the way of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 the justice of their God.
\q1
\v 5 I will go to the great
\q2 and will speak to them,
\q1 for they know the way of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 the justice of their God.”
\q1 \x + \xo 5:5 \xt ch. 2:20; Ps. 2:3; 107:14\x*But they all alike had broken the yoke;
\q2 they had burst the bonds.
\b
\q1
\v 6 Therefore \x + \xo 5:6 \xt See ch. 4:7 \x*a lion from the forest shall strike them down;
\q2 a \x + \xo 5:6 \xt Hab. 1:8; Zeph. 3:3 \x*wolf from the desert shall devastate them.
\q1 \x + \xo 5:6 \xt Hos. 13:7 \x*A leopard is watching their cities;
\q2 everyone who goes out of them shall be torn in pieces,
\q1 because their transgressions are many,
\q2 their \x + \xo 5:6 \xt ch. 2:19\x*apostasies are great.
\b
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 5:7 \xt [ver. 1] \x*“How can I pardon you?
\q2 Your children have forsaken me
\q2 \x + \xo 5:7 \xt Deut. 32:21; Josh. 23:7; 2 Chr. 13:9; Gal. 4:8 \x*and have sworn by those who are no gods.
\q1 \x + \xo 5:7 \xt Deut. 32:15 \x*When I fed them to the full,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:7 \xt ch. 9:2; 23:10 \x*they committed adultery
\q2 \x + \xo 5:7 \xt Mic. 5:1\x*and trooped to the houses of whores.
\q1
\v 8 They were well-fed, lusty stallions,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:8 \xt ch. 13:27; 50:11 \x*each neighing \x + \xo 5:8 \xt Ezek. 22:11\x*for his neighbor’s wife.
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 5:9 \xt ver. 29; ch. 9:9; [Rom. 2:2]\x*Shall I not punish them for these things?
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 and shall I not avenge myself
\q2 on a nation such as this?
\b
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 5:10 \xt [ch. 39:8] \x*“Go up through her vine rows and destroy,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:10 \xt See ch. 4:27\x*but make not a full end;
\q1 strip away her branches,
\q2 for they are not the \nd Lord\nd*’s.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 5:11 \xt ch. 3:20\x*For the house of Israel and the house of Judah
\q2 have been utterly treacherous to me,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 12 They have spoken falsely of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q2 and have said, ‘He will do nothing;
\q1 \x + \xo 5:12 \xt [Gen. 3:4] \x*no disaster will come upon us,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:12 \xt [ch. 14:13; Isa. 28:15]\x*nor shall we see sword or famine.
\q1
\v 13 The prophets will become wind;
\q2 the word is not in them.
\q1 Thus shall it be done to them!’”
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Proclaims Judgment
\q1
\v 14 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of hosts:
\q1 “Because you have spoken this word,
\q1 behold, \x + \xo 5:14 \xt [ch. 1:9, 10] \x*I am making my words in your mouth \x + \xo 5:14 \xt [Obad. 18; Zech. 12:6; Rev. 11:5]\x*a fire,
\q2 and this people wood, and the fire shall consume them.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 5:15 \xt ch. 34:21, 22; Deut. 28:49; [ch. 1:15; Amos 6:14] \x*Behold, I am bringing against you
\q2 a nation from afar, O house of Israel,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1 It is an enduring nation;
\q2 it is an ancient nation,
\q1 a nation whose language you do not know,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:15 \xt Isa. 33:19\x*nor can you understand what they say.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 5:16 \xt See Isa. 5:28 \x*Their quiver is like \x + \xo 5:16 \xt Ps. 5:9\x*an open tomb;
\q2 they are all mighty warriors.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 5:17 \xt Lev. 26:16; Deut. 28:31, 33, 51 \x*They shall eat up your harvest and your food;
\q2 they shall eat up your sons and your daughters;
\q1 they shall eat up your flocks and your herds;
\q2 they shall eat up your vines and your fig trees;
\q1 your \x + \xo 5:17 \xt [Hos. 8:14]\x*fortified cities in which you trust
\q2 they shall beat down with the sword.”
\b
\p
\v 18 “But even in those days, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 5:18 \xt [See ver. 10 above]\x*I will not make a full end of you.
\v 19 And when your people say, \x + \xo 5:19 \xt ch. 13:22; 16:10, 11; 22:8, 9; Deut. 29:24, 25; 1 Kgs. 9:8, 9 \x*‘Why has the \nd Lord\nd* our God done all these things to us?’ you shall say to them, ‘As you have forsaken me and served foreign gods in your land, \x + \xo 5:19 \xt Deut. 4:27, 28; 28:47, 48, 68\x*so you shall serve foreigners in a land that is not yours.’”
\b
\q1
\v 20 Declare this in the house of Jacob;
\q2 proclaim it in Judah:
\q1
\v 21 “Hear this, \x + \xo 5:21 \xt Deut. 32:6; Isa. 6:9 \x*O foolish and senseless people,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:21 \xt [Matt. 13:14]\x*who have eyes, but see not,
\q2 who have ears, but hear not.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 5:22 \xt ch. 10:7 \x*Do you not fear me? declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q2 Do you not tremble before me?
\q1 I placed the sand \x + \xo 5:22 \xt Job 26:10; 38:10, 11; Ps. 104:9 \x*as the boundary for the sea,
\q2 a perpetual barrier that it cannot pass;
\q1 though the waves toss, they cannot prevail;
\q2 though \x + \xo 5:22 \xt ch. 51:55; [Ps. 46:3]\x*they roar, they cannot pass over it.
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 5:23 \xt ch. 6:28\x*But this people has a stubborn and rebellious heart;
\q2 they have turned aside and gone away.
\q1
\v 24 They do not say in their hearts,
\q2 ‘Let us fear the \nd Lord\nd* our God,
\q1 \x + \xo 5:24 \xt ch. 14:22; Deut. 11:14; Job 5:10; Ps. 147:8; Matt. 5:45 \x*who gives the rain in its season,
\q2 the autumn rain and the spring rain,
\q1 and keeps for us
\q2 \x + \xo 5:24 \xt Gen. 8:22\x*the weeks appointed for the harvest.’
\q1
\v 25 \x + \xo 5:25 \xt ch. 3:3\x*Your iniquities have turned these away,
\q2 and your sins have kept good from you.
\q1
\v 26 For wicked men are found among my people;
\q2 \x + \xo 5:26 \xt [Prov. 1:11] \x*they lurk like fowlers lying in wait.\f + \fr 5:26 \ft The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain\f*
\q1 \x + \xo 5:26 \xt Ps. 10:9; [Ps. 124:7]\x*They set a trap;
\q2 they catch men.
\q1
\v 27 Like a cage full of birds,
\q2 their houses are full of deceit;
\q1 therefore they have become great and rich;
\q2
\v 28 \x + \xo 5:28 \xt Deut. 32:15 \x*they have grown fat and sleek.
\q1 They know no bounds in deeds of evil;
\q2 \x + \xo 5:28 \xt [ch. 7:6; Isa. 1:23; Zech. 7:10]\x*they judge not with justice
\q1 the cause of the fatherless, to make it prosper,
\q2 and they do not defend the rights of the needy.
\q1
\v 29 \x + \xo 5:29 \xt See ver. 9\x*Shall I not punish them for these things?
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and shall I not avenge myself
\q2 on a nation such as this?”
\b
\q1
\v 30 An appalling and \x + \xo 5:30 \xt ch. 23:14; Hos. 6:10\x*horrible thing
\q2 has happened in the land:
\q1
\v 31 \x + \xo 5:31 \xt ch. 6:13; 14:14, 18; 20:6; 23:21, 25; 27:10, 15; 29:9; Ezek. 13:6 \x*the prophets prophesy falsely,
\q2 and the priests rule at their direction;
\q1 \x + \xo 5:31 \xt [Mic. 2:11]\x*my people love to have it so,
\q2 but what will you do when the end comes?
\c 6
\s1 Impending Disaster for Jerusalem
\q1 \v 1 Flee for safety, \x + \xo 6:1 \xt [Judg. 1:21] \x*O people of Benjamin,
\q2 from the midst of Jerusalem!
\q1 Blow the trumpet in \x + \xo 6:1 \xt See 2 Sam. 14:2 \x*Tekoa,
\q2 and raise a signal on \x + \xo 6:1 \xt Neh. 3:14 \x*Beth-haccherem,
\q1 for disaster looms \x + \xo 6:1 \xt See ch. 1:14\x*out of the north,
\q2 and great destruction.
\q1
\v 2 The lovely and delicately bred I will destroy,
\q2 \x + \xo 6:2 \xt See 2 Kgs. 19:21\x*the daughter of Zion.\f + \fr 6:2 \ft Or \fq I have likened the daughter of Zion to the loveliest pasture\f*
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 6:3 \xt [ch. 23:1] \x*Shepherds with their flocks shall come against her;
\q2 \x + \xo 6:3 \xt ch. 4:17\x*they shall pitch their tents around her;
\q2 they shall pasture, each in his place.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 6:4 \xt ch. 22:7; Joel 3:9; [ch. 51:27] \x*“Prepare war against her;
\q2 arise, and let us attack \x + \xo 6:4 \xt ch. 15:8\x*at noon!
\q1 Woe to us, for the day declines,
\q2 for the shadows of evening lengthen!
\q1
\v 5 Arise, and let us attack by night
\q2 and destroy her palaces!”
\b
\q1
\v 6 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts:
\q1 \x + \xo 6:6 \xt [Deut. 20:20] \x*“Cut down her trees;
\q2 \x + \xo 6:6 \xt 2 Kgs. 19:32; Isa. 37:33; Ezek. 26:8; Luke 19:43 \x*cast up a siege mound against Jerusalem.
\q1 This is the city that must be \x + \xo 6:6 \xt Luke 19:44\x*punished;
\q2 there is nothing but oppression within her.
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 6:7 \xt Isa. 57:20 \x*As a well keeps its water fresh,
\q2 so she keeps fresh her evil;
\q1 \x + \xo 6:7 \xt Ps. 55:9; Ezek. 7:11, 23\x*violence and destruction are heard within her;
\q2 sickness and wounds are ever before me.
\q1
\v 8 Be warned, O Jerusalem,
\q2 \x + \xo 6:8 \xt Ezek. 23:18; [Hos. 9:12] \x*lest I turn from you in disgust,
\q1 lest I make you \x + \xo 6:8 \xt See ch. 4:7\x*a desolation,
\q2 an uninhabited land.”
\b
\q1
\v 9 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts:
\q1 \x + \xo 6:9 \xt [Deut. 24:21]\x*“They shall glean thoroughly as a vine
\q2 the remnant of Israel;
\q1 like a grape gatherer pass your hand again
\q2 over its branches.”
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 6:10 \xt Isa. 28:9; 53:1 \x*To whom shall I speak and give warning,
\q2 that they may hear?
\q1 \x + \xo 6:10 \xt [Ex. 6:12; Acts 7:51] \x*Behold, their ears are uncircumcised,
\q2 \x + \xo 6:10 \xt ch. 7:26 \x*they cannot listen;
\q1 behold, \x + \xo 6:10 \xt ch. 20:8\x*the word of the \nd Lord\nd* is to them an object of scorn;
\q2 they take no pleasure in it.
\q1
\v 11 Therefore I am full of the wrath of the \nd Lord\nd*;
