\c 7
\s1 Evil in the Land
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*:
\v 2 \x + \xo 7:2 \xt ch. 26:2\x*“Stand in the gate of the \nd Lord\nd*’s house, and proclaim there this word, and say, Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, all you men of Judah who enter these gates to worship the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 3 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 7:3 \xt ch. 18:11; 26:13\x*Amend your ways and your deeds, and I will let you dwell in this place.
\v 4 \x + \xo 7:4 \xt [ver. 8]\x*Do not trust in these deceptive words: ‘This is the temple of the \nd Lord\nd*, the temple of the \nd Lord\nd*, the temple of the \nd Lord\nd*.’
\p
\v 5 “For if you truly \x + \xo 7:5 \xt ch. 22:3 \x*amend your ways and your deeds, if you truly \x + \xo 7:5 \xt Deut. 24:14\x*execute justice one with another,
\v 6 if you \x + \xo 7:6 \xt [See ver. 5 above] \x*do not oppress the sojourner, the fatherless, or the widow, \x + \xo 7:6 \xt [See ver. 5 above] \x*or shed innocent blood in this place, \x + \xo 7:6 \xt ch. 13:10; 25:6; Deut. 6:14\x*and if you do not go after other gods to your own harm,
\v 7 \x + \xo 7:7 \xt Deut. 4:40 \x*then I will let you dwell in this place, \x + \xo 7:7 \xt ch. 3:18\x*in the land that I gave of old to your fathers forever.
\p
\v 8 “Behold, you trust in deceptive words to no avail.
\v 9 \x + \xo 7:9 \xt Hos. 4:1, 2 \x*Will you steal, murder, commit adultery, \x + \xo 7:9 \xt ch. 5:2 \x*swear falsely, \x + \xo 7:9 \xt ch. 1:16 \x*make offerings to Baal, \x + \xo 7:9 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*and go after other gods that you have not known,
\v 10 and then come and stand before me in this house, \x + \xo 7:10 \xt ch. 32:34; 34:15\x*which is called by my name, and say, ‘We are delivered!’—only to go on doing all these abominations?
\v 11 \x + \xo 7:11 \xt Isa. 56:7 \x*Has this house, \x + \xo 7:11 \xt [See ver. 10 above] \x*which is called by my name, \x + \xo 7:11 \xt Cited Matt. 21:13; Mark 11:17; Luke 19:46; [Ezek. 7:22]\x*become a den of robbers in your eyes? Behold, I myself have seen it, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 12 Go now to \x + \xo 7:12 \xt Judg. 18:31; 1 Sam. 1:3 \x*my place that was in Shiloh, \x + \xo 7:12 \xt Deut. 12:11 \x*where I made my name dwell at first, and \x + \xo 7:12 \xt ch. 26:6; Ps. 78:60; See 1 Sam. 4:3-12\x*see what I did to it because of the evil of my people Israel.
\v 13 And now, because you have done all these things, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and \x + \xo 7:13 \xt ver. 25; 2 Chr. 36:15 \x*when I spoke to you persistently you did not listen, and \x + \xo 7:13 \xt Prov. 1:24; [ver. 27; Isa. 50:2; 65:12]\x*when I called you, you did not answer,
\v 14 therefore I will do to \x + \xo 7:14 \xt Deut. 12:5; 1 Kgs. 9:7 \x*the house \x + \xo 7:14 \xt [See ver. 10 above] \x*that is called by my name, and in which you trust, and to the place that I gave to you and to your fathers, \x + \xo 7:14 \xt [See ver. 12 above]\x*as I did to Shiloh.
\v 15 \x + \xo 7:15 \xt [See ver. 14 above] \x*And I will cast you out of my sight, \x + \xo 7:15 \xt 2 Kgs. 17:6, 23 \x*as I cast out all your kinsmen, all the offspring of \x + \xo 7:15 \xt Ps. 78:67; Hos. 4:17; 5:3, 9; 6:4; 12:1\x*Ephraim.
\p
\v 16 “As for you, \x + \xo 7:16 \xt ch. 11:14; 14:11; [Ex. 32:10; Deut. 9:14; 1 John 5:16]\x*do not pray for this people, or lift up a cry or prayer for them, and do not intercede with me, for I will not hear you.
\v 17 Do you not see what they are doing in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem?
\v 18 The children gather wood, the fathers kindle fire, \x + \xo 7:18 \xt Hos. 7:4 \x*and the women knead dough, to \x + \xo 7:18 \xt ch. 44:17, 19 \x*make cakes for \x + \xo 7:18 \xt [2 Kgs. 23:13] \x*the queen of heaven. And \x + \xo 7:18 \xt ch. 19:13 \x*they pour out drink offerings to other gods, \x + \xo 7:18 \xt ch. 11:17; Deut. 32:16, 21; 1 Kgs. 14:9; 16:2; 2 Chr. 34:25\x*to provoke me to anger.
\v 19 \x + \xo 7:19 \xt [Job 35:6] \x*Is it I whom they provoke? declares the \nd Lord\nd*. Is it not themselves, \x + \xo 7:19 \xt ch. 51:51\x*to their own shame?
\v 20 Therefore thus says the Lord \nd God\nd*: Behold, \x + \xo 7:20 \xt ch. 42:18; 44:6; 2 Chr. 34:25; Lam. 4:11 \x*my anger and my wrath will be poured out on this place, upon man and beast, upon the trees of the field and the fruit of the ground; \x + \xo 7:20 \xt ch. 17:27\x*it will burn and not be quenched.”
\p
\v 21 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 7:21 \xt See ch. 6:20\x*“Add your burnt offerings to your sacrifices, and eat the flesh.
\v 22 For in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt, I did not speak to your fathers or command them \x + \xo 7:22 \xt Hos. 6:6\x*concerning burnt offerings and sacrifices.
\v 23 But this command I gave them: \x + \xo 7:23 \xt ch. 11:4, 7; Ex. 15:26; Deut. 6:3 \x*‘Obey my voice, and \x + \xo 7:23 \xt Lev. 26:12 \x*I will be your God, and you shall be my people. \x + \xo 7:23 \xt Deut. 5:33 \x*And walk in all the way that I command you, \x + \xo 7:23 \xt ch. 42:6; Deut. 4:40\x*that it may be well with you.’
\v 24 \x + \xo 7:24 \xt Ps. 81:11 \x*But they did not obey or incline their ear, \x + \xo 7:24 \xt Ps. 81:12 \x*but walked in their own counsels and \x + \xo 7:24 \xt [ch. 3:17; Hos. 4:16] \x*the stubbornness of their evil hearts, and \x + \xo 7:24 \xt ch. 2:19, 27; 8:5; 15:6; 32:33\x*went backward and not forward.
\v 25 From the day that your fathers came out of the land of Egypt to this day, \x + \xo 7:25 \xt 2 Chr. 36:15, 16\x*I have persistently sent all my servants the prophets to them, day after day.
\v 26 \x + \xo 7:26 \xt [See ver. 24 above] \x*Yet they did not listen to me or incline their ear, \x + \xo 7:26 \xt 2 Chr. 30:8 \x*but stiffened their neck. \x + \xo 7:26 \xt ch. 16:12\x*They did worse than their fathers.
\p
\v 27 \x + \xo 7:27 \xt ch. 1:17 \x*“So you shall speak all these words to them, but they will not listen to you. \x + \xo 7:27 \xt [ver. 13]\x*You shall call to them, but they will not answer you.
\v 28 And you shall say to them, ‘This is the nation that did not obey the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* their God, and did not accept discipline; \x + \xo 7:28 \xt ch. 9:3\x*truth has perished; it is cut off from their lips.
\b
\q1
\v 29 \x + \xo 7:29 \xt [Job 1:20] \x*“‘Cut off your hair and cast it away;
\q2 raise a lamentation on \x + \xo 7:29 \xt See ch. 3:2\x*the bare heights,
\q1 for the \nd Lord\nd* has rejected and forsaken
\q2 the generation of his wrath.’
\s1 The Valley of Slaughter
\p
\v 30 “For the sons of Judah have done evil in my sight, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. They have set \x + \xo 7:30 \xt ch. 32:34; Ezek. 5:11; 7:20; [ch. 19:5; 2 Kgs. 21:4, 7] \x*their detestable things in the house \x + \xo 7:30 \xt See ver. 10\x*that is called by my name, to \x + \xo 7:30 \xt ch. 32:34; Ezek. 5:11; 7:20; [ch. 19:5; 2 Kgs. 21:4, 7] \x*defile it.
\v 31 And they have built the high places of \x + \xo 7:31 \xt 2 Kgs. 23:10 \x*Topheth, which is in \x + \xo 7:31 \xt [ch. 31:40; Josh. 18:16] \x*the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, \x + \xo 7:31 \xt Ps. 106:38 \x*to burn their sons and their daughters in the fire, \x + \xo 7:31 \xt Deut. 17:3; [ver. 21, 22]\x*which I did not command, nor did it come into my mind.
\v 32 \x + \xo 7:32 \xt ch. 19:6 \x*Therefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when it will no more be called \x + \xo 7:32 \xt [See ver. 31 above] \x*Topheth, or \x + \xo 7:32 \xt [See ver. 31 above] \x*the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter; \x + \xo 7:32 \xt ch. 19:11; [Ezek. 6:5]\x*for they will bury in Topheth, because there is no room elsewhere.
\v 33 \x + \xo 7:33 \xt ch. 12:9; 16:4; 19:7; 34:20; Deut. 28:26; Ps. 79:2 \x*And the dead bodies of this people will be food for the birds of the air, and for the beasts of the earth, \x + \xo 7:33 \xt [Isa. 17:2]\x*and none will frighten them away.
\v 34 \x + \xo 7:34 \xt ch. 16:9; 25:10; Ps. 78:63; Isa. 24:7, 8; Rev. 18:22, 23; [Ezek. 26:13; Hos. 2:11] \x*And I will silence in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, \x + \xo 7:34 \xt ch. 27:17; 44:2, 6; Lev. 26:31, 33\x*for the land shall become a waste.
\c 8
\p \v 1 “At that time, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, the bones of the kings of Judah, the bones of its officials, the bones of the priests, the bones of the prophets, and the bones of the inhabitants of Jerusalem shall be brought out of their tombs.
\v 2 And they shall be spread \x + \xo 8:2 \xt Deut. 4:19; 2 Kgs. 21:3; 23:5; [Job 31:26-28; Ezek. 8:16] \x*before the sun and the moon and all the host of heaven, which they have loved and served, which they have gone after, and which they have sought and worshiped. \x + \xo 8:2 \xt [Job 27:19] \x*And they shall not be gathered or buried. \x + \xo 8:2 \xt ch. 9:22; 16:4; 25:33\x*They shall be as dung on the surface of the ground.
\v 3 \x + \xo 8:3 \xt [Job 3:21, 22; 7:15, 16; Rev. 9:6] \x*Death shall be preferred to life by all the remnant that remains of this evil family \x + \xo 8:3 \xt ch. 23:3, 8; 29:14, 18; 32:37; Dan. 9:7\x*in all the places where I have driven them, declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts.
\s1 Sin and Treachery
