\q2 Is there no physician there?
\q1 Why then has the health of the daughter of my people
\q2 not been restored?
\c 9
\q1
\v 1 \f + \fr 9:1 \ft Ch 8:23 in Hebrew\f* \x + \xo 9:1 \xt See ch. 13:17 \x*Oh that my head were waters,
\q2 and my eyes a fountain of tears,
\q1 that I might weep day and night
\q2 for the slain of \x + \xo 9:1 \xt [See ch. 8:21 above]\x*the daughter of my people!
\q1
\v 2 \f + \fr 9:2 \ft Ch 9:1 in Hebrew\f* Oh that I had in the desert
\q2 a travelers’ lodging place,
\q1 that I might leave my people
\q2 and go away from them!
\q1 For they are all \x + \xo 9:2 \xt ch. 5:7, 8; 23:10; Hos. 7:4 \x*adulterers,
\q2 a company of \x + \xo 9:2 \xt Isa. 21:2\x*treacherous men.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 9:3 \xt [Ps. 64:3] \x*They bend their tongue like a bow;
\q2 falsehood and not truth has grown strong\f + \fr 9:3 \ft Septuagint; Hebrew \fq and not for truth they have grown strong\f* in the land;
\q1 for they proceed from evil to evil,
\q2 \x + \xo 9:3 \xt [Judg. 2:10; Hos. 4:1]\x*and they do not know me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 9:4 \xt ch. 12:6; Ps. 41:9; Mic. 7:5 \x*Let everyone beware of his neighbor,
\q2 and put no trust in any brother,
\q1 for every \x + \xo 9:4 \xt [Gen. 27:36] \x*brother is a deceiver,
\q2 and every neighbor \x + \xo 9:4 \xt ch. 6:28; [Lev. 19:16]\x*goes about as a slanderer.
\q1
\v 5 Everyone deceives his neighbor,
\q2 and no one speaks the truth;
\q1 they have taught their tongue to speak lies;
\q2 they weary themselves committing iniquity.
\q1
\v 6 Heaping oppression upon oppression, and deceit upon deceit,
\q2 \x + \xo 9:6 \xt ch. 8:5\x*they refuse to know me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 7 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts:
\q1 “Behold, \x + \xo 9:7 \xt Isa. 1:25 \x*I will refine them and \x + \xo 9:7 \xt ch. 6:27 \x*test them,
\q2 for what else can I do, \x + \xo 9:7 \xt [See ch. 8:21 above]\x*because of my people?
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 9:8 \xt [Ps. 57:4] \x*Their tongue is a deadly arrow;
\q2 \x + \xo 9:8 \xt [Ps. 12:2; 120:3] \x*it speaks deceitfully;
\q1 with his mouth \x + \xo 9:8 \xt Ps. 28:3 \x*each speaks peace to his neighbor,
\q2 but in his heart \x + \xo 9:8 \xt Hos. 7:6\x*he plans an ambush for him.
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 9:9 \xt ch. 5:9, 29\x*Shall I not punish them for these things? declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and shall I not avenge myself
\q2 on a nation such as this?
\b
\q1
\v 10 “I will take up weeping and wailing for the mountains,
\q2 and a lamentation for \x + \xo 9:10 \xt ch. 12:4; Ps. 65:12 \x*the pastures of the wilderness,
\q1 \x + \xo 9:10 \xt ver. 12 \x*because they are laid waste so that no one passes through,
\q2 and the lowing of cattle is not heard;
\q1 \x + \xo 9:10 \xt ch. 4:25\x*both the birds of the air and the beasts
\q2 have fled and are gone.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 9:11 \xt Isa. 25:2 \x*I will make Jerusalem a heap of ruins,
\q2 \x + \xo 9:11 \xt ch. 10:22; 49:33; 51:37 \x*a lair of jackals,
\q1 \x + \xo 9:11 \xt ch. 34:22; 44:6\x*and I will make the cities of Judah a desolation,
\q2 without inhabitant.”
\b
\p
\v 12 \x + \xo 9:12 \xt ch. 23:18; Ps. 107:43; Hos. 14:9 \x*Who is the man so wise that he can understand this? To whom has the mouth of the \nd Lord\nd* spoken, that he may declare it? Why is the land ruined \x + \xo 9:12 \xt ver. 10\x*and laid waste like a wilderness, so that no one passes through?
\v 13 And the \nd Lord\nd* says: \x + \xo 9:13 \xt [Ps. 89:30-32]\x*“Because they have forsaken my law that I set before them, and have not obeyed my voice or walked in accord with it,
\v 14 but \x + \xo 9:14 \xt See ch. 3:17\x*have stubbornly followed their own hearts and have gone after the Baals, as their fathers taught them.
\v 15 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 9:15 \xt Deut. 29:18; [Ps. 80:5] \x*Behold, I will feed this people with bitter food, and give them \x + \xo 9:15 \xt See ch. 8:14\x*poisonous water to drink.
\v 16 \x + \xo 9:16 \xt Lev. 26:33; Deut. 28:64 \x*I will scatter them among the nations \x + \xo 9:16 \xt ch. 15:14 \x*whom neither they nor their fathers have known, and I will \x + \xo 9:16 \xt ch. 14:12; [ch. 49:37; Ezek. 5:2, 12]\x*send the sword after them, until I have consumed them.”
\b
\q1
\v 17 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts:
\q1 \x + \xo 9:17 \xt [2 Chr. 35:25]\x*“Consider, and call for the mourning women to come;
\q2 send for the skillful women to come;
\q1
\v 18 let them make haste \x + \xo 9:18 \xt Amos 5:16; [Matt. 9:23; Mark 5:38] \x*and raise a wailing over us,
\q2 \x + \xo 9:18 \xt ver. 1; ch. 14:17\x*that our eyes may run down with tears
\q2 and our eyelids flow with water.
\q1
\v 19 For a sound of wailing is heard from Zion:
\q2 \x + \xo 9:19 \xt ch. 4:13\x*‘How we are ruined!
\q2 We are utterly shamed,
\q1 because we have left the land,
\q2 because they have cast down our dwellings.’”
\b
\q1
\v 20 Hear, O women, the word of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and let your ear receive the word of his mouth;
\q1 teach to your daughters a lament,
\q2 and each to her neighbor a dirge.
\q1
\v 21 For death has come up into our windows;
\q2 it has entered our palaces,
\q1 \x + \xo 9:21 \xt ch. 6:11\x*cutting off the children from the streets
\q2 and the young men from the squares.
\q1
\v 22 Speak: “Thus declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 \x + \xo 9:22 \xt See ch. 8:2 \x*‘The dead bodies of men shall fall
\q2 like dung upon the open field,
\q1 \x + \xo 9:22 \xt [Lev. 23:22; Job 5:26]\x*like sheaves after the reaper,
\q2 and none shall gather them.’”
\b
\p
\v 23 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 9:23 \xt Prov. 3:5; 21:30; Eccles. 9:11\x*“Let not the wise man boast in his wisdom, let not the mighty man boast in his might, let not the rich man boast in his riches,
\v 24 but \x + \xo 9:24 \xt [Ps. 34:2; 1 Cor. 1:31; 2 Cor. 10:17] \x*let him who boasts boast in this, that he understands and knows me, that I am the \nd Lord\nd* who practices steadfast love, justice, and righteousness in the earth. \x + \xo 9:24 \xt [Mic. 6:8; 7:18]\x*For in these things I delight, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\p
\v 25 “Behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when \x + \xo 9:25 \xt [Isa. 24:21]\x*I will punish all those who are circumcised merely in the flesh—
\v 26 \x + \xo 9:26 \xt [ch. 25:19-21] \x*Egypt, Judah, Edom, the sons of Ammon, Moab, and \x + \xo 9:26 \xt ch. 25:23; 49:32; [Lev. 19:27] \x*all who dwell in the desert who cut the corners of their hair, for all these nations are uncircumcised, and all the house of Israel are \x + \xo 9:26 \xt Lev. 26:41; Deut. 10:16; Ezek. 44:7; Rom. 2:28, 29; [ch. 4:4]\x*uncircumcised in heart.”
\c 10
\s1 Idols and the Living God
\p \v 1 Hear the word that the \nd Lord\nd* speaks to you, O house of Israel.
\v 2 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 “Learn not the way of the nations,
\q2 nor be dismayed at the signs of the heavens
\q2 because the nations are dismayed at them,
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 10:3 \xt Isa. 44:9 \x*for the customs of the peoples are vanity.\f + \fr 10:3 \ft Or \fq vapor\ft , or \fq mist\f*
\q1 \x + \xo 10:3 \xt Isa. 40:20; 45:20\x*A tree from the forest is cut down
\q2 and worked with an axe by the hands of a craftsman.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 10:4 \xt Isa. 40:19 \x*They decorate it with silver and gold;
\q2 \x + \xo 10:4 \xt Isa. 41:7\x*they fasten it with hammer and nails
\q2 so that it cannot move.
\q1
\v 5 Their idols\f + \fr 10:5 \ft Hebrew \fq They\f* are like scarecrows in a cucumber field,
\q2 and \x + \xo 10:5 \xt Ps. 115:5; 135:16; Hab. 2:18, 19; 1 Cor. 12:2 \x*they cannot speak;
\q1 \x + \xo 10:5 \xt Ps. 115:7; Isa. 46:7 \x*they have to be carried,
\q2 for they cannot walk.
\q1 Do not be afraid of them,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:5 \xt Isa. 41:23\x*for they cannot do evil,
\q2 neither is it in them to do good.”
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 10:6 \xt ch. 49:19; Ex. 15:11; Ps. 86:8, 10\x*There is none like you, O \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 you are great, and your name is great in might.
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 10:7 \xt ch. 5:22; Rev. 15:4\x*Who would not fear you, O King of the nations?
\q2 For this is your due;
\q1 for among all the wise ones of the nations
\q2 and in all their kingdoms
\q2 there is none like you.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 10:8 \xt [Isa. 41:29; Hab. 2:18; Zech. 10:2] \x*They are both \x + \xo 10:8 \xt ver. 21\x*stupid and foolish;
\q2 the instruction of idols is but wood!
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 10:9 \xt Isa. 40:19 \x*Beaten silver is brought from \x + \xo 10:9 \xt Gen. 10:4; See 1 Kgs. 10:22 \x*Tarshish,
\q2 and gold from \x + \xo 10:9 \xt Dan. 10:5 \x*Uphaz.
\q1 \x + \xo 10:9 \xt Isa. 40:19 \x*They are the work of the craftsman and of the hands of the goldsmith;
\q2 their clothing is violet and purple;
\q2 \x + \xo 10:9 \xt Ps. 115:4\x*they are all the work of skilled men.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 10:10 \xt Deut. 32:4; Ps. 31:5 \x*But the \nd Lord\nd* is the true God;
\q2 \x + \xo 10:10 \xt Ps. 42:2\x*he is the living God and the everlasting King.
\q1 At his wrath the earth quakes,
\q2 and the nations cannot endure his indignation.
\b
\p
\v 11 Thus shall you say to them: \x + \xo 10:11 \xt [Ps. 96:5] \x*“The gods who did not make the heavens and the earth \x + \xo 10:11 \xt ver. 15; Isa. 2:18; Zech. 13:2\x*shall perish from the earth and from under the heavens.”\f + \fr 10:11 \ft This verse is in Aramaic\f*
\b
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 10:12 \xt For ver. 12-16, see ch. 51:15-19 \x*It is he who \x + \xo 10:12 \xt Gen. 1:1, 6, 9; Ps. 104:5; Prov. 3:19 \x*made the earth by his power,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:12 \xt Gen. 1:1, 6, 9; Ps. 104:5; Prov. 3:19 \x*who established the world by his wisdom,
\q2 and \x + \xo 10:12 \xt Job 9:8\x*by his understanding stretched out the heavens.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 10:13 \xt [Job 38:34; Ps. 104:6, 7] \x*When he utters his voice, there is a tumult of waters in the heavens,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:13 \xt Ps. 135:7 \x*and he makes the mist rise from the ends of the earth.
\q1 \x + \xo 10:13 \xt Ps. 135:7 \x*He makes lightning \x + \xo 10:13 \xt ch. 14:22; Job 5:10 \x*for the rain,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:13 \xt Ps. 135:7 \x*and he brings forth the wind \x + \xo 10:13 \xt Job 38:22\x*from his storehouses.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 10:14 \xt ver. 8; Prov. 30:2; [Rom. 1:22] \x*Every man is stupid and without knowledge;
\q2 \x + \xo 10:14 \xt See Isa. 42:17 \x*every goldsmith is put to shame by his idols,
\q1 for his images are false,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:14 \xt Ps. 135:17; Hab. 2:19\x*and there is no breath in them.
\q1
\v 15 They are worthless, a work of delusion;
\q2 at the time of their punishment they shall perish.
\q1
\v 16 Not like these is he who is \x + \xo 10:16 \xt Ps. 16:5 \x*the portion of Jacob,
\q2 for he is the one who formed all things,
\q1 \x + \xo 10:16 \xt Deut. 32:9 \x*and Israel is the tribe of his inheritance;
\q2 \x + \xo 10:16 \xt ch. 31:35; 32:18; 50:34\x*the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts is his name.
\b
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 10:17 \xt [ch. 6:1; Ezek. 12:3]\x*Gather up your bundle from the ground,
\q2 O you who dwell under siege!
\q1
\v 18 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 \x + \xo 10:18 \xt 1 Sam. 25:29 \x*“Behold, I am slinging out the inhabitants of the land
\q2 at this time,
\q1 \x + \xo 10:18 \xt Deut. 28:20\x*and I will bring distress on them,
\q2 that they may feel it.”
\b
\q1
\v 19 Woe is me because of my hurt!
\q2 \x + \xo 10:19 \xt ch. 14:17; 30:12\x*My wound is grievous.
\q1 But I said, “Truly this is an affliction,
\q2 and I must bear it.”
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 10:20 \xt ch. 4:20; [Isa. 54:2] \x*My tent is destroyed,
\q2 and all my cords are broken;
\q1 my children have gone from me,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:20 \xt ch. 31:15\x*and they are not;
\q1 there is no one to spread my tent again
\q2 and \x + \xo 10:20 \xt ch. 4:20; [Isa. 54:2] \x*to set up my curtains.
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 10:21 \xt ch. 23:1; Ezek. 34:2 \x*For the shepherds \x + \xo 10:21 \xt ver. 8 \x*are stupid
\q2 and do not inquire of the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q1 therefore they have not prospered,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:21 \xt Ezek. 34:5, 6\x*and all their flock is scattered.
\b
\q1
\v 22 A voice, a rumor! Behold, it comes!—
\q2 \x + \xo 10:22 \xt See ch. 1:13 \x*a great commotion out of the north country
\q1 to make \x + \xo 10:22 \xt See ch. 9:11\x*the cities of Judah a desolation,
\q2 \x + \xo 10:22 \xt See ch. 9:11\x*a lair of jackals.
\b
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 10:23 \xt Prov. 16:1; 20:24; Dan. 5:23\x*I know, O \nd Lord\nd*, that the way of man is not in himself,
\q2 that it is not in man who walks to direct his steps.
\q1
\v 24 \x + \xo 10:24 \xt ch. 30:11; 46:28; Ps. 6:1; 38:1\x*Correct me, O \nd Lord\nd*, but in justice;
\q2 not in your anger, lest you bring me to nothing.
\b
\q1
\v 25 \x + \xo 10:25 \xt Ps. 79:6, 7 \x*Pour out your wrath on the nations that know you not,
\q2 and on the peoples that call not on your name,
\q1 \x + \xo 10:25 \xt ch. 8:16; 30:16; Ps. 14:4\x*for they have devoured Jacob;
\q2 they have devoured him and consumed him,
\q2 and have laid waste his habitation.
\c 11
\s1 The Broken Covenant
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*:
\v 2 \x + \xo 11:2 \xt ver. 6, 8; [2 Kgs. 23:3]\x*“Hear the words of this covenant, and speak to the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
\v 3 You shall say to them, Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 11:3 \xt Deut. 27:26; Gal. 3:10\x*Cursed be the man who does not hear the words of this covenant
\v 4 that I commanded your fathers when I brought them out of the land of Egypt, \x + \xo 11:4 \xt Deut. 4:20 \x*from the iron furnace, saying, \x + \xo 11:4 \xt ch. 7:22, 23; Lev. 26:3, 12\x*Listen to my voice, and do all that I command you. \x + \xo 11:4 \xt ch. 7:22, 23; Lev. 26:3, 12\x*So shall you be my people, and I will be your God,
\v 5 \x + \xo 11:5 \xt Deut. 7:12, 13; Ps. 105:9, 10 \x*that I may confirm the oath that I swore to your fathers, \x + \xo 11:5 \xt See Ex. 3:8\x*to give them a land flowing with milk and honey, as at this day.” Then I answered, “So be it, \nd Lord\nd*.”
\p
\v 6 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, \x + \xo 11:6 \xt [ch. 19:2] \x*“Proclaim all these words in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem: \x + \xo 11:6 \xt ver. 2, 8; [2 Kgs. 23:3]\x*Hear the words of this covenant and do them.
\v 7 For I solemnly warned your fathers when I brought them up out of the land of Egypt, \x + \xo 11:7 \xt ch. 7:25; See 2 Chr. 36:15 \x*warning them persistently, even to this day, saying, \x + \xo 11:7 \xt [See ver. 4 above]\x*Obey my voice.
\v 8 \x + \xo 11:8 \xt ch. 7:26; 32:23 \x*Yet they did not obey or incline their ear, \x + \xo 11:8 \xt See ch. 3:17 \x*but everyone walked in the stubbornness of his evil heart. Therefore I brought upon them all \x + \xo 11:8 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*the words of this covenant, which I commanded them to do, but they did not.”
\p
\v 9 Again the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, \x + \xo 11:9 \xt Ezek. 22:25; [Isa. 8:12; Hos. 6:9]\x*“A conspiracy exists among the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
\v 10 They have turned back to \x + \xo 11:10 \xt [ch. 17:23; Ps. 78:8; 79:8; Ezek. 20:18] \x*the iniquities of their forefathers, who refused to hear my words. \x + \xo 11:10 \xt [ch. 17:23; Ps. 78:8; 79:8; Ezek. 20:18] \x*They have gone after other gods to serve them. \x + \xo 11:10 \xt Deut. 31:16, 20\x*The house of Israel and the house of Judah have broken my covenant that I made with their fathers.
\v 11 Therefore, thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, Behold, I am bringing disaster upon them that they cannot escape. \x + \xo 11:11 \xt Prov. 1:28; Isa. 1:15; Ezek. 8:18; Mic. 3:4\x*Though they cry to me, I will not listen to them.
\v 12 Then the cities of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem \x + \xo 11:12 \xt ch. 2:28; [Acts 17:16]\x*will go and cry to the gods to whom they make offerings, \x + \xo 11:12 \xt ch. 2:28; [Acts 17:16]\x*but they cannot save them in the time of their trouble.
\v 13 \x + \xo 11:13 \xt [See ver. 12 above] \x*For your gods have become as many as your cities, O Judah, and as many as the streets of Jerusalem are the altars you have set up to shame, \x + \xo 11:13 \xt [Hos. 9:10]; See Judg. 6:25-32\x*altars to make offerings to Baal.
\p
\v 14 “Therefore \x + \xo 11:14 \xt ch. 7:16; [Heb. 10:26; 1 John 5:16] \x*do not pray for this people, or lift up a cry or prayer on their behalf, \x + \xo 11:14 \xt [See ver. 11 above]\x*for I will not listen when they call to me in the time of their trouble.
\v 15 \x + \xo 11:15 \xt Isa. 1:11, 12 \x*What right has my beloved in my house, \x + \xo 11:15 \xt [Ezek. 16:25] \x*when she has done many vile deeds? Can even sacrificial flesh avert your doom? \x + \xo 11:15 \xt Prov. 2:14\x*Can you then exult?
\v 16 The \nd Lord\nd* once called you \x + \xo 11:16 \xt Ps. 52:8; [Hos. 14:6] \x*‘a green olive tree, beautiful with good fruit.’ But \x + \xo 11:16 \xt [Ps. 83:2] \x*with the roar of a great tempest he will set fire to it, and \x + \xo 11:16 \xt Rom. 11:17, 20\x*its branches will be consumed.
\v 17 The \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, \x + \xo 11:17 \xt ch. 2:21; Isa. 5:2 \x*who planted you, has decreed disaster against you, because of the evil that the house of Israel and the house of Judah have done, \x + \xo 11:17 \xt See ch. 7:18\x*provoking me to anger by making offerings to Baal.”
\b
\q1
\v 18 The \nd Lord\nd* made it known to me and I knew;
\q2 then you showed me their deeds.
\q1
\v 19 But I was \x + \xo 11:19 \xt Isa. 53:7; [Rev. 5:6] \x*like a gentle lamb
\q2 led to the slaughter.
\q1 I did not know \x + \xo 11:19 \xt ch. 18:18; Lam. 3:60, 61 \x*it was against me
\q2 they devised schemes, saying,
\q1 “Let us destroy the tree with its fruit,
\q2 \x + \xo 11:19 \xt Ps. 83:4; Isa. 53:8 \x*let us cut him off from \x + \xo 11:19 \xt Ps. 27:13\x*the land of the living,
\q2 that his name be remembered no more.”
\q1
\v 20 But, O \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, who judges righteously,
\q2 who \x + \xo 11:20 \xt ch. 17:10; 20:12; Ps. 7:9; Rev. 2:23 \x*tests \x + \xo 11:20 \xt See 1 Sam. 16:7 \x*the heart and the mind,
\q1 \x + \xo 11:20 \xt ch. 15:15; 17:18; 20:12; Lam. 3:64\x*let me see your vengeance upon them,
\q2 for to you have I committed my cause.
\b
\p
\v 21 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning the men of \x + \xo 11:21 \xt Josh. 21:18 \x*Anathoth, \x + \xo 11:21 \xt [ch. 12:6; Matt. 13:57] \x*who seek your life, and say, \x + \xo 11:21 \xt Isa. 30:10\x*“Do not prophesy in the name of the \nd Lord\nd*, or you will die by our hand”—
\v 22 therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts: “Behold, I will punish them. The young men shall die by the sword, their sons and their daughters shall die by famine,
\v 23 and none of them shall be left. For I will bring disaster upon the men of \x + \xo 11:23 \xt Josh. 21:18 \x*Anathoth, \x + \xo 11:23 \xt ch. 23:12\x*the year of their punishment.”
\c 12
\s1 Jeremiah’s Complaint
\q1 \v 1 \x + \xo 12:1 \xt Ezra 9:15; Ps. 51:4; Lam. 1:18; Dan. 9:7 \x*Righteous are you, O \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 when I complain to you;
\q2 yet I would plead my case before you.
\q1 \x + \xo 12:1 \xt Job 12:6; Ps. 37:1, 7; 92:7; Hab. 1:13; Mal. 3:15; See Job 21:7-15; Ps. 73:3-12 \x*Why does the way of the wicked prosper?
\q2 Why do all \x + \xo 12:1 \xt [Isa. 21:2]\x*who are treacherous thrive?
\q1
\v 2 You plant them, and they take root;
\q2 they grow and produce fruit;
\q1 \x + \xo 12:2 \xt Isa. 29:13\x*you are near in their mouth
\q2 and far from their heart.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 12:3 \xt ch. 15:15; Ps. 139:1 \x*But you, O \nd Lord\nd*, know me;
\q2 \x + \xo 12:3 \xt Ps. 17:3 \x*you see me, and test my heart toward you.
\q1 \x + \xo 12:3 \xt [2 Pet. 2:12] \x*Pull them out like sheep for the slaughter,
\q2 and set them apart for \x + \xo 12:3 \xt James 5:5\x*the day of slaughter.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 12:4 \xt ver. 11; ch. 9:10; 23:10 \x*How long will the land mourn
\q2 and the grass of every field wither?
\q1 \x + \xo 12:4 \xt Ps. 107:34 \x*For the evil of those who dwell in it
\q2 \x + \xo 12:4 \xt ch. 4:25; 7:20; 9:10; Hos. 4:3; [Rom. 8:22]\x*the beasts and the birds are swept away,
\q2 because they said, “He will not see our latter end.”
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Answers Jeremiah
\q1
\v 5 “If you have raced with men on foot, and they have wearied you,
\q2 how will you compete with horses?
\q1 And if in a safe land you are so trusting,
\q2 what will you do in \x + \xo 12:5 \xt ch. 49:19; 50:44; Zech. 11:3; [Josh. 3:15]\x*the thicket of the Jordan?
\q1
\v 6 For \x + \xo 12:6 \xt ch. 9:4; [ch. 11:19, 21] \x*even your brothers and the house of your father,
\q2 \x + \xo 12:6 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*even they have dealt treacherously with you;
\q2 they are in full cry after you;
\q1 \x + \xo 12:6 \xt Prov. 26:25\x*do not believe them,
\q2 though they speak friendly words to you.”
\b
\q1
\v 7 “I have forsaken my house;
\q2 I have abandoned \x + \xo 12:7 \xt Isa. 19:25 \x*my heritage;
\q1 I have given \x + \xo 12:7 \xt ch. 11:15\x*the beloved of my soul
\q2 into the hands of her enemies.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 12:8 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*My heritage has become to me
\q2 like a lion in the forest;
\q1 she has lifted up her voice against me;
\q2 therefore I hate her.
\q1
\v 9 Is \x + \xo 12:9 \xt [See ver. 7 above] \x*my heritage to me like \x + \xo 12:9 \xt Isa. 46:11 \x*a hyena’s lair?
\q2 Are the \x + \xo 12:9 \xt Isa. 46:11 \x*birds of prey against her all around?
\q1 Go, \x + \xo 12:9 \xt ch. 7:33; Isa. 56:9; [Ezek. 39:17; Rev. 19:17]\x*assemble all the wild beasts;
\q2 bring them to devour.
\q1
\v 10 Many shepherds have destroyed my vineyard;
\q2 \x + \xo 12:10 \xt Isa. 63:18\x*they have trampled down my portion;
\q1 they have made my pleasant portion
\q2 a desolate wilderness.
\q1
\v 11 They have made it a desolation;
\q2 desolate, \x + \xo 12:11 \xt [See ver. 4 above] \x*it mourns to me.
\q1 The whole land is made desolate,
\q2 \x + \xo 12:11 \xt Isa. 42:25\x*but no man lays it to heart.
\q1
\v 12 Upon all the bare heights in the desert
\q2 destroyers have come,
\q1 for the sword of the \nd Lord\nd* devours
\q2 from one end of the land to the other;
\q2 no flesh has peace.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 12:13 \xt [Lev. 26:16; Deut. 28:38; Mic. 6:15; Hag. 1:6] \x*They have sown wheat and have reaped thorns;
\q2 \x + \xo 12:13 \xt Isa. 55:2; Hab. 2:13 \x*they have tired themselves out but profit nothing.
\q1 They shall be ashamed of their\f + \fr 12:13 \ft Hebrew \fq your\f* harvests
\q2 \x + \xo 12:13 \xt ch. 4:8, 26; 25:37, 38; 30:24; 49:37; 51:45; Lam. 1:12; 4:11\x*because of the fierce anger of the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\b
\p
\v 14 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning all \x + \xo 12:14 \xt [Ps. 137:7]; See Ezek. 25 \x*my evil neighbors \x + \xo 12:14 \xt Zech. 2:8 \x*who touch the heritage that \x + \xo 12:14 \xt ch. 3:18\x*I have given my people Israel to inherit: “Behold, I will pluck them up from their land, and I will pluck up the house of Judah from among them.
\v 15 And after I have plucked them up, I will again have compassion on them, \x + \xo 12:15 \xt ch. 48:47; 49:6\x*and I will bring them again each to his heritage and each to his land.
\v 16 And it shall come to pass, if they will diligently learn the ways of my people, \x + \xo 12:16 \xt ch. 4:2 \x*to swear by my name, ‘As the \nd Lord\nd* lives,’ even as they taught my people to swear by Baal, \x + \xo 12:16 \xt ch. 24:6; [1 Pet. 2:5]\x*then they shall be built up in the midst of my people.
\v 17 \x + \xo 12:17 \xt [Isa. 60:12]\x*But if any nation will not listen, then I will utterly pluck it up and destroy it, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\c 13
\s1 The Ruined Loincloth
\p \v 1 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* to me, “Go and buy a linen loincloth and \x + \xo 13:1 \xt Ex. 28:39; Lev. 16:4; [Acts 21:11]\x*put it around your waist, and do not dip it in water.”
\v 2 So I bought a loincloth according to the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, and put it around my waist.
\v 3 And the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me a second time,
\v 4 “Take the loincloth that you have bought, which is around your waist, and arise, \x + \xo 13:4 \xt [ch. 51:59, 63] \x*go to the Euphrates and hide it there in \x + \xo 13:4 \xt Isa. 7:19\x*a cleft of the rock.”
\v 5 So I went and hid it by the Euphrates, as the \nd Lord\nd* commanded me.
\v 6 And after many days the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, “Arise, go to the Euphrates, and take from there \x + \xo 13:6 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*the loincloth that I commanded you to hide there.”
\v 7 Then I went to the Euphrates, and dug, and I took \x + \xo 13:7 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*the loincloth from the place where I had hidden it. And behold, the loincloth was \x + \xo 13:7 \xt ch. 18:4 \x*spoiled; it was \x + \xo 13:7 \xt [Ezek. 15:4, 5]\x*good for nothing.
\p
\v 8 Then the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me:
\v 9 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 13:9 \xt [Ps. 137:1] \x*Even so will I spoil the pride of Judah and the great \x + \xo 13:9 \xt Lev. 26:19\x*pride of Jerusalem.
\v 10 This evil people, who refuse to hear my words, \x + \xo 13:10 \xt [ch. 3:17; 16:11, 12] \x*who stubbornly follow their own heart and have gone after other gods to serve them and worship them, shall be like this loincloth, which is \x + \xo 13:10 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*good for nothing.
\v 11 For as the loincloth clings to the waist of a man, so I made the whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah cling to me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 13:11 \xt [Ex. 19:5] \x*that they might be for me a people, \x + \xo 13:11 \xt ch. 33:9; Isa. 55:13; Zeph. 3:20\x*a name, a praise, and a glory, but they would not listen.
\s1 The Jars Filled with Wine
\p
\v 12 “You shall speak to them this word: ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, “Every jar shall be filled with wine.”’ And they will say to you, ‘Do we not indeed know that \x + \xo 13:12 \xt ch. 48:12\x*every jar will be filled with wine?’
\v 13 Then you shall say to them, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 13:13 \xt Ezek. 23:33 \x*Behold, I will fill with drunkenness all the inhabitants of this land: \x + \xo 13:13 \xt ch. 17:20; 19:3; 22:2 \x*the kings who sit on David’s throne, \x + \xo 13:13 \xt [ch. 18:18]\x*the priests, the prophets, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
\v 14 And I will \x + \xo 13:14 \xt Ps. 2:9; [ch. 19:10, 11]\x*dash them one against another, fathers and sons together, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. I will not pity or spare or have compassion, that I should not destroy them.’”
\s1 Exile Threatened
\q1
\v 15 Hear and give ear; be not proud,
\q2 for the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 13:16 \xt [Josh. 7:19] \x*Give glory to the \nd Lord\nd* your God
\q2 \x + \xo 13:16 \xt Isa. 5:30; 8:22; Amos 5:8; 8:9; [John 11:10] \x*before he brings darkness,
\q1 before your feet stumble
\q2 on the twilight mountains,
\q1 and \x + \xo 13:16 \xt Isa. 5:30; 8:22; Amos 5:8; 8:9; [John 11:10] \x*while you look for light
\q2 he turns it into gloom
\q2 and makes it \x + \xo 13:16 \xt Isa. 60:2\x*deep darkness.
\q1
\v 17 But if you will not listen,
\q2 \x + \xo 13:17 \xt ch. 9:1, 18; 14:17; Lam. 1:2, 16; 2:18; 3:49\x*my soul will weep in secret for your pride;
\q1 my eyes will weep bitterly and run down with tears,
\q2 because the \nd Lord\nd*’s flock has been taken captive.
\b
\q1
\v 18 Say to \x + \xo 13:18 \xt ch. 22:26; 2 Kgs. 24:12 \x*the king and \x + \xo 13:18 \xt ch. 22:26; 2 Kgs. 24:12 \x*the queen mother:
\q2 “Take a lowly seat,
\q1 for \x + \xo 13:18 \xt Prov. 4:9; Isa. 28:5; 62:3; Lam. 5:16\x*your beautiful crown
\q2 has come down from your head.”
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 13:19 \xt [Josh. 6:1]\x*The cities of the Negeb are shut up,
\q2 with none to open them;
\q1 all Judah is taken into exile,
\q2 wholly taken into exile.
\b
\q1
\v 20 “Lift up your eyes \x + \xo 13:20 \xt ch. 1:13, 14; 6:22\x*and see
\q2 those who come from the north.
\q1 Where is the flock that was given you,
\q2 your beautiful flock?
\q1
\v 21 What will you say when they set as head over you
\q2 those whom you yourself have taught to be friends to you?
\q1 \x + \xo 13:21 \xt See Isa. 13:8\x*Will not pangs take hold of you
\q2 like those of a woman in labor?
\q1
\v 22 And if you say in your heart,
\q2 \x + \xo 13:22 \xt See ch. 5:19 \x*‘Why have these things come upon me?’
\q1 it is for the greatness of your iniquity
\q2 that \x + \xo 13:22 \xt ver. 26; Isa. 3:17; Lam. 1:8; Nah. 3:5; [Hos. 2:10]\x*your skirts are lifted up
\q2 and you suffer violence.
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 13:23 \xt [Matt. 19:26]\x*Can the Ethiopian change his skin
\q2 or \x + \xo 13:23 \xt [Matt. 19:26]\x*the leopard his spots?
\q1 Then also you can do good
\q2 who are accustomed to do evil.
\q1
\v 24 I will scatter you\f + \fr 13:24 \ft Hebrew \fq them\f* \x + \xo 13:24 \xt Ps. 1:4; 83:13\x*like chaff
\q2 driven by the wind from the desert.
\q1
\v 25 \x + \xo 13:25 \xt Job 20:29; Ps. 11:6 \x*This is your lot,
\q2 the portion I have measured out to you, declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 because \x + \xo 13:25 \xt ch. 2:32\x*you have forgotten me
\q2 and trusted in lies.
\q1
\v 26 \x + \xo 13:26 \xt [See ver. 22 above]\x*I myself will lift up your skirts over your face,
\q2 and your shame will be seen.
\q1
\v 27 I have seen \x + \xo 13:27 \xt ch. 6:15 \x*your abominations,
\q2 your adulteries and \x + \xo 13:27 \xt ch. 5:8 \x*neighings, your lewd whorings,
\q2 \x + \xo 13:27 \xt See ch. 2:20 \x*on the hills in the field.
\q1 Woe to you, O Jerusalem!
\q2 How long will it be \x + \xo 13:27 \xt Isa. 1:16; [Ezek. 24:13]\x*before you are made clean?”
\c 14
\s1 Famine, Sword, and Pestilence
\p \v 1 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* that came to Jeremiah concerning \x + \xo 14:1 \xt ch. 17:8\x*the drought:
\b
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 14:2 \xt Lam. 1:4 \x*“Judah mourns,
\q2 and \x + \xo 14:2 \xt Isa. 3:26; [Lam. 2:8] \x*her gates languish;
\q1 her people lament on the ground,
\q2 and \x + \xo 14:2 \xt [1 Sam. 5:12]\x*the cry of Jerusalem goes up.
\q1
\v 3 Her nobles send their servants for water;
\q2 they come to the cisterns;
\q1 they find no water;
\q2 they return with their vessels empty;
\q1 they are \x + \xo 14:3 \xt Ps. 40:14 \x*ashamed and confounded
\q2 and \x + \xo 14:3 \xt [2 Sam. 15:30]\x*cover their heads.
\q1
\v 4 Because of the ground that is dismayed,
\q2 since there is \x + \xo 14:4 \xt ch. 3:3\x*no rain on the land,
\q1 the farmers are ashamed;
\q2 they cover their heads.
\q1
\v 5 Even \x + \xo 14:5 \xt Job 39:1; Ps. 29:9\x*the doe in the field forsakes her newborn fawn
\q2 because there is no grass.
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 14:6 \xt ch. 2:24\x*The wild donkeys stand on the bare heights;
\q2 they pant for air like jackals;
\q1 their eyes fail
\q2 because there is no vegetation.
\b
\q1
\v 7 “Though our iniquities testify against us,
\q2 act, O \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 14:7 \xt ver. 21; Ps. 25:11 \x*for your name’s sake;
\q1 \x + \xo 14:7 \xt ch. 2:19 \x*for our backslidings are many;
\q2 \x + \xo 14:7 \xt ver. 20\x*we have sinned against you.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 14:8 \xt ch. 17:13; 50:7; Ps. 71:5\x*O you hope of Israel,
\q2 its savior in time of trouble,
\q1 why should you be like a stranger in the land,
\q2 like a traveler who turns aside to tarry for a night?
\q1
\v 9 Why should you be like a man confused,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:9 \xt [Isa. 59:1] \x*like a mighty warrior who cannot save?
\q1 Yet \x + \xo 14:9 \xt [Ex. 29:45] \x*you, O \nd Lord\nd*, are in the midst of us,
\q2 and \x + \xo 14:9 \xt Dan. 9:18; [Eph. 3:15] \x*we are called by your name;
\q2 \x + \xo 14:9 \xt Ps. 119:121\x*do not leave us.”
\b
\q1
\v 10 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning this people:
\q1 “They have loved to wander thus;
\q2 they have not restrained their feet;
\q1 \x + \xo 14:10 \xt Hos. 8:13 \x*therefore the \nd Lord\nd* does not accept them;
\q2 \x + \xo 14:10 \xt Hos. 9:9\x*now he will remember their iniquity
\q2 and punish their sins.”
\b
\p
\v 11 The \nd Lord\nd* said to me: \x + \xo 14:11 \xt See ch. 7:16\x*“Do not pray for the welfare of this people.
\v 12 Though they fast, I will not hear their cry, \x + \xo 14:12 \xt Prov. 1:28; Isa. 1:15; Ezek. 8:18; Mic. 3:4; See ch. 6:20 \x*and though they offer burnt offering and grain offering, I will not accept them. But I will consume them \x + \xo 14:12 \xt ch. 16:4; 24:10; 32:24; Ezek. 14:21\x*by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence.”
\s1 Lying Prophets
\p
\v 13 Then I said: “Ah, Lord \nd God\nd*, behold, the prophets \x + \xo 14:13 \xt [ch. 4:10; 6:14]\x*say to them, ‘You shall not see the sword, nor shall you have famine, but I will give you assured peace in this place.’”
\v 14 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to me: “The \x + \xo 14:14 \xt See ch. 5:31 \x*prophets are prophesying lies in my name. \x + \xo 14:14 \xt ch. 23:21; 27:15; Deut. 18:20; [Matt. 7:15; Mark 13:22] \x*I did not send them, nor did I command them or speak to them. They are prophesying to you a lying vision, \x + \xo 14:14 \xt Ezek. 13:6; [ch. 27:9; 29:8] \x*worthless divination, and \x + \xo 14:14 \xt ch. 23:26\x*the deceit of their own minds.
\v 15 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning the prophets who prophesy in my name although \x + \xo 14:15 \xt [See ver. 14 above] \x*I did not send them, and who say, \x + \xo 14:15 \xt [See ver. 12 above] \x*‘Sword and famine shall not come upon this land’: \x + \xo 14:15 \xt [ch. 23:34]\x*By sword and famine those prophets shall be consumed.
\v 16 And the people to whom they prophesy shall be cast out in the streets of Jerusalem, victims of famine and sword, \x + \xo 14:16 \xt Ps. 79:3\x*with none to bury them—them, their wives, their sons, and their daughters. For I will pour out their evil upon them.
\b
\q1
\v 17 “You shall say to them this word:
\q1 \x + \xo 14:17 \xt See ch. 13:17 \x*‘Let my eyes run down with tears night and day,
\q2 and let them not cease,
\q1 for the virgin \x + \xo 14:17 \xt See ch. 8:21 \x*daughter of my people is shattered with a great wound,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:17 \xt ch. 10:19; 30:12\x*with a very grievous blow.
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 14:18 \xt Ezek. 7:15 \x*If I go out into the field,
\q2 behold, those pierced by the sword!
\q1 \x + \xo 14:18 \xt Ezek. 7:15 \x*And if I enter the city,
\q2 behold, the diseases of famine!
\q1 \x + \xo 14:18 \xt [ch. 5:31]\x*For both prophet and priest ply their trade through the land
\q2 and have no knowledge.’”
\b
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 14:19 \xt Lam. 5:22 \x*Have you utterly rejected Judah?
\q2 Does your soul loathe Zion?
\q1 Why have you struck us down
\q2 \x + \xo 14:19 \xt [ch. 15:18] \x*so that there is no healing for us?
\q1 \x + \xo 14:19 \xt ch. 8:15\x*We looked for peace, but no good came;
\q2 \x + \xo 14:19 \xt ch. 8:15\x*for a time of healing, but behold, terror.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 14:20 \xt [Ps. 106:6; Dan. 9:5, 8]\x*We acknowledge our wickedness, O \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and the iniquity of our fathers,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:20 \xt [Ps. 106:6; Dan. 9:5, 8]\x*for we have sinned against you.
\q1
\v 21 Do not spurn us, \x + \xo 14:21 \xt ver. 7 \x*for your name’s sake;
\q2 do not dishonor your glorious throne;
\q2 \x + \xo 14:21 \xt Lev. 26:42; Ps. 106:45\x*remember and do not break your covenant with us.
\q1
\v 22 Are there any among \x + \xo 14:22 \xt ch. 10:15; [Deut. 32:21] \x*the false gods of the nations \x + \xo 14:22 \xt Job 28:26; 38:26, 28; Zech. 10:1, 2 \x*that can bring rain?
\q2 Or can the heavens give showers?
\q1 Are you not he, O \nd Lord\nd* our God?
\q2 We set our hope on you,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:22 \xt Job 12:9; Isa. 66:2\x*for you do all these things.
\c 15
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Will Not Relent
\p \v 1 Then the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, \x + \xo 15:1 \xt Ps. 99:6; [Ezek. 14:14] \x*“Though \x + \xo 15:1 \xt [Ps. 106:23]; See Ex. 32:11-13 \x*Moses \x + \xo 15:1 \xt [1 Sam. 7:9; 8:6; 12:23; 15:11] \x*and Samuel \x + \xo 15:1 \xt ch. 35:19; [ver. 19]\x*stood before me, yet my heart would not turn toward this people. Send them out of my sight, and let them go!
\v 2 And when they ask you, ‘Where shall we go?’ you shall say to them, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 15:2 \xt ch. 14:12; 16:4; 21:9; 43:11; Ezek. 5:12; 6:11, 12; Zech. 11:9\x*“‘Those who are for pestilence, to pestilence,
\q2 and those who are for the sword, to the sword;
\q1 those who are for famine, to famine,
\q2 and those who are for captivity, to captivity.’
\b
\m
\v 3 \x + \xo 15:3 \xt See Lev. 26:16-22 \x*I will appoint over them four kinds of destroyers, declares the \nd Lord\nd*: the sword to kill, the dogs to tear, and \x + \xo 15:3 \xt Deut. 28:26 \x*the birds of the air \x + \xo 15:3 \xt Rev. 6:8\x*and the beasts of the earth to devour and destroy.
\v 4 \x + \xo 15:4 \xt ch. 24:9; 29:18; 34:17; Deut. 28:25 \x*And I will make them a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth because of what \x + \xo 15:4 \xt [2 Kgs. 21:2, 11, 16, 17; 23:26; 24:3, 4]\x*Manasseh the son of Hezekiah, king of Judah, did in Jerusalem.
\b
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 15:5 \xt Isa. 51:19; [Nah. 3:7]\x*“Who will have pity on you, O Jerusalem,
\q2 \x + \xo 15:5 \xt Isa. 51:19; [Nah. 3:7]\x*or who will grieve for you?
\q1 Who will turn aside
\q2 to ask about your welfare?
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 15:6 \xt Deut. 32:15 \x*You have rejected me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 \x + \xo 15:6 \xt See ch. 7:24 \x*you keep going backward,
\q1 so I have stretched out my hand against you and destroyed you—
\q2 \x + \xo 15:6 \xt [Hos. 13:14]\x*I am weary of relenting.
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 15:7 \xt [ch. 51:2; Isa. 41:16; Matt. 3:12; Luke 3:17] \x*I have winnowed them with \x + \xo 15:7 \xt Isa. 30:24 \x*a winnowing fork
\q2 in the gates of the land;
\q1 I have bereaved them; I have destroyed my people;
\q2 \x + \xo 15:7 \xt ch. 5:3; Isa. 9:13; Amos 4:6, 8-11\x*they did not turn from their ways.
\q1
\v 8 I have made their widows more in number
\q2 than \x + \xo 15:8 \xt Gen. 22:17; Ps. 139:18\x*the sand of the seas;
\q1 I have brought against the mothers of young men
\q2 a destroyer at noonday;
\q1 I have made anguish and terror
\q2 fall upon them suddenly.
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 15:9 \xt 1 Sam. 2:5; [Lam. 1:1] \x*She who bore seven has grown feeble;
\q2 \x + \xo 15:9 \xt Job 11:20 \x*she has fainted away;
\q1 \x + \xo 15:9 \xt Amos 8:9\x*her sun went down while it was yet day;
\q2 she has been shamed and disgraced.
\q1 And the rest of them I will give to the sword
\q2 before their enemies,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\s1 Jeremiah’s Complaint
\p
\v 10 \x + \xo 15:10 \xt ch. 20:14 \x*Woe is me, my mother, that you bore me, a man of strife and contention to the whole land! \x + \xo 15:10 \xt Ex. 22:25; Ps. 15:5; Isa. 24:2\x*I have not lent, nor have I borrowed, yet all of them curse me.
\v 11 The \nd Lord\nd* said, “Have I not\f + \fr 15:11 \ft The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain\f* set you free for their good? Have I not pleaded for you before the enemy in the time of trouble and in the time of distress?
\v 12 Can one break iron, iron \x + \xo 15:12 \xt See ch. 1:13\x*from the north, and bronze?
\p
\v 13 \x + \xo 15:13 \xt ch. 17:3 \x*“Your wealth and your treasures I will give as \x + \xo 15:13 \xt Ps. 44:12\x*spoil, without price, for all your sins, throughout all your territory.
\v 14 I will make you serve your enemies \x + \xo 15:14 \xt ch. 9:16; 16:13; 17:4; 22:28 \x*in a land that you do not know, \x + \xo 15:14 \xt Deut. 32:22\x*for in my anger a fire is kindled that shall burn forever.”
\b
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 15:15 \xt ch. 12:3 \x*O \nd Lord\nd*, you know;
\q2 \x + \xo 15:15 \xt [Judg. 16:28] \x*remember me and visit me,
\q2 \x + \xo 15:15 \xt [Judg. 16:28] \x*\x + \xo 15:15 \xt ch. 11:20; 20:12 \x*and take vengeance for me on my persecutors.
\q1 In your forbearance take me not away;
\q2 \x + \xo 15:15 \xt ch. 17:16 \x*know that \x + \xo 15:15 \xt Ps. 69:7\x*for your sake I bear reproach.
\q1
\v 16 Your words were found, \x + \xo 15:16 \xt Ezek. 3:1, 3; Rev. 10:9, 10 \x*and I ate them,
\q2 and \x + \xo 15:16 \xt Ps. 119:111, 162 \x*your words became to me a joy
\q2 and the delight of my heart,
\q1 \x + \xo 15:16 \xt ch. 14:9\x*for I am called by your name,
\q2 O \nd Lord\nd*, God of hosts.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 15:17 \xt Ps. 26:4 \x*I did not sit in the company of revelers,
\q2 nor did I rejoice;
\q1 \x + \xo 15:17 \xt Ps. 102:7; Lam. 3:28\x*I sat alone, because your hand was upon me,
\q2 for you had filled me with indignation.
\q1
\v 18 Why is my pain unceasing,
\q2 \x + \xo 15:18 \xt ch. 30:15; Job 34:6 \x*my wound incurable,
\q2 refusing to be healed?
\q1 Will you be to me \x + \xo 15:18 \xt Job 6:15; Isa. 58:11\x*like a deceitful brook,
\q2 like waters that fail?
\b
\q1
\v 19 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 \x + \xo 15:19 \xt ch. 3:14 \x*“If you return, I will restore you,
\q2 and you shall \x + \xo 15:19 \xt [ver. 1]\x*stand before me.
\q1 If you utter what is precious, and not what is worthless,
\q2 you shall be as my mouth.
\q1 They shall turn to you,
\q2 but you shall not turn to them.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 15:20 \xt [ch. 1:18; 6:27] \x*And I will make you to this people
\q2 a fortified wall of bronze;
\q1 they will fight against you,
\q2 \x + \xo 15:20 \xt ch. 1:19; 20:11 \x*but they shall not prevail over you,
\q1 \x + \xo 15:20 \xt See ch. 1:8\x*for I am with you
\q2 to save you and deliver you,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 15:21 \xt [See ver. 20 above] \x*I will deliver you out of the hand of the wicked,
\q2 and redeem you from the grasp of \x + \xo 15:21 \xt Isa. 13:11; 25:4, 5; 29:5\x*the ruthless.”
\c 16
\s1 Famine, Sword, and Death
\p \v 1 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me:
\v 2 “You shall not take a wife, nor shall you have sons or daughters in this place.
\v 3 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning the sons and daughters who are born in this place, and concerning the mothers who bore them and the fathers who fathered them in this land:
\v 4 \x + \xo 16:4 \xt See ch. 15:2 \x*They shall die of deadly diseases. \x + \xo 16:4 \xt ch. 22:18, 19; 25:33 \x*They shall not be lamented, nor shall they be buried. \x + \xo 16:4 \xt See ch. 8:2 \x*They shall be as dung on the surface of the ground. \x + \xo 16:4 \xt See ch. 14:12 \x*They shall perish by the sword and by famine, \x + \xo 16:4 \xt See ch. 7:33\x*and their dead bodies shall be food for the birds of the air and for the beasts of the earth.
\p
\v 5 “For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 16:5 \xt See Ezek. 24:16-23\x*Do not enter the house of mourning, or go to lament or grieve for them, for I have taken away my peace from this people, my steadfast love and mercy, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 6 Both great and small shall die in this land. \x + \xo 16:6 \xt [See ver. 4 above] \x*They shall not be buried, and no one shall lament for them or \x + \xo 16:6 \xt Lev. 19:28; Deut. 14:1 \x*cut himself \x + \xo 16:6 \xt Job 1:20; [Isa. 3:24]\x*or make himself bald for them.
\v 7 No one shall \x + \xo 16:7 \xt Isa. 58:7; Ezek. 24:17; [Deut. 26:14; Hos. 9:4]\x*break bread for the mourner, to comfort him for the dead, nor shall anyone give him the cup of consolation to drink for his father or his mother.
\v 8 You shall not go into the house of feasting to sit with them, to eat and drink.
\v 9 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 16:9 \xt See ch. 7:34\x*Behold, I will silence in this place, before your eyes and in your days, the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride.
\p
\v 10 “And when you tell this people all these words, and they say to you, \x + \xo 16:10 \xt See ch. 5:19\x*‘Why has the \nd Lord\nd* pronounced all this great evil against us? What is our iniquity? What is the sin that we have committed against the \nd Lord\nd* our God?’
\v 11 then you shall say to them: \x + \xo 16:11 \xt ch. 5:19; 22:9; [Deut. 29:25, 26; 2 Kgs. 22:17; 2 Chr. 34:25] \x*‘Because your fathers have forsaken me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and \x + \xo 16:11 \xt ch. 13:10\x*have gone after other gods and have served and worshiped them, and have forsaken me and have not kept my law,
\v 12 and because \x + \xo 16:12 \xt ch. 7:26 \x*you have done worse than your fathers, for behold, \x + \xo 16:12 \xt See ch. 3:17\x*every one of you follows his stubborn, evil will, refusing to listen to me.
\v 13 Therefore \x + \xo 16:13 \xt ch. 10:18; 22:26; Isa. 22:17, 18; See Deut. 4:26-28; 28:64, 65 \x*I will hurl you out of this land into \x + \xo 16:13 \xt See ch. 15:14 \x*a land that neither you nor your fathers have known, \x + \xo 16:13 \xt Deut. 28:36, 64\x*and there you shall serve other gods day and night, for I will show you no favor.’
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Will Restore Israel
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 16:14 \xt For ver. 14, 15, see ch. 23:7, 8 \x*“Therefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when it shall no longer be said, \x + \xo 16:14 \xt ch. 4:2\x*‘As the \nd Lord\nd* lives who brought up the people of Israel out of the land of Egypt,’
\v 15 but \x + \xo 16:15 \xt [See ver. 14 above] \x*‘As the \nd Lord\nd* lives who brought up the people of Israel \x + \xo 16:15 \xt [Isa. 43:5, 6]; See ch. 3:18 \x*out of the north country and out of all the countries where he had driven them.’ For \x + \xo 16:15 \xt ch. 24:6; 30:3; 32:37\x*I will bring them back to their own land that I gave to their fathers.
\p
\v 16 “Behold, \x + \xo 16:16 \xt [Ezek. 12:13; Amos 4:2; Hab. 1:15] \x*I am sending for many fishers, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and they shall catch them. And afterward I will send for many hunters, and they shall hunt them from every mountain and every hill, and out \x + \xo 16:16 \xt ch. 13:4\x*of the clefts of the rocks.
\v 17 For \x + \xo 16:17 \xt ch. 32:19; 2 Chr. 16:9; Job 34:21; Prov. 5:21 \x*my eyes are on all their ways. \x + \xo 16:17 \xt [Ps. 51:9; 90:8]\x*They are not hidden from me, \x + \xo 16:17 \xt [Ps. 51:9; 90:8]\x*nor is their iniquity concealed from my eyes.
\v 18 But first \x + \xo 16:18 \xt ch. 17:18; Isa. 40:2 \x*I will doubly repay their iniquity and their sin, because they have polluted my land with the carcasses of their detestable idols, and \x + \xo 16:18 \xt [Isa. 65:4]; See Ezek. 43:7-9\x*have filled my inheritance with their abominations.”
\b
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 16:19 \xt 2 Sam. 22:33; Ps. 28:7; 31:3, 4; Isa. 25:4 \x*O \nd Lord\nd*, my strength and my stronghold,
\q2 \x + \xo 16:19 \xt ch. 17:17 \x*my refuge in the day of trouble,
\q1 \x + \xo 16:19 \xt [Isa. 9:2; 49:6, 22, 23] \x*to you shall the nations come
\q2 from the ends of the earth and say:
\q1 “Our fathers have inherited nothing but lies,
\q2 \x + \xo 16:19 \xt See ch. 18:15\x*worthless things in which there is no profit.
\q1
\v 20 Can man make for himself \x + \xo 16:20 \xt [1 Cor. 8:4]; See ch. 2:11\x*gods?
\q2 Such are not gods!”
\b
\p
\v 21 “Therefore, behold, I will make them know, this once I will make them know my power and my might, and they shall know that \x + \xo 16:21 \xt See ch. 33:2\x*my name is the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\c 17
\s1 The Sin of Judah
\p \v 1 “The sin of Judah is written with \x + \xo 17:1 \xt Job 19:24 \x*a pen of iron; with a point of diamond it is engraved on \x + \xo 17:1 \xt Prov. 3:3; 7:3; [2 Cor. 3:3] \x*the tablet of their heart, and on \x + \xo 17:1 \xt Ex. 27:2; Ps. 118:27\x*the horns of their altars,
\v 2 while \x + \xo 17:2 \xt [ch. 19:5] \x*their children remember their altars and their \x + \xo 17:2 \xt Judg. 3:7; See Deut. 16:21 \x*Asherim, \x + \xo 17:2 \xt [Isa. 1:29]; See ch. 2:20\x*beside every green tree and on the high hills,
\v 3 \x + \xo 17:3 \xt Ps. 48:1, 2; 87:1; Isa. 2:3 \x*on the mountains in the open country. \x + \xo 17:3 \xt ch. 15:13\x*Your wealth and all your treasures I will give for spoil as the price of your high places for sin throughout all your territory.
\v 4 You shall loosen your hand from your heritage that I gave to you, \x + \xo 17:4 \xt See ch. 15:14 \x*and I will make you serve your enemies in a land that you do not know, \x + \xo 17:4 \xt See Deut. 32:22\x*for in my anger a fire is kindled that shall burn forever.”
\b
\q1
\v 5 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 “Cursed is the man \x + \xo 17:5 \xt 2 Chr. 32:8; Ps. 146:3\x*who trusts in man
\q2 and makes flesh his strength,\f + \fr 17:5 \ft Hebrew \fq arm\f*
\q2 whose heart turns away from the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 17:6 \xt ch. 48:6 \x*He is like a shrub in the desert,
\q2 \x + \xo 17:6 \xt ch. 29:32; Job 20:17; Ps. 34:12 \x*and shall not see any good come.
\q1 He shall dwell in the parched places of the wilderness,
\q2 in \x + \xo 17:6 \xt Deut. 29:23; Job 39:6\x*an uninhabited salt land.
\b
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 17:7 \xt Ps. 25:2; 34:8; 125:1; See Ps. 2:12 \x*“Blessed is the man who trusts in the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 17:7 \xt Ps. 71:5\x*whose trust is the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 17:8 \xt Ps. 1:3; [Ezek. 47:12]\x*He is like a tree planted by water,
\q2 that sends out its roots by the stream,
\q1 and does not fear when heat comes,
\q2 for its leaves remain green,
\q1 and is not anxious in the year of drought,
\q2 for it does not cease to bear fruit.”
\b
\q1
\v 9 The heart is deceitful above all things,
\q2 and desperately sick;
\q2 who can understand it?
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 17:10 \xt 1 Sam. 16:7; 1 Chr. 28:9; Ps. 139:23; Rom. 8:27 \x*“I the \nd Lord\nd* search the heart
\q2 \x + \xo 17:10 \xt See ch. 11:20 \x*and test the mind,\f + \fr 17:10 \ft Hebrew \fq kidneys\f*
\q1 \x + \xo 17:10 \xt ch. 32:19; Job 34:11; Ps. 62:12\x*to give every man according to his ways,
\q2 according to the fruit of his deeds.”
\b
\q1
\v 11 Like the \x + \xo 17:11 \xt [1 Sam. 26:20] \x*partridge that gathers a brood that she did not hatch,
\q2 so is \x + \xo 17:11 \xt Ps. 39:6 \x*he who gets riches but not by justice;
\q1 \x + \xo 17:11 \xt [Ps. 55:23] \x*in the midst of his days they will leave him,
\q2 \x + \xo 17:11 \xt [Luke 12:20]\x*and at his end he will be a fool.
\b
\q1
\v 12 A glorious throne set on high from the beginning
\q2 is the place of our sanctuary.
\q1
\v 13 O \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 17:13 \xt See ch. 14:8 \x*the hope of Israel,
\q2 \x + \xo 17:13 \xt Josh. 24:20; Ps. 73:27; Isa. 1:28 \x*all who forsake you shall be put to shame;
\q1 those who turn away from you\f + \fr 17:13 \ft Hebrew \fq me\f* \x + \xo 17:13 \xt [Luke 10:20] \x*shall be written in the earth,
\q2 for \x + \xo 17:13 \xt ch. 1:16 \x*they have forsaken \x + \xo 17:13 \xt ch. 2:13; [John 4:10, 14]\x*the \nd Lord\nd*, the fountain of living water.
\s1 Jeremiah Prays for Deliverance
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 17:14 \xt Ps. 6:2 \x*Heal me, O \nd Lord\nd*, and I shall be healed;
\q2 save me, and I shall be saved,
\q2 for \x + \xo 17:14 \xt Deut. 10:21\x*you are my praise.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 17:15 \xt Isa. 5:19; 2 Pet. 3:4\x*Behold, they say to me,
\q2 “Where is the word of the \nd Lord\nd*?
\q2 Let it come!”
\q1
\v 16 I have not run away from being your shepherd,
\q2 nor have I desired the day of sickness.
\q1 \x + \xo 17:16 \xt ch. 15:15; Ps. 40:9; 139:4\x*You know \x + \xo 17:16 \xt ch. 15:15; Ps. 40:9; 139:4\x*what came out of my lips;
\q2 it was before your face.
\q1
\v 17 Be not a terror to me;
\q2 \x + \xo 17:17 \xt ch. 16:19\x*you are my refuge in the day of disaster.
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 17:18 \xt Ps. 35:4; 40:14 \x*Let those be put to shame who persecute me,
\q2 but let me not be put to shame;
\q1 \x + \xo 17:18 \xt Ps. 35:4; 40:14 \x*let them be dismayed,
\q2 but let me not be dismayed;
\q1 \x + \xo 17:18 \xt ch. 11:20; Ps. 35:8\x*bring upon them the day of disaster;
\q2 destroy them with double destruction!
\s1 Keep the Sabbath Holy
\p
\v 19 Thus said the \nd Lord\nd* to me: “Go and stand in the People’s Gate, by which \x + \xo 17:19 \xt See ch. 13:13\x*the kings of Judah enter and by which they go out, and in all the gates of Jerusalem,
\v 20 and say: ‘Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 17:20 \xt [See ver. 19 above]\x*you kings of Judah, and all Judah, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, who enter by these gates.
\v 21 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: Take care for the sake of your lives, and \x + \xo 17:21 \xt [John 5:10]; See Neh. 13:15-19\x*do not bear a burden on the Sabbath day or bring it in by the gates of Jerusalem.
\v 22 And do not carry a burden out of your houses on the Sabbath \x + \xo 17:22 \xt See Num. 15:32-36 \x*or do any work, but \x + \xo 17:22 \xt Ex. 23:12; 31:13; Isa. 56:2; 58:13; Ezek. 20:12, 20; See Ex. 20:8-11; Deut. 5:12-15\x*keep the Sabbath day holy, as I commanded your fathers.
\v 23 Yet \x + \xo 17:23 \xt ch. 7:24, 26; [ch. 11:10] \x*they did not listen or incline their ear, \x + \xo 17:23 \xt [2 Chr. 30:8; Acts 7:51] \x*but stiffened their neck, that they \x + \xo 17:23 \xt See ch. 5:3\x*might not hear and receive instruction.
\p
\v 24 “‘But if you listen to me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and \x + \xo 17:24 \xt [See ver. 21 above] \x*bring in no burden by the gates of this city on the Sabbath day, but \x + \xo 17:24 \xt [See ver. 22 above]\x*keep the Sabbath day holy and do no work on it,
\v 25 then \x + \xo 17:25 \xt ch. 22:4\x*there shall enter by the gates of this city kings and princes who sit on the throne of David, riding in chariots and on horses, they and their officials, the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. And this city shall be inhabited forever.
\v 26 And people shall come from \x + \xo 17:26 \xt ch. 32:44; 33:13 \x*the cities of Judah \x + \xo 17:26 \xt Zech. 7:7 \x*and the places around Jerusalem, \x + \xo 17:26 \xt ch. 32:44; 33:13 \x*from the land of Benjamin, \x + \xo 17:26 \xt Zech. 7:7 \x*from the Shephelah, from the hill country, \x + \xo 17:26 \xt Zech. 7:7 \x*and from \x + \xo 17:26 \xt Gen. 13:1 \x*the Negeb, bringing \x + \xo 17:26 \xt Lev. 7:12; 22:29; 2 Chr. 33:16; Ps. 107:22; 116:17\x*burnt offerings and sacrifices, grain offerings and frankincense, and \x + \xo 17:26 \xt Lev. 7:12; 22:29; 2 Chr. 33:16; Ps. 107:22; 116:17\x*bringing thank offerings to the house of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 27 But if you do not listen to me, to \x + \xo 17:27 \xt [See ver. 22 above] \x*keep the Sabbath day holy, \x + \xo 17:27 \xt [See ver. 21 above] \x*and not to bear a burden and enter by the gates of Jerusalem on the Sabbath day, then I will \x + \xo 17:27 \xt ch. 21:14; 43:12; 49:27; 50:32; Lam. 4:11; Amos 1:14 \x*kindle a fire in its gates, and it shall \x + \xo 17:27 \xt ch. 52:13; 2 Kgs. 25:9 \x*devour the palaces of Jerusalem and \x + \xo 17:27 \xt ch. 7:20\x*shall not be quenched.’”
\c 18
\s1 The Potter and the Clay
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*:
\v 2 “Arise, and go down to \x + \xo 18:2 \xt ch. 19:1; 1 Chr. 4:23; [Zech. 11:13]\x*the potter’s house, and there I will let you hear my words.”
\v 3 So I went down to \x + \xo 18:3 \xt ch. 19:1; 1 Chr. 4:23; [Zech. 11:13]\x*the potter’s house, and there he was working at his wheel.
\v 4 And the vessel he was making of clay was \x + \xo 18:4 \xt ch. 13:7 \x*spoiled in the potter’s hand, and \x + \xo 18:4 \xt [Rom. 9:21]\x*he reworked it into another vessel, as it seemed good to the potter to do.
\p
\v 5 Then the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me:
\v 6 “O house of Israel, \x + \xo 18:6 \xt Isa. 45:9; See Rom. 9:20-24 \x*can I not do with you as this potter has done? declares the \nd Lord\nd*. \x + \xo 18:6 \xt Job 10:9; Isa. 64:8\x*Behold, like the clay in the potter’s hand, so are you in my hand, O house of Israel.
\v 7 If at any time I declare concerning a nation or a kingdom, that I will \x + \xo 18:7 \xt ch. 1:10; 42:10\x*pluck up and break down and destroy it,
\v 8 and if that nation, concerning which I have spoken, \x + \xo 18:8 \xt Ezek. 18:21 \x*turns from its evil, \x + \xo 18:8 \xt ch. 26:3, 13, 19; Judg. 2:18; Jonah 3:10\x*I will relent of the disaster that I intended to do to it.
\v 9 And if at any time I declare concerning a nation or a kingdom that I will \x + \xo 18:9 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*build and plant it,
\v 10 and if it does evil in my sight, not listening to my voice, then I will relent of the good that I had intended to do to it.
\v 11 Now, therefore, say to the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem: ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, Behold, I am shaping disaster against you and devising a plan against you. \x + \xo 18:11 \xt ch. 35:15; 2 Kgs. 17:13; Jonah 3:8 \x*Return, every one from his evil way, and \x + \xo 18:11 \xt ch. 7:3; 25:5; 35:15\x*amend your ways and your deeds.’
\p
\v 12 “But they say, \x + \xo 18:12 \xt ch. 2:25 \x*‘That is in vain! We will follow our own plans, and will every one act according to \x + \xo 18:12 \xt See ch. 3:17\x*the stubbornness of his evil heart.’
\b
\q1
\v 13 “Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 \x + \xo 18:13 \xt ch. 2:10, 11 \x*Ask among the nations,
\q2 Who has heard the like of this?
\q1 The virgin Israel
\q2 has done \x + \xo 18:13 \xt ch. 5:30\x*a very horrible thing.
\q1
\v 14 Does the snow of Lebanon leave
\q2 the crags of Sirion?\f + \fr 18:14 \ft Hebrew \fq of the field\f*
\q1 Do the mountain waters run dry,\f + \fr 18:14 \ft Hebrew \fq Are foreign waters plucked up\f*
\q2 the cold flowing streams?
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 18:15 \xt ch. 2:13, 32; 17:13 \x*But my people have forgotten me;
\q2 they make offerings to \x + \xo 18:15 \xt ch. 2:5; 10:15; 16:19 \x*false gods;
\q1 they made them stumble in their ways,
\q2 \x + \xo 18:15 \xt ch. 6:16 \x*in the ancient roads,
\q1 and to walk into side roads,
\q2 \x + \xo 18:15 \xt [Isa. 57:14]\x*not the highway,
\q1
\v 16 making their land \x + \xo 18:16 \xt ch. 19:8; 25:9, 11, 18; 49:13, 17; 50:13; 51:37; 2 Chr. 29:8 \x*a horror,
\q2 a thing \x + \xo 18:16 \xt ch. 19:8; 25:9, 11, 18; 49:13, 17; 50:13; 51:37; 2 Chr. 29:8 \x*to be hissed at forever.
\q1 \x + \xo 18:16 \xt ch. 50:13; Lam. 2:15 \x*Everyone who passes by it is horrified
\q2 \x + \xo 18:16 \xt Job 16:4; Ps. 22:7; Matt. 27:39\x*and shakes his head.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 18:17 \xt Gen. 41:6, 23, 27; Ex. 10:13; Job 27:21; Ps. 48:7; Ezek. 27:26; Hos. 13:15; Jonah 4:8 \x*Like the east wind \x + \xo 18:17 \xt ch. 13:24 \x*I will scatter them
\q2 before the enemy.
\q1 \x + \xo 18:17 \xt [ch. 2:27]\x*I will show them my back, not my face,
\q2 in the day of their calamity.”
\b
\p
\v 18 Then they said, \x + \xo 18:18 \xt ch. 11:19 \x*“Come, let us make plots against Jeremiah, \x + \xo 18:18 \xt [ch. 2:8; 5:13, 31; 6:13] \x*for the law shall not perish from the priest, nor counsel from the wise, nor the word from the prophet. \x + \xo 18:18 \xt ch. 9:3, 8; Job 5:21; [Ps. 31:20]\x*Come, let us strike him with the tongue, and let us not pay attention to any of his words.”
\b
\q1
\v 19 Hear me, O \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and \x + \xo 18:19 \xt Ps. 35:1; Isa. 49:25\x*listen to the voice of my adversaries.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 18:20 \xt Ps. 35:12 \x*Should good be repaid with evil?
\q2 Yet \x + \xo 18:20 \xt Ps. 35:7; 57:6; 119:85 \x*they have dug a pit for my life.
\q1 \x + \xo 18:20 \xt [Neh. 13:14]\x*Remember how I stood before you
\q2 to speak good for them,
\q2 to turn away your wrath from them.
\q1
\v 21 Therefore \x + \xo 18:21 \xt Ps. 109:10 \x*deliver up their children to famine;
\q2 give them over to the power of the sword;
\q1 let their wives become childless \x + \xo 18:21 \xt Ps. 109:9\x*and widowed.
\q2 May their men meet death by pestilence,
\q2 their youths be struck down by the sword in battle.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 18:22 \xt [ch. 20:16] \x*May a cry be heard from their houses,
\q2 when you bring the plunderer suddenly upon them!
\q1 For \x + \xo 18:22 \xt [See ver. 20 above] \x*they have dug a pit to take me
\q2 \x + \xo 18:22 \xt Ps. 140:5\x*and laid snares for my feet.
\q1
\v 23 Yet \x + \xo 18:23 \xt [Ps. 35:22] \x*you, O \nd Lord\nd*, know
\q2 all their plotting to kill me.
\q1 \x + \xo 18:23 \xt Neh. 4:5\x*Forgive not their iniquity,
\q2 nor blot out their sin from your sight.
\q1 Let them be overthrown before you;
\q2 deal with them in the time of your anger.
\c 19
\s1 The Broken Flask
\p \v 1 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, “Go, buy \x + \xo 19:1 \xt See ch. 18:2 \x*a potter’s earthenware \x + \xo 19:1 \xt ver. 10 \x*flask, and take some of \x + \xo 19:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 19:2; 23:1; Ezek. 8:1\x*the elders of the people and some of \x + \xo 19:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 19:2; 23:1; Ezek. 8:1\x*the elders of the priests,
\v 2 and go out \x + \xo 19:2 \xt See Josh. 15:8\x*to the Valley of the Son of Hinnom at the entry of the Potsherd Gate, and proclaim there the words that I tell you.
\v 3 You shall say, \x + \xo 19:3 \xt ch. 17:20 \x*‘Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 19:3 \xt See ch. 13:13 \x*O kings of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem. Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, I am bringing such disaster upon this place that \x + \xo 19:3 \xt 1 Sam. 3:11; 2 Kgs. 21:12\x*the ears of everyone who hears of it will tingle.
\v 4 \x + \xo 19:4 \xt See ch. 1:16 \x*Because the people have forsaken me and have profaned this place by making offerings in it to other gods whom neither they nor their fathers nor the kings of Judah have known; \x + \xo 19:4 \xt 2 Kgs. 21:16; See ch. 2:34\x*and because they have filled this place with the blood of innocents,
\v 5 \x + \xo 19:5 \xt ch. 7:31; 32:35; Lev. 18:21 \x*and have built the high places of Baal \x + \xo 19:5 \xt ch. 7:31; 32:35; Lev. 18:21 \x*to burn their sons in the fire as burnt offerings to Baal, \x + \xo 19:5 \xt ch. 7:31; 32:35; Deut. 17:3\x*which I did not command or decree, nor did it come into my mind—
\v 6 therefore, \x + \xo 19:6 \xt ch. 7:32 \x*behold, days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when this place shall no more be called Topheth, or \x + \xo 19:6 \xt ver. 2\x*the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter.
\v 7 And in this place \x + \xo 19:7 \xt [Isa. 19:3] \x*I will make void the plans of Judah and Jerusalem, \x + \xo 19:7 \xt [Lev. 26:17] \x*and will cause their people to fall by the sword before their enemies, and by the hand of those who seek their life. \x + \xo 19:7 \xt See ch. 7:33\x*I will give their dead bodies for food to the birds of the air and to the beasts of the earth.
\v 8 And I will make this city \x + \xo 19:8 \xt See ch. 18:16\x*a horror, \x + \xo 19:8 \xt See ch. 18:16\x*a thing to be hissed at. Everyone who passes by it will be horrified and will hiss because of all its wounds.
\v 9 \x + \xo 19:9 \xt Lev. 26:29; Deut. 28:53; Isa. 9:20; Lam. 2:20; 4:10; Ezek. 5:10 \x*And I will make them eat the flesh of their sons and their daughters, and everyone shall eat the flesh of his neighbor \x + \xo 19:9 \xt Deut. 28:53, 55, 57\x*in the siege and in the distress, with which their enemies and those who seek their life afflict them.’
\p
\v 10 “Then \x + \xo 19:10 \xt [ch. 51:63, 64] \x*you shall break \x + \xo 19:10 \xt ver. 1\x*the flask in the sight of the men who go with you,
\v 11 and shall say to them, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts: So will I break this people and this city, \x + \xo 19:11 \xt Ps. 2:9; Isa. 30:14; Lam. 4:2 \x*as one breaks a potter’s vessel, \x + \xo 19:11 \xt [Prov. 6:15] \x*so that it can never be mended. \x + \xo 19:11 \xt ch. 7:32\x*Men shall bury in Topheth because there will be no place else to bury.
\v 12 Thus will I do to this place, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and to its inhabitants, making this city \x + \xo 19:12 \xt [2 Kgs. 23:10]\x*like Topheth.
\v 13 The houses of Jerusalem and the houses of the kings of Judah—\x + \xo 19:13 \xt ch. 32:29; 44:18; 2 Kgs. 23:12; Zeph. 1:5 \x*all the houses on whose \x + \xo 19:13 \xt 2 Sam. 11:2 \x*roofs offerings have been offered \x + \xo 19:13 \xt Deut. 4:19; Acts 7:42 \x*to all the host of heaven, and \x + \xo 19:13 \xt ch. 7:18; 44:18 \x*drink offerings have been poured out to other gods—shall be defiled \x + \xo 19:13 \xt [See ver. 12 above]\x*like the place of Topheth.’”
\p
\v 14 Then Jeremiah came from \x + \xo 19:14 \xt ver. 2, 3 \x*Topheth, where the \nd Lord\nd* had sent him to prophesy, \x + \xo 19:14 \xt ch. 26:2; [2 Chr. 20:5]\x*and he stood in the court of the \nd Lord\nd*’s house and said to all the people:
\v 15 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel, behold, I am bringing upon this city and upon all its towns all the disaster that I have pronounced against it, \x + \xo 19:15 \xt ch. 7:26; 2 Chr. 30:8 \x*because they have stiffened their neck, \x + \xo 19:15 \xt ch. 25:3\x*refusing to hear my words.”
\c 20
\s1 Jeremiah Persecuted by Pashhur
\p \v 1 Now \x + \xo 20:1 \xt ch. 21:1; 38:1; 1 Chr. 9:12; [Ezra 2:38] \x*Pashhur the priest, the son of \x + \xo 20:1 \xt 1 Chr. 24:14; Ezra 2:37 \x*Immer, who was \x + \xo 20:1 \xt [ch. 29:26]\x*chief officer in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*, heard Jeremiah prophesying these things.
\v 2 Then \x + \xo 20:2 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*Pashhur beat Jeremiah the prophet, and put him \x + \xo 20:2 \xt ch. 29:26; Acts 16:24 \x*in the stocks that were in the upper \x + \xo 20:2 \xt ch. 37:13\x*Benjamin Gate of the house of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 3 The next day, when \x + \xo 20:3 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*Pashhur released Jeremiah from the stocks, Jeremiah said to him, “The \nd Lord\nd* does not call your name \x + \xo 20:3 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*Pashhur, but Terror on Every Side.
\v 4 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: Behold, I will make you \x + \xo 20:4 \xt See ch. 6:25\x*a terror to yourself and to all your friends. They shall fall by the sword of their enemies while you look on. And I will give all Judah into the hand of the king of Babylon. He shall carry them captive to Babylon, and shall strike them down with the sword.
\v 5 Moreover, \x + \xo 20:5 \xt [2 Kgs. 20:17]; See 2 Kgs. 24:12-16; 25:13-17 \x*I will give all the wealth of the city, all its gains, all its \x + \xo 20:5 \xt Job 28:10; Ezek. 22:25\x*prized belongings, and all the treasures of the kings of Judah into the hand of their enemies, who shall plunder them and seize them and carry them to Babylon.
\v 6 And you, \x + \xo 20:6 \xt ch. 21:1; 38:1; 1 Chr. 9:12; [Ezra 2:38] \x*Pashhur, and all who dwell in your house, shall go into captivity. To Babylon you shall go, and there you shall die, and there you shall be buried, you and all your friends, \x + \xo 20:6 \xt See ch. 14:14\x*to whom you have prophesied falsely.”
\b
\q1
\v 7 O \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 20:7 \xt [Ezek. 14:9] \x*you have deceived me,
\q2 and I was deceived;
\q1 \x + \xo 20:7 \xt [2 Pet. 1:21] \x*you are stronger than I,
\q2 and you have prevailed.
\q1 \x + \xo 20:7 \xt Ps. 119:51; Lam. 3:14\x*I have become a laughingstock all the day;
\q2 everyone mocks me.
\q1
\v 8 For whenever I speak, I cry out,
\q2 I shout, \x + \xo 20:8 \xt ch. 6:7 \x*“Violence and destruction!”
\q1 For \x + \xo 20:8 \xt ch. 6:10 \x*the word of the \nd Lord\nd* has become for me
\q2 \x + \xo 20:8 \xt Ps. 44:13; 79:4\x*a reproach and \x + \xo 20:8 \xt Ps. 44:13; 79:4\x*derision all day long.
\q1
\v 9 If I say, “I will not mention him,
\q2 or speak any more in his name,”
\q1 \x + \xo 20:9 \xt Job 32:18, 19; Ps. 39:3 \x*there is in my heart as it were a burning fire
\q2 shut up in my bones,
\q1 and \x + \xo 20:9 \xt ch. 6:11\x*I am weary with holding it in,
\q2 and I cannot.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 20:10 \xt Ps. 31:13 \x*For I hear many whispering.
\q2 \x + \xo 20:10 \xt See ch. 6:25 \x*Terror is on every side!
\q1 “Denounce him! \x + \xo 20:10 \xt [ch. 36:16, 20] \x*Let us denounce him!”
\q2 say all my \x + \xo 20:10 \xt Ps. 41:9; 55:13; [ch. 9:4; 38:22] \x*close friends,
\q2 \x + \xo 20:10 \xt [Ps. 56:6] \x*watching for \x + \xo 20:10 \xt Ps. 35:15 \x*my fall.
\q1 “Perhaps he will be deceived;
\q2 then \x + \xo 20:10 \xt ch. 1:19; 5:22\x*we can overcome him
\q2 and take our revenge on him.”
\q1
\v 11 But \x + \xo 20:11 \xt See ch. 1:8 \x*the \nd Lord\nd* is with me as a dread warrior;
\q2 therefore my persecutors will stumble;
\q2 \x + \xo 20:11 \xt See ch. 1:8 \x*they will not overcome me.
\q1 \x + \xo 20:11 \xt ch. 17:18; 23:40 \x*They will be greatly shamed,
\q2 for they will not succeed.
\q1 Their \x + \xo 20:11 \xt ch. 23:40\x*eternal dishonor
\q2 will never be forgotten.
\q1
\v 12 O \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, who tests the righteous,
\q2 \x + \xo 20:12 \xt See ch. 11:20\x*who sees the heart and the mind,\f + \fr 20:12 \ft Hebrew \fq kidneys\f*
\q1 let me see your vengeance upon them,
\q2 for to you have I committed my cause.
\b
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 20:13 \xt [Ps. 35:9, 10; 109:30, 31]\x*Sing to the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 praise the \nd Lord\nd*!
\q1 For he has delivered the life of the needy
\q2 from the hand of evildoers.
\b
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 20:14 \xt ch. 15:10; Job 3:3\x*Cursed be the day
\q2 on which I was born!
\q1 The day when my mother bore me,
\q2 let it not be blessed!
\q1
\v 15 Cursed be the man who brought the news to my father,
\q1 “A son is born to you,”
\q2 \x + \xo 20:15 \xt [John 16:21]\x*making him very glad.
\q1
\v 16 Let that man be like \x + \xo 20:16 \xt Gen. 19:25; Isa. 13:19 \x*the cities
\q2 that the \nd Lord\nd* overthrew without pity;
\q1 \x + \xo 20:16 \xt ch. 18:22\x*let him hear a cry in the morning
\q2 and an alarm at noon,
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 20:17 \xt [Job 3:10, 11]\x*because he did not kill me in the womb;
\q2 so my mother would have been my grave,
\q2 and her womb forever great.
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 20:18 \xt [Job 3:20] \x*Why did I come out from the womb
\q2 \x + \xo 20:18 \xt [Lam. 3:1, 2]\x*to see toil and sorrow,
\q2 and spend my days in shame?
\c 21
\s1 Jerusalem Will Fall to Nebuchadnezzar
\p \v 1 This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*, when King Zedekiah sent to him \x + \xo 21:1 \xt See ch. 20:1 \x*Pashhur the son of Malchiah and \x + \xo 21:1 \xt ch. 29:25; 37:3; 2 Kgs. 25:18 \x*Zephaniah the priest, the son of \x + \xo 21:1 \xt ch. 35:4; 2 Chr. 34:8\x*Maaseiah, saying,
\v 2 \x + \xo 21:2 \xt [ch. 37:7] \x*“Inquire of the \nd Lord\nd* for us, \x + \xo 21:2 \xt [2 Kgs. 25:1] \x*for Nebuchadnezzar\f + \fr 21:2 \ft Hebrew \fq Nebuchadrezzar\ft , an alternate spelling of \fq Nebuchadnezzar \ft (king of Babylon) occurring frequently from Jeremiah 21–52; this latter spelling is used throughout Jeremiah for consistency\f* king of Babylon is making war against us. Perhaps the \nd Lord\nd* will deal with us according to \x + \xo 21:2 \xt Ps. 105:2, 5\x*all his wonderful deeds and will make him withdraw from us.”
\p
\v 3 Then Jeremiah said to them: “Thus you shall say to Zedekiah,
\v 4 ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 21:4 \xt [ch. 32:5; 37:10] \x*Behold, I will turn back the weapons of war that are in your hands and with which you are fighting against the king of Babylon and against the Chaldeans who are besieging you outside the walls. \x + \xo 21:4 \xt [Isa. 13:4]\x*And I will bring them together into the midst of this city.
\v 5 I myself will fight against you \x + \xo 21:5 \xt ch. 27:5; 32:17, 21; Ex. 6:6; Deut. 4:34; Ezek. 20:33 \x*with outstretched hand and strong arm, \x + \xo 21:5 \xt ch. 32:37; Deut. 29:28\x*in anger and in fury and in great wrath.
\v 6 And I will strike down the inhabitants of this city, both man and beast. They shall die of a great pestilence.
\v 7 Afterward, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 21:7 \xt ch. 37:17; 39:5; 52:9 \x*I will give Zedekiah king of Judah and his servants and the people in this city who survive the pestilence, sword, and famine into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and into the hand of their enemies, into the hand of those who seek their lives. He shall strike them down with the edge of the sword. \x + \xo 21:7 \xt Deut. 28:50; 2 Chr. 36:17; Ezek. 5:11\x*He shall not pity them or spare them or have compassion.’
\p
\v 8 “And to this people you shall say: \x + \xo 21:8 \xt Deut. 30:15, 19 \x*‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: Behold, \x + \xo 21:8 \xt ch. 38:2\x*I set before you the way of life and the way of death.
\v 9 He who stays in this city shall die \x + \xo 21:9 \xt See ch. 15:2 \x*by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence, but he who goes out and \x + \xo 21:9 \xt ch. 37:13, 14 \x*surrenders to the Chaldeans who are besieging you shall live \x + \xo 21:9 \xt ch. 39:18; 45:5\x*and shall have his life as a prize of war.
\v 10 For \x + \xo 21:10 \xt ch. 44:11; Lev. 20:3, 5; Ps. 34:16; Ezek. 14:8; [Amos 9:4] \x*I have set my face against this city for harm and \x + \xo 21:10 \xt [ch. 14:11] \x*not for good, declares the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 21:10 \xt ver. 7; ch. 34:2; 37:8, 10; 38:17, 18, 23; 39:8; 52:13; 2 Chr. 36:19\x*it shall be given into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall burn it with fire.’
\s1 Message to the House of David
\p
\v 11 “And to the house of the king of Judah say, ‘Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\v 12 O house of David! Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 21:12 \xt ch. 22:3; Zech. 7:9; [ch. 22:16] \x*“‘Execute justice \x + \xo 21:12 \xt Ps. 101:8 \x*in the morning,
\q2 and deliver from the hand of the oppressor
\q2 him who has been robbed,
\q1 \x + \xo 21:12 \xt ch. 4:4\x*lest my wrath go forth like fire,
\q2 and burn with none to quench it,
\q2 because of your evil deeds.’”
\b
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 21:13 \xt [ver. 10]; See Ezek. 13:8 \x*“Behold, I am against you, O inhabitant of the valley,
\q2 O rock of the plain,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q1 you who say, \x + \xo 21:13 \xt [ch. 49:4]\x*‘Who shall come down against us,
\q2 or who shall enter our habitations?’
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 21:14 \xt ch. 9:25 \x*I will punish you according to \x + \xo 21:14 \xt Prov. 1:31; Isa. 3:10 \x*the fruit of your deeds,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 \x + \xo 21:14 \xt Ezek. 20:47\x*I will kindle a fire in her forest,
\q2 \x + \xo 21:14 \xt Ezek. 20:47\x*and it shall devour all that is around her.”
\b
\c 22
\p \v 1 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: “Go down to the house of the king of Judah and speak there this word,
\v 2 and say, \x + \xo 22:2 \xt ch. 21:12\x*‘Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, O king of Judah, who sits on the throne of David, you, and your servants, and your people who enter these gates.
\v 3 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 22:3 \xt ch. 7:5, 6; 21:12 \x*Do justice and righteousness, and deliver from the hand of the oppressor him who has been robbed. And \x + \xo 22:3 \xt Lev. 19:33 \x*do no wrong or violence \x + \xo 22:3 \xt [Ps. 82:3; Isa. 1:17] \x*to the resident alien, \x + \xo 22:3 \xt ch. 7:5, 6; 21:12 \x*the fatherless, and the widow, nor \x + \xo 22:3 \xt ver. 17; [ch. 26:15]\x*shed innocent blood in this place.
\v 4 For if you will indeed obey this word, \x + \xo 22:4 \xt ch. 17:25\x*then there shall enter the gates of this house kings who sit on the throne of David, riding in chariots and on horses, they and their servants and their people.
\v 5 But if you will not obey these words, I \x + \xo 22:5 \xt ch. 49:13; 51:14; Gen. 22:16; Amos 6:8; [Heb. 6:13] \x*swear by myself, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, that \x + \xo 22:5 \xt ch. 7:34; 25:11, 18; 44:6, 22; Isa. 64:10; Ezek. 5:14\x*this house shall become a desolation.
\v 6 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning the house of the king of Judah:
\b
\q1 “‘You are like Gilead to me,
\q2 like the summit of \x + \xo 22:6 \xt ver. 20, 23 \x*Lebanon,
\q1 yet surely I will make you a desert,
\q2 \x + \xo 22:6 \xt [ch. 6:8]\x*an uninhabited city.\f + \fr 22:6 \ft Hebrew \fq cities\f*
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 22:7 \xt ch. 6:4 \x*I will prepare destroyers against you,
\q2 each with his weapons,
\q1 \x + \xo 22:7 \xt 2 Kgs. 19:23; Isa. 37:24\x*and they shall cut down your choicest cedars
\q2 and cast them into the fire.
\b
\p
\v 8 “‘And many nations will pass by this city, and every man will say to his neighbor, \x + \xo 22:8 \xt See ch. 5:19\x*“Why has the \nd Lord\nd* dealt thus with this great city?”
\v 9 \x + \xo 22:9 \xt Deut. 29:25, 26\x*And they will answer, “Because they have forsaken the covenant of the \nd Lord\nd* their God and worshiped other gods and served them.”’”
\b
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 22:10 \xt [2 Chr. 35:24, 25] \x*Weep not for him who is dead,
\q2 nor grieve for him,
\q1 \x + \xo 22:10 \xt ver. 11\x*but weep bitterly for him who goes away,
\q2 for he shall return no more
\q2 to see his native land.
\s1 Message to the Sons of Josiah
\p
\v 11 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning Shallum the son of Josiah, king of Judah, who reigned instead of Josiah his father, and \x + \xo 22:11 \xt [2 Kgs. 23:34; 2 Chr. 36:4; Ezek. 19:4]\x*who went away from this place: “He shall return here no more,
\v 12 but \x + \xo 22:12 \xt [See ver. 11 above]\x*in the place where they have carried him captive, there shall he die, and he shall never see this land again.”
\b
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 22:13 \xt Hab. 2:12; See Isa. 5:18-23 \x*“Woe to him who builds his house by \x + \xo 22:13 \xt [Mic. 3:10] \x*unrighteousness,
\q2 and his upper rooms by injustice,
\q1 \x + \xo 22:13 \xt Lev. 19:13; 25:39, 40; Deut. 24:14, 15; James 5:4\x*who makes his neighbor serve him for nothing
\q2 and does not give him his wages,
\q1
\v 14 who says, ‘I will build myself a great house
\q2 with spacious upper rooms,’
\q1 who cuts out windows for it,
\q2 paneling it with cedar
\q2 and \x + \xo 22:14 \xt Ezek. 23:14\x*painting it with vermilion.
\q1
\v 15 Do you think you are a king
\q2 because you compete in cedar?
\q1 Did not your father eat and drink
\q2 and \x + \xo 22:15 \xt [2 Kgs. 23:25] \x*do justice and righteousness?
\q2 \x + \xo 22:15 \xt Ps. 128:2; Eccles. 8:12; Isa. 3:10\x*Then it was well with him.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 22:16 \xt Prov. 31:9; [Isa. 1:17] \x*He judged the cause of the poor and needy;
\q2 \x + \xo 22:16 \xt [See ver. 15 above] \x*then it was well.
\q1 Is not this \x + \xo 22:16 \xt [Judg. 2:10]\x*to know me?
\q2 declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 17 But you have eyes and heart
\q2 only for your dishonest gain,
\q1 \x + \xo 22:17 \xt ver. 3; [ch. 26:15]\x*for shedding innocent blood,
\q2 and for practicing oppression and violence.”
\b
\p
\v 18 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 22:18 \xt Ps. 78:64; See ch. 16:4-6 \x*“They shall not lament for him, saying,
\q2 \x + \xo 22:18 \xt [1 Kgs. 13:30] \x*‘Ah, my brother!’ or ‘Ah, sister!’
\q1 They shall not lament for him, saying,
\q2 \x + \xo 22:18 \xt [ch. 34:5]\x*‘Ah, lord!’ or ‘Ah, his majesty!’
\q1
\v 19 With the burial of a donkey \x + \xo 22:19 \xt ch. 8:2; 36:30; [Isa. 14:19]\x*he shall be buried,
\q2 dragged and dumped beyond the gates of Jerusalem.”
\b
\q1
\v 20 “Go up to Lebanon, and cry out,
\q2 and lift up your voice in Bashan;
\q1 cry out from \x + \xo 22:20 \xt Num. 27:12; Deut. 32:49 \x*Abarim,
\q2 for all \x + \xo 22:20 \xt [ch. 3:1]\x*your lovers are destroyed.
\q1
\v 21 I spoke to you in your prosperity,
\q2 but you said, ‘I will not listen.’
\q1 \x + \xo 22:21 \xt ch. 3:25 \x*This has been your way from \x + \xo 22:21 \xt Ps. 129:1, 2\x*your youth,
\q2 that you have not obeyed my voice.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 22:22 \xt ch. 23:1; [Ezek. 34:10] \x*The wind shall shepherd all your shepherds,
\q2 and \x + \xo 22:22 \xt [See ver. 20 above] \x*your lovers shall go into captivity;
\q1 \x + \xo 22:22 \xt ch. 3:25\x*then you will be ashamed and confounded
\q2 because of all your evil.
\q1
\v 23 O inhabitant of \x + \xo 22:23 \xt ver. 6 \x*Lebanon,
\q2 nested among the cedars,
\q1 how you will be pitied when pangs come upon you,
\q2 \x + \xo 22:23 \xt ch. 6:24; See Isa. 13:8\x*pain as of a woman in labor!”
\b
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 22:24 \xt Isa. 49:18; See Ezek. 5:11 \x*“As I live, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, though Coniah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, were \x + \xo 22:24 \xt 1 Kgs. 21:8; Song 8:6; Hag. 2:23\x*the signet ring on my right hand, yet I would tear you off
\v 25 and \x + \xo 22:25 \xt ch. 34:20 \x*give you \x + \xo 22:25 \xt ch. 39:17; [Deut. 1:17]\x*into the hand of those who seek your life, into the hand of those of whom you are afraid, even into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and into the hand of the Chaldeans.
\v 26 \x + \xo 22:26 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:15; 2 Chr. 36:10 \x*I will hurl you and \x + \xo 22:26 \xt [2 Kgs. 24:8]\x*the mother who bore you into another country, where you were not born, and there you shall die.
\v 27 But to the land to which they will long to return, there they shall not return.”
\b
\q1
\v 28 Is this man \x + \xo 22:28 \xt ver. 24 \x*Coniah a despised, broken pot,
\q2 a \x + \xo 22:28 \xt [ch. 48:38; Ps. 31:12; Hos. 8:8] \x*vessel no one cares for?
\q1 Why are he and his children hurled and cast
\q2 into a \x + \xo 22:28 \xt See ch. 15:14\x*land that they do not know?
\q1
\v 29 \x + \xo 22:29 \xt Isa. 1:2\x*O land, land, land,
\q2 hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*!
\q1
\v 30 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 “Write this man down as \x + \xo 22:30 \xt [1 Chr. 3:17; Matt. 1:12] \x*childless,
\q2 a man who shall not succeed in his days,
\q1 \x + \xo 22:30 \xt ch. 36:30\x*for none of his offspring shall succeed
\q2 \x + \xo 22:30 \xt ch. 36:30\x*in sitting on the throne of David
\q2 and ruling again in Judah.”
\c 23
\s1 The Righteous Branch
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 23:1 \xt ch. 6:3; 10:21; 22:22; 25:34, 36; Isa. 56:11; Ezek. 34:2; Zech. 11:17; [John 10:12, 13]\x*“Woe to the shepherds who destroy and scatter the sheep of my pasture!” declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 2 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, concerning \x + \xo 23:2 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*the shepherds who care for my people: “You have scattered my flock and have driven them away, and you have not attended to them. \x + \xo 23:2 \xt ver. 22; ch. 4:4\x*Behold, I will attend to you for your evil deeds, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 3 \x + \xo 23:3 \xt ch. 29:14; 32:37; Deut. 30:3; Ezek. 20:34, 41; 37:21; [Ps. 107:3]; See Ezek. 34:11-16 \x*Then I will gather the remnant of my flock \x + \xo 23:3 \xt [ch. 8:3] \x*out of all the countries where I have driven them, and I will bring them back to their fold, \x + \xo 23:3 \xt [Gen. 1:28]\x*and they shall be fruitful and multiply.
\v 4 \x + \xo 23:4 \xt ch. 3:15\x*I will set shepherds over them who will care for them, and they shall fear no more, nor be dismayed, neither shall any be missing, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\p
\v 5 \x + \xo 23:5 \xt For ver. 5, 6, see ch. 33:14-16 \x*“Behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when I will raise up for David a righteous \x + \xo 23:5 \xt Isa. 4:2; 11:1 \x*Branch, and \x + \xo 23:5 \xt ch. 30:9; Isa. 32:1; Ezek. 37:24; Hos. 3:5; Zech. 9:9; Matt. 2:2; Luke 1:32; 19:38; John 1:49\x*he shall reign as king and deal wisely, and shall execute justice and righteousness in the land.
\v 6 In his days Judah will be saved, and \x + \xo 23:6 \xt Deut. 33:28; [Zech. 14:11] \x*Israel will \x + \xo 23:6 \xt ch. 32:37 \x*dwell securely. And this is the name by which he will be called: \x + \xo 23:6 \xt Rom. 10:4; 1 Cor. 1:30\x*‘The \nd Lord\nd* is our righteousness.’
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 23:7 \xt For ver. 7, 8, see ch. 16:14, 15\x*“Therefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when they shall no longer say, ‘As the \nd Lord\nd* lives who brought up the people of Israel out of the land of Egypt,’
\v 8 but ‘As the \nd Lord\nd* lives who brought up and led the offspring of the house of Israel out of the north country and out of all the countries where he\f + \fr 23:8 \ft Septuagint; Hebrew \fq I\f* had driven them.’ Then they shall dwell in their own land.”
\s1 Lying Prophets
\p
\v 9 Concerning the prophets:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 23:9 \xt Ezek. 6:9 \x*My heart is broken within me;
\q2 \x + \xo 23:9 \xt Hab. 3:16\x*all my bones shake;
\q1 I am like a drunken man,
\q2 like a man overcome by wine,
\q1 because of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q2 and because of his holy words.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 23:10 \xt ch. 5:7, 8; 9:2 \x*For the land is full of adulterers;
\q2 \x + \xo 23:10 \xt Ps. 10:7; 59:12; Hos. 4:2, 3 \x*because of the curse \x + \xo 23:10 \xt ch. 4:28 \x*the land mourns,
\q2 and \x + \xo 23:10 \xt ch. 9:10; 12:4; Ps. 107:34 \x*the pastures of the wilderness are dried up.
\q1 \x + \xo 23:10 \xt [ch. 22:17]\x*Their course is evil,
\q2 and their might is not right.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 23:11 \xt [ver. 33, 34; Zeph. 3:4]; See ch. 6:13 \x*“Both prophet and priest are ungodly;
\q2 even \x + \xo 23:11 \xt ch. 7:30; 32:34; Ezek. 8:16; 23:39\x*in my house I have found their evil,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 23:12 \xt Ps. 35:6; 73:18 \x*Therefore their way shall be to them
\q2 like slippery paths \x + \xo 23:12 \xt Prov. 4:19; [ch. 13:16] \x*in the darkness,
\q2 into which they shall be driven and fall,
\q1 for I will bring disaster upon them
\q2 \x + \xo 23:12 \xt ch. 11:23\x*in the year of their punishment,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 13 In the prophets of \x + \xo 23:13 \xt Isa. 7:9; Ezek. 16:46, 51, 53, 55; 23:4, 33 \x*Samaria
\q2 \x + \xo 23:13 \xt Lam. 2:14 \x*I saw an unsavory thing:
\q1 \x + \xo 23:13 \xt ch. 2:8 \x*they prophesied by Baal
\q2 \x + \xo 23:13 \xt Isa. 9:16; Mic. 3:5\x*and led my people Israel astray.
\q1
\v 14 But in the prophets of Jerusalem
\q2 I have seen a horrible thing:
\q1 \x + \xo 23:14 \xt ch. 29:23 \x*they commit adultery and walk in lies;
\q2 \x + \xo 23:14 \xt Ps. 64:5; Ezek. 13:22 \x*they strengthen the hands of evildoers,
\q2 so that no one turns from his evil;
\q1 \x + \xo 23:14 \xt Isa. 1:9, 10; 13:19\x*all of them have become like Sodom to me,
\q2 \x + \xo 23:14 \xt Isa. 1:9, 10; 13:19\x*and its inhabitants like Gomorrah.”
\q1
\v 15 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts concerning the prophets:
\q1 \x + \xo 23:15 \xt ch. 9:15; Prov. 5:4 \x*“Behold, I will feed them with bitter food
\q2 \x + \xo 23:15 \xt ch. 9:15; Prov. 5:4 \x*and give them \x + \xo 23:15 \xt ch. 8:14\x*poisoned water to drink,
\q1 for from the prophets of Jerusalem
\q2 ungodliness has gone out into all the land.”
\b
\p
\v 16 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts: “Do not listen to the words of the prophets who prophesy to you, \x + \xo 23:16 \xt [Ps. 12:2] \x*filling you with vain hopes. \x + \xo 23:16 \xt [ver. 21, 26; Num. 16:28]\x*They speak visions of their own minds, not from the mouth of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 17 They say continually to those who despise the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 23:17 \xt [Zech. 10:2]; See ch. 6:14 \x*‘It shall be well with you’; and to everyone who \x + \xo 23:17 \xt See ch. 3:17 \x*stubbornly follows his own heart, they say, \x + \xo 23:17 \xt ch. 5:12; Mic. 3:11\x*‘No disaster shall come upon you.’”
\b
\q1
\v 18 For \x + \xo 23:18 \xt ver. 22; Isa. 40:14\x*who among them has stood in the council of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q2 to see and to hear his word,
\q2 or who has paid attention to his word and listened?
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 23:19 \xt ch. 30:23 \x*Behold, the storm of the \nd Lord\nd*!
\q2 Wrath has gone forth,
\q1 \x + \xo 23:19 \xt ch. 25:32\x*a whirling tempest;
\q2 it will burst upon the head of the wicked.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 23:20 \xt ch. 30:24; [Isa. 55:11] \x*The anger of the \nd Lord\nd* will not turn back
\q2 until he has executed and \x + \xo 23:20 \xt ch. 30:24; [Isa. 55:11] \x*accomplished
\q2 the intents of his heart.
\q1 \x + \xo 23:20 \xt ch. 30:24\x*In the latter days you will understand it clearly.
\b
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 23:21 \xt See ch. 14:14\x*“I did not send the prophets,
\q2 yet they ran;
\q1 I did not speak to them,
\q2 yet they prophesied.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 23:22 \xt ver. 18 \x*But if they had stood in my council,
\q2 then they would have proclaimed my words to my people,
\q1 \x + \xo 23:22 \xt ch. 25:5; [Luke 1:17] \x*and they would have turned them from their evil way,
\q2 and \x + \xo 23:22 \xt ver. 2\x*from the evil of their deeds.
\b
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 23:23 \xt [Ps. 94:7, 9; Amos 9:2, 3]; See Ps. 139:7-12\x*“Am I a God at hand, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and not a God far away?
\v 24 \x + \xo 23:24 \xt [See ver. 23 above] \x*Can a man hide himself in secret places so that I cannot see him? declares the \nd Lord\nd*. \x + \xo 23:24 \xt Isa. 66:1; Acts 7:49\x*Do I not fill heaven and earth? declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 25 I have heard what the prophets have said \x + \xo 23:25 \xt See ch. 5:31 \x*who prophesy lies in my name, saying, \x + \xo 23:25 \xt [Zech. 10:2]\x*‘I have dreamed, I have dreamed!’
\v 26 How long shall there be lies in the heart of \x + \xo 23:26 \xt [ver. 16, 21; Num. 16:28]\x*the prophets who prophesy lies, and who prophesy the deceit of their own heart,
\v 27 who think to make my people forget my name \x + \xo 23:27 \xt [See ver. 25 above] \x*by their dreams that they tell one another, even as their \x + \xo 23:27 \xt Judg. 3:7; 8:33, 34\x*fathers forgot my name for Baal?
\v 28 \x + \xo 23:28 \xt [Num. 12:6] \x*Let the prophet who has a dream \x + \xo 23:28 \xt ver. 25 \x*tell the dream, but let him who has my word speak my word faithfully. \x + \xo 23:28 \xt [Luke 3:17]\x*What has straw in common with wheat? declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 29 \x + \xo 23:29 \xt [See ver. 28 above] \x*Is not my word like fire, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and \x + \xo 23:29 \xt [Dan. 2:34, 45]\x*like a hammer that breaks the rock in pieces?
\v 30 \x + \xo 23:30 \xt Ezek. 13:8; [ch. 14:15; Deut. 18:20]\x*Therefore, behold, I am against the prophets, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, who steal my words from one another.
\v 31 Behold, I am against the prophets, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, who use their tongues and declare, ‘declares the \nd Lord\nd*.’
\v 32 Behold, I am against those who prophesy lying dreams, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and who tell them and \x + \xo 23:32 \xt ver. 13 \x*lead my people astray by their lies and their recklessness, when \x + \xo 23:32 \xt ver. 21; See ch. 14:14\x*I did not send them or charge them. So they do not profit this people at all, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 23:33 \xt See Ezek. 14:1-11 \x*“When one of this people, or a prophet or a priest asks you, ‘What is the burden of the \nd Lord\nd*?’ you shall say to them, ‘You are the burden,\f + \fr 23:33 \ft Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew \fq What burden?\f* and \x + \xo 23:33 \xt [Hos. 4:6]\x*I will cast you off, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.’
\v 34 And as for the prophet, priest, or one of the people who says, ‘The burden of the \nd Lord\nd*,’ \x + \xo 23:34 \xt [See ver. 33 above]\x*I will punish that man and his household.
\v 35 Thus shall you say, every one to his neighbor and every one to his brother, ‘What has the \nd Lord\nd* answered?’ or ‘What has the \nd Lord\nd* spoken?’
\v 36 But ‘the burden of the \nd Lord\nd*’ you shall mention no more, for the burden is every man’s own word, and \x + \xo 23:36 \xt [Matt. 15:6] \x*you pervert the words of \x + \xo 23:36 \xt Ps. 42:2\x*the living God, the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, our God.
\v 37 Thus you shall say to the prophet, ‘What has the \nd Lord\nd* answered you?’ or ‘What has the \nd Lord\nd* spoken?’
\v 38 But if you say, ‘The burden of the \nd Lord\nd*,’ thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, ‘Because you have said these words, “The burden of the \nd Lord\nd*,” when I sent to you, saying, “You shall not say, ‘The burden of the \nd Lord\nd*,’”
\v 39 therefore, behold, I will surely lift you up and \x + \xo 23:39 \xt [See ver. 33 above]\x*cast you away from my presence, you and the city that I gave to you and your fathers.
\v 40 \x + \xo 23:40 \xt ch. 20:11\x*And I will bring upon you everlasting reproach and \x + \xo 23:40 \xt ch. 20:11\x*perpetual shame, which shall not be forgotten.’”
\c 24
\s1 The Good Figs and the Bad Figs
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 24:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:12; 2 Chr. 36:10 \x*After Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had taken into exile from Jerusalem \x + \xo 24:1 \xt Matt. 1:11; [ch. 22:18, 24, 28] \x*Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, together with \x + \xo 24:1 \xt ch. 29:2; 2 Kgs. 24:12, 14 \x*the officials of Judah, the craftsmen, and the metal workers, and had brought them to Babylon, the \nd Lord\nd* showed me this vision: behold, \x + \xo 24:1 \xt Amos 8:1, 2\x*two baskets of figs placed before the temple of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 2 One basket had very good figs, \x + \xo 24:2 \xt [Isa. 28:4] \x*like first-ripe figs, but the other basket had \x + \xo 24:2 \xt ch. 29:17\x*very bad figs, so bad that they could not be eaten.
\v 3 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, “What do you see, Jeremiah?” I said, “Figs, the good figs very good, and the bad figs very bad, so bad that they cannot be eaten.”
\p
\v 4 Then the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me:
\v 5 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel: Like these good figs, so I will regard as good the exiles from Judah, \x + \xo 24:5 \xt ch. 29:20\x*whom I have sent away from this place to the land of the Chaldeans.
\v 6 \x + \xo 24:6 \xt [Amos 9:4] \x*I will set my eyes on them for good, and I will bring them back to this land. \x + \xo 24:6 \xt ch. 12:15; 29:10 \x*I will build them up, and not tear them down; \x + \xo 24:6 \xt ch. 31:28; 42:10; [ch. 1:10; Amos 9:15]\x*I will plant them, and not pluck them up.
\v 7 \x + \xo 24:7 \xt ch. 32:39; Deut. 30:6; Ezek. 11:19; 36:26, 27 \x*I will give them a heart to know that I am the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 24:7 \xt See ch. 30:22; 31:33 \x*and they shall be my people \x + \xo 24:7 \xt See ch. 30:22; 31:33 \x*and I will be their God, \x + \xo 24:7 \xt ch. 29:13; Joel 2:12, 13\x*for they shall return to me with their whole heart.
\p
\v 8 “But thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: Like \x + \xo 24:8 \xt ver. 2; ch. 29:17 \x*the bad figs that are so bad they cannot be eaten, so will I treat \x + \xo 24:8 \xt ch. 21:1 \x*Zedekiah the king of Judah, his officials, the remnant of Jerusalem who remain in this land, and those who \x + \xo 24:8 \xt See ch. 43–44\x*dwell in the land of Egypt.
\v 9 I will make them \x + \xo 24:9 \xt See ch. 15:4 \x*a horror\f + \fr 24:9 \ft Compare Septuagint; Hebrew \fq horror for evil\f* to all the kingdoms of the earth, to be \x + \xo 24:9 \xt ch. 29:18; 49:13; Neh. 2:17; Isa. 43:28 \x*a reproach, \x + \xo 24:9 \xt Deut. 28:37; 2 Chr. 7:20 \x*a byword, \x + \xo 24:9 \xt ch. 29:18; 49:13; Neh. 2:17; Isa. 43:28 \x*a taunt, and \x + \xo 24:9 \xt ch. 25:18; 26:6; 29:22; 2 Kgs. 22:19\x*a curse in all the places where I shall drive them.
\v 10 And I will send \x + \xo 24:10 \xt See ch. 14:12\x*sword, famine, and pestilence upon them, until they shall be utterly destroyed from the land that I gave to them and their fathers.”
\c 25
\s1 Seventy Years of Captivity
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 25:1 \xt ch. 1:3; 36:1; [2 Kgs. 24:1]\x*The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of Judah, in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah (that was the first year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon),
\v 2 which Jeremiah the prophet spoke to all the people of Judah and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem:
\v 3 “For twenty-three years, \x + \xo 25:3 \xt ch. 1:2 \x*from the thirteenth year of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah, to this day, the word of the \nd Lord\nd* has come to me, and I have spoken \x + \xo 25:3 \xt ch. 7:13; 11:7, 8; 26:5; 29:19; 32:33; 35:14; 2 Chr. 36:15 \x*persistently to you, \x + \xo 25:3 \xt See ch. 7:13\x*but you have not listened.
\v 4 \x + \xo 25:4 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*You have neither listened nor inclined your ears to hear, although the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 25:4 \xt [See ver. 3 above]\x*persistently sent to you all his servants the prophets,
\v 5 saying, \x + \xo 25:5 \xt See ch. 18:11 \x*‘Turn now, every one of you, \x + \xo 25:5 \xt ch. 23:22 \x*from his evil way and evil deeds, and \x + \xo 25:5 \xt ch. 7:7\x*dwell upon the land that the \nd Lord\nd* has given to you and your fathers from of old and forever.
\v 6 \x + \xo 25:6 \xt See ch. 7:6 \x*Do not go after other gods to serve and worship them, \x + \xo 25:6 \xt [ch. 32:30]\x*or provoke me to anger \x + \xo 25:6 \xt [ch. 32:30]\x*with the work of your hands. Then I will do you no harm.’
\v 7 \x + \xo 25:7 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*Yet you have not listened to me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 25:7 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*that you might provoke me to anger \x + \xo 25:7 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*with the work of your hands to your own harm.
\p
\v 8 “Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts: Because you have not obeyed my words,
\v 9 \x + \xo 25:9 \xt ch. 1:15 \x*behold, I will send for all the tribes of the north, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and for Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, \x + \xo 25:9 \xt ch. 27:6; 43:10; [Isa. 44:28; 45:1]; See Ezek. 29:18-20 \x*my servant, and I will bring them against this land and its inhabitants, and against all these surrounding nations. I will devote them to destruction, \x + \xo 25:9 \xt See ch. 18:16\x*and make them a horror, a hissing, and an everlasting desolation.
\v 10 Moreover, \x + \xo 25:10 \xt See ch. 7:34 \x*I will banish from them the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, \x + \xo 25:10 \xt Eccles. 12:4; Rev. 18:22 \x*the grinding of the millstones and \x + \xo 25:10 \xt Rev. 18:23\x*the light of the lamp.
\v 11 \x + \xo 25:11 \xt [See ver. 9 above] \x*This whole land shall become a ruin and a waste, and \x + \xo 25:11 \xt [ch. 28:14]; See ch. 27:3-6 \x*these nations shall serve the king of Babylon \x + \xo 25:11 \xt 2 Chr. 36:21, 22; Ezra 1:1; Dan. 9:2; [Isa. 23:15]\x*seventy years.
\v 12 Then after \x + \xo 25:12 \xt [See ver. 11 above] \x*seventy years are completed, \x + \xo 25:12 \xt ch. 51:24, 26, 62; Isa. 13:19\x*I will punish the king of Babylon and that nation, \x + \xo 25:12 \xt ch. 51:24, 26, 62; Isa. 13:19\x*the land of the Chaldeans, for their iniquity, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 25:12 \xt ch. 51:24, 26, 62; Isa. 13:19\x*making the land an everlasting waste.
\v 13 I will bring upon that land all the words that I have uttered against it, everything written \x + \xo 25:13 \xt See ch. 46–51\x*in this book, which Jeremiah prophesied against all the nations.
\v 14 \x + \xo 25:14 \xt ch. 27:7; 50:9, 41; 51:27, 28 \x*For many nations \x + \xo 25:14 \xt ch. 27:7; 50:9, 41; 51:27, 28 \x*and great kings shall make slaves even of them, \x + \xo 25:14 \xt ch. 50:29; 51:6, 24\x*and I will recompense them according to their deeds and the work of their hands.”
\s1 The Cup of the \nd Lord\nd*’s Wrath
\p
\v 15 Thus the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, said to me: \x + \xo 25:15 \xt ch. 49:12; 51:7; Job 21:20; Ps. 60:3; 75:8; Isa. 51:17; Lam. 4:21; Rev. 14:10\x*“Take from my hand this cup of the wine of wrath, and make all the nations to whom I send you drink it.
\v 16 They shall drink and stagger and be crazed because of \x + \xo 25:16 \xt [ch. 47:6]\x*the sword that I am sending among them.”
\p
\v 17 So I took the cup from the \nd Lord\nd*’s hand, \x + \xo 25:17 \xt [Isa. 51:22, 23]\x*and made all the nations to whom the \nd Lord\nd* sent me drink it:
\v 18 \x + \xo 25:18 \xt [Zech. 12:2] \x*Jerusalem and the cities of Judah, its kings and officials, \x + \xo 25:18 \xt See ch. 18:16\x*to make them a desolation and a waste, a hissing and a curse, as at this day;
\v 19 \x + \xo 25:19 \xt ch. 46:25\x*Pharaoh king of Egypt, his servants, his officials, all his people,
\v 20 and \x + \xo 25:20 \xt ch. 50:37; [Ex. 12:38; Ezek. 30:5] \x*all the mixed tribes among them; all the kings of \x + \xo 25:20 \xt Job 1:1; Lam. 4:21 \x*the land of Uz and all the kings of \x + \xo 25:20 \xt ch. 47:1, 4, 5 \x*the land of the Philistines (\x + \xo 25:20 \xt ch. 47:1, 4, 5 \x*Ashkelon, \x + \xo 25:20 \xt ch. 47:1, 4, 5 \x*Gaza, Ekron, and the remnant of \x + \xo 25:20 \xt [Isa. 20:1]\x*Ashdod);
\v 21 \x + \xo 25:21 \xt ch. 9:26; See ch. 49:7-22 \x*Edom, \x + \xo 25:21 \xt See ch. 48 \x*Moab, and the sons of \x + \xo 25:21 \xt See ch. 49:1-6\x*Ammon;
\v 22 all the kings of \x + \xo 25:22 \xt ch. 47:4; Isa. 23:1, 2 \x*Tyre, all the kings of \x + \xo 25:22 \xt ch. 47:4; Isa. 23:1, 2 \x*Sidon, and the kings of the coastland across \x + \xo 25:22 \xt [ch. 49:23]\x*the sea;
\v 23 \x + \xo 25:23 \xt ch. 49:8; Isa. 21:13 \x*Dedan, \x + \xo 25:23 \xt Job 6:19 \x*Tema, \x + \xo 25:23 \xt [Job 32:2, 6] \x*Buz, and all who cut \x + \xo 25:23 \xt See ch. 9:26\x*the corners of their hair;
\v 24 all the \x + \xo 25:24 \xt 2 Chr. 9:14 \x*kings of Arabia and all the kings of \x + \xo 25:24 \xt [See ver. 20 above]\x*the mixed tribes who dwell in the desert;
\v 25 all the kings of Zimri, all the kings of \x + \xo 25:25 \xt Isa. 11:11; See ch. 49:34-39 \x*Elam, and all the kings of \x + \xo 25:25 \xt [2 Kgs. 17:6]\x*Media;
\v 26 all the kings of \x + \xo 25:26 \xt ch. 50:9 \x*the north, far and near, one after another, and all the kingdoms of the world that are on the face of the earth. And after them the king of \x + \xo 25:26 \xt ch. 51:41\x*Babylon\f + \fr 25:26 \ft Hebrew \+tl Sheshach\+tl*, a code name for Babylon\f* shall drink.
\p
\v 27 “Then you shall say to them, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 25:27 \xt Hab. 2:16 \x*Drink, be drunk and vomit, fall and rise no more, because of \x + \xo 25:27 \xt Ezek. 38:21; [ver. 16]\x*the sword that I am sending among you.’
\p
\v 28 “And if they refuse to accept the cup from your hand to drink, then you shall say to them, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts: \x + \xo 25:28 \xt ch. 49:12\x*You must drink!
\v 29 For behold, \x + \xo 25:29 \xt Prov. 11:31; Isa. 10:12; Amos 3:2; Obad. 16; [1 Pet. 4:17] \x*I begin to work disaster at the city that is called by my name, and shall you go unpunished? You shall not go unpunished, \x + \xo 25:29 \xt [See ver. 27 above]\x*for I am summoning a sword against all the inhabitants of the earth, declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts.’
\p
\v 30 “You, therefore, shall prophesy against them all these words, and say to them:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 25:30 \xt Joel 3:16; Amos 1:2 \x*“‘The \nd Lord\nd* will roar from on high,
\q2 and from his holy habitation utter his voice;
\q1 he will roar mightily against his fold,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:30 \xt [Judg. 9:27; Isa. 16:9]\x*and shout, like those who tread grapes,
\q2 against all the inhabitants of the earth.
\q1
\v 31 The clamor will resound to the ends of the earth,
\q2 for \x + \xo 25:31 \xt Hos. 4:1 \x*the \nd Lord\nd* has an indictment against the nations;
\q1 \x + \xo 25:31 \xt Isa. 66:16; [Joel 3:2]\x*he is entering into judgment with all flesh,
\q2 and the wicked he will put to the sword,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.’
\b
\q1
\v 32 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts:
\q1 Behold, disaster is going forth
\q2 from nation to nation,
\q1 \x + \xo 25:32 \xt ch. 23:19; 30:23 \x*and a great tempest is stirring
\q2 \x + \xo 25:32 \xt ch. 6:22\x*from the farthest parts of the earth!
\b
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 25:33 \xt Isa. 66:16 \x*“And those pierced by the \nd Lord\nd* on that day shall extend from one end of the earth to the other. \x + \xo 25:33 \xt See ch. 16:4 \x*They shall not be lamented, \x + \xo 25:33 \xt See ch. 8:2\x*or gathered, or buried; \x + \xo 25:33 \xt See ch. 8:2\x*they shall be dung on the surface of the ground.
\b
\q1
\v 34 \x + \xo 25:34 \xt ch. 4:8 \x*“Wail, \x + \xo 25:34 \xt See ch. 23:1 \x*you shepherds, and cry out,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:34 \xt ch. 6:26\x*and roll in ashes, you lords of the flock,
\q1 for the days of your slaughter and dispersion have come,
\q2 and you shall fall like a choice vessel.
\q1
\v 35 No refuge will remain \x + \xo 25:35 \xt See ch. 23:1\x*for the shepherds,
\q2 nor escape for the lords of the flock.
\q1
\v 36 A voice—the cry \x + \xo 25:36 \xt [See ver. 35 above] \x*of the shepherds,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:36 \xt ch. 4:8\x*and the wail of the lords of the flock!
\q1 For the \nd Lord\nd* is laying waste their pasture,
\q2
\v 37 \x + \xo 25:37 \xt [Isa. 32:18] \x*and the peaceful folds are devastated
\q2 \x + \xo 25:37 \xt See ch. 12:13\x*because of the fierce anger of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 38 Like a lion \x + \xo 25:38 \xt [Job 38:40] \x*he has left his lair,
\q2 for their land has become a waste
\q1 because of \x + \xo 25:38 \xt ch. 46:16; 50:16 \x*the sword of the oppressor,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:38 \xt [See ver. 37 above]\x*and because of his fierce anger.”
\c 26
\s1 Jeremiah Threatened with Death
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 26:1 \xt ch. 27:1 \x*In the beginning of the reign of \x + \xo 26:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 23:36; 2 Chr. 36:5\x*Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came from the \nd Lord\nd*:
\v 2 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 26:2 \xt ch. 19:14 \x*Stand in the court of the \nd Lord\nd*’s house, and speak to all the cities of Judah that come to worship in the house of the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 26:2 \xt [Ezek. 3:10] \x*all the words that I command you to speak to them; \x + \xo 26:2 \xt Deut. 4:2; 12:32; [Acts 20:27]\x*do not hold back a word.
\v 3 \x + \xo 26:3 \xt ch. 36:3 \x*It may be they will listen, and every one turn from his evil way, \x + \xo 26:3 \xt ver. 13, 19; See ch. 18:8 \x*that I may relent of the disaster that I intend to do to them \x + \xo 26:3 \xt ch. 4:4\x*because of their evil deeds.
\v 4 You shall say to them, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 26:4 \xt Lev. 26:14; Deut. 28:15\x*If you will not listen to me, to walk in my law that I have set before you,
\v 5 \x + \xo 26:5 \xt See ch. 25:3, 4\x*and to listen to the words of my servants the prophets whom I send to you \x + \xo 26:5 \xt See ch. 25:3, 4\x*urgently, \x + \xo 26:5 \xt See ch. 25:3, 4\x*though you have not listened,
\v 6 then I will make this house \x + \xo 26:6 \xt See ch. 7:12 \x*like Shiloh, and I will make this city \x + \xo 26:6 \xt See ch. 24:9\x*a curse for all the nations of the earth.’”
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 26:7 \xt ch. 23:33\x*The priests and the prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah speaking these words in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 8 And when Jeremiah had finished speaking all that the \nd Lord\nd* had commanded him to speak to all the people, then \x + \xo 26:8 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*the priests and the prophets and all the people laid hold of him, saying, “You shall die!
\v 9 Why have you prophesied in the name of the \nd Lord\nd*, saying, ‘This house shall be \x + \xo 26:9 \xt [See ver. 6 above] \x*like Shiloh, and this city shall be desolate, \x + \xo 26:9 \xt See ch. 4:7\x*without inhabitant’?” And all the people gathered around Jeremiah in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\p
\v 10 When \x + \xo 26:10 \xt ch. 36:12 \x*the officials of Judah heard these things, they came up from the king’s house to the house of the \nd Lord\nd* and took their seat in the \x + \xo 26:10 \xt ch. 36:10\x*entry of the New Gate of the house of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 11 Then \x + \xo 26:11 \xt [See ver. 7 above] \x*the priests and the prophets said to the officials and to all the people, \x + \xo 26:11 \xt ch. 38:4; [ver. 16]\x*“This man deserves the sentence of death, because he has prophesied against this city, as you have heard with your own ears.”
\p
\v 12 Then Jeremiah spoke to all the officials and all the people, saying, “The \nd Lord\nd* sent me to prophesy against this house and this city all the words you have heard.
\v 13 Now therefore \x + \xo 26:13 \xt See ch. 7:3 \x*mend your ways and your deeds, \x + \xo 26:13 \xt Deut. 30:2 \x*and obey the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* your God, \x + \xo 26:13 \xt [See ver. 3 above]\x*and the \nd Lord\nd* will relent of the disaster that he has pronounced against you.
\v 14 \x + \xo 26:14 \xt Josh. 9:25\x*But as for me, behold, I am in your hands. Do with me as seems good and right to you.
\v 15 Only know for certain that if you put me to death, \x + \xo 26:15 \xt [Matt. 27:24]\x*you will bring innocent blood upon yourselves and upon this city and its inhabitants, for in truth the \nd Lord\nd* sent me to you to speak all these words in your ears.”
\s1 Jeremiah Spared from Death
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 26:16 \xt ver. 8 \x*Then the officials and all the people said to the priests and the prophets, \x + \xo 26:16 \xt [ver. 11]\x*“This man does not deserve the sentence of death, for he has spoken to us in the name of the \nd Lord\nd* our God.”
\v 17 \x + \xo 26:17 \xt [Acts 5:34] \x*And certain of \x + \xo 26:17 \xt See ch. 19:1\x*the elders of the land arose and spoke to all the assembled people, saying,
\v 18 “Micah of Moresheth prophesied in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah, and said to all the people of Judah: ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 26:18 \xt Mic. 3:12\x*“‘Zion shall be plowed as a field;
\q2 Jerusalem shall become a heap of ruins,
\q2 and the mountain of the house a wooded height.’
\b
\m
\v 19 Did Hezekiah king of Judah and all Judah put him to death? \x + \xo 26:19 \xt [2 Chr. 32:26] \x*Did he not fear the \nd Lord\nd* and entreat the favor of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 26:19 \xt Ex. 32:14; 2 Sam. 24:16; [1 Kgs. 13:6] \x*and did not the \nd Lord\nd* relent of the disaster that he had pronounced against them? \x + \xo 26:19 \xt [Acts 5:39]\x*But we are about to bring great disaster upon ourselves.”
\p
\v 20 There was another man who prophesied in the name of the \nd Lord\nd*, Uriah the son of Shemaiah from \x + \xo 26:20 \xt Josh. 9:17; 1 Sam. 6:21; 7:1, 2; 1 Chr. 13:5, 6\x*Kiriath-jearim. He prophesied against this city and against this land in words like those of Jeremiah.
\v 21 And when \x + \xo 26:21 \xt ver. 1; ch. 27:1\x*King Jehoiakim, with all his warriors and all the officials, heard his words, the king sought to put him to death. But when Uriah heard of it, he was afraid and fled and escaped to Egypt.
\v 22 Then \x + \xo 26:22 \xt [See ver. 21 above] \x*King Jehoiakim sent to Egypt certain men, \x + \xo 26:22 \xt ch. 36:12, 25 \x*Elnathan the son of \x + \xo 26:22 \xt 2 Kgs. 22:12, 14\x*Achbor and others with him,
\v 23 and they took Uriah from Egypt and brought him to King Jehoiakim, \x + \xo 26:23 \xt [ch. 22:17; Neh. 9:26; Matt. 21:35; 23:37]\x*who struck him down with the sword and dumped his dead body into the burial place of the common people.
\p
\v 24 But the hand of \x + \xo 26:24 \xt 2 Kgs. 22:12\x*Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah so that he was not given over to the people to be put to death.
\c 27
\s1 The Yoke of Nebuchadnezzar
\p \v 1 In the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah\f + \fr 27:1 \ft Or \fq Jehoiakim\f* the son of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 2 Thus the \nd Lord\nd* said to me: \x + \xo 27:2 \xt [1 Kgs. 22:11; Ezek. 7:23] \x*“Make yourself straps and \x + \xo 27:2 \xt ch. 28:10, 12, 13; See Lev. 26:13\x*yoke-bars, and put them on your neck.
\v 3 Send word\f + \fr 27:3 \ft Hebrew \fq Send them\f* to the king of \x + \xo 27:3 \xt ch. 25:21, 22\x*Edom, the king of \x + \xo 27:3 \xt ch. 25:21, 22\x*Moab, the king of the sons of \x + \xo 27:3 \xt ch. 25:21, 22\x*Ammon, the king of \x + \xo 27:3 \xt ch. 25:21, 22\x*Tyre, and the king of Sidon by the hand of the envoys who have come to Jerusalem to Zedekiah king of Judah.
\v 4 Give them this charge for their masters: ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: This is what you shall say to your masters:
\v 5 “It is I who \x + \xo 27:5 \xt See ch. 21:5 \x*by my great power and my outstretched arm \x + \xo 27:5 \xt Ps. 115:15; Isa. 45:12 \x*have made the earth, with the men and animals that are on the earth, \x + \xo 27:5 \xt Ps. 115:16; Dan. 4:17, 25, 32\x*and I give it to whomever it seems right to me.
\v 6 \x + \xo 27:6 \xt [Ezek. 30:21, 25] \x*Now I have given all these lands into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar, the king of Babylon, \x + \xo 27:6 \xt See ch. 25:9 \x*my servant, \x + \xo 27:6 \xt ch. 28:14; Dan. 2:38\x*and I have given him also the beasts of the field to serve him.
\v 7 \x + \xo 27:7 \xt [Dan. 2:37, 38] \x*All the nations shall serve him and \x + \xo 27:7 \xt ch. 52:31 \x*his son and \x + \xo 27:7 \xt Dan. 5:1, 30 \x*his grandson, \x + \xo 27:7 \xt See ch. 25:12 \x*until the time of his own land comes. \x + \xo 27:7 \xt See ch. 25:14\x*Then many nations and great kings shall make him their slave.
\p
\v 8 “‘“But if any nation or kingdom will not serve this Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, \x + \xo 27:8 \xt ver. 11, 12; [ch. 30:8] \x*and put its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon, I will punish that nation \x + \xo 27:8 \xt See ch. 14:12\x*with the sword, with famine, and with pestilence, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, until I have consumed it by his hand.
\v 9 So \x + \xo 27:9 \xt [ch. 14:14] \x*do not listen to your \x + \xo 27:9 \xt [ch. 29:8] \x*prophets, your diviners, your dreamers, your \x + \xo 27:9 \xt [Deut. 18:10; Isa. 2:6]\x*fortune-tellers, or your sorcerers, who are saying to you, ‘You shall not serve the king of Babylon.’
\v 10 \x + \xo 27:10 \xt See ch. 5:31\x*For it is a lie that they are prophesying to you, with the result that you will be removed far from your land, and I will drive you out, and you will perish.
\v 11 \x + \xo 27:11 \xt [ver. 2, 8]\x*But any nation that will bring its neck under the yoke of the king of Babylon and serve him, I will leave on its own land, to work it and dwell there, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”’”
\p
\v 12 To \x + \xo 27:12 \xt ch. 28:1; [ver. 1] \x*Zedekiah king of Judah I spoke in like manner: \x + \xo 27:12 \xt [See ver. 11 above] \x*“Bring your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon, and \x + \xo 27:12 \xt ver. 17; [ch. 38:17]\x*serve him and his people and live.
\v 13 \x + \xo 27:13 \xt Ezek. 18:31 \x*Why will you and your people die \x + \xo 27:13 \xt See ch. 14:12 \x*by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence, \x + \xo 27:13 \xt ver. 8\x*as the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken concerning any nation that will not serve the king of Babylon?
\v 14 \x + \xo 27:14 \xt [ch. 14:14] \x*Do not listen to the words of the prophets who are saying to you, ‘You shall not serve the king of Babylon,’ \x + \xo 27:14 \xt [See ver. 10 above]\x*for it is a lie that they are prophesying to you.
\v 15 I have not sent them, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, but \x + \xo 27:15 \xt [See ver. 10 above]\x*they are prophesying falsely in my name, with the result that I will drive you out and you will perish, you and the prophets who are prophesying to you.”
\p
\v 16 Then I spoke to the priests and to all this people, saying, “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 27:16 \xt [See ver. 14 above] \x*Do not listen to the words of your prophets who are prophesying to you, saying, \x + \xo 27:16 \xt ch. 28:3; 2 Kgs. 24:13; 2 Chr. 36:7, 10, 18 \x*‘Behold, the vessels of the \nd Lord\nd*’s house will now shortly be brought back from Babylon,’ \x + \xo 27:16 \xt [See ver. 10 above]\x*for it is a lie that they are prophesying to you.
\v 17 \x + \xo 27:17 \xt [See ver. 14 above] \x*Do not listen to them; \x + \xo 27:17 \xt [See ver. 11 above] \x*serve the king of Babylon and live. Why should this city \x + \xo 27:17 \xt See ch. 7:34\x*become a desolation?
\v 18 If they are prophets, and if the word of the \nd Lord\nd* is with them, then \x + \xo 27:18 \xt [Isa. 59:16] \x*let them intercede with the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, \x + \xo 27:18 \xt Dan. 1:2\x*that the vessels that are left in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*, in the house of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem may not go to Babylon.
\v 19 \x + \xo 27:19 \xt [2 Kgs. 25:13]\x*For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts concerning the pillars, the sea, the stands, and the rest of the vessels that are left in this city,
\v 20 which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon did not take away, \x + \xo 27:20 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:14, 15; Matt. 1:11, 12; See ch. 24:1\x*when he took into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, and all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem—
\v 21 thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel, \x + \xo 27:21 \xt [See ver. 19 above]\x*concerning the vessels that are left in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*, in the house of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem:
\v 22 \x + \xo 27:22 \xt ch. 52:17, 20, 21; 2 Kgs. 25:13; 2 Chr. 36:18 \x*They shall be carried to Babylon \x + \xo 27:22 \xt ch. 32:5 \x*and remain there \x + \xo 27:22 \xt ch. 29:10; 2 Chr. 36:22; Ezra 1:1 \x*until the day when I visit them, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. \x + \xo 27:22 \xt Ezra 1:7, 8; 5:14; 7:19\x*Then I will bring them back \x + \xo 27:22 \xt ch. 52:17, 20, 21; 2 Kgs. 25:13; 2 Chr. 36:18 \x*and restore them to this place.”
\c 28
\s1 Hananiah the False Prophet
\p \v 1 In that same year, at the beginning of the reign of \x + \xo 28:1 \xt ch. 27:12 \x*Zedekiah king of Judah, in the fifth month of the fourth year, Hananiah the son of \x + \xo 28:1 \xt Ezek. 11:1 \x*Azzur, the prophet from \x + \xo 28:1 \xt Josh. 9:3; 21:17\x*Gibeon, spoke to me in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*, in the presence of the priests and all the people, saying,
\v 2 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 28:2 \xt [ch. 27:2, 11, 12]\x*I have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon.
\v 3 \x + \xo 28:3 \xt ch. 27:16 \x*Within \x + \xo 28:3 \xt ver. 11\x*two years I will bring back to this place all the vessels of the \nd Lord\nd*’s house, which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took away from this place and carried to Babylon.
\v 4 I will also bring back to this place \x + \xo 28:4 \xt [ch. 22:10, 12, 26] \x*Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, and all the exiles from Judah who went to Babylon, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 28:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above]\x*for I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon.”
\p
\v 5 Then the prophet Jeremiah spoke to Hananiah the prophet in the presence of the priests and all the people who were standing in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\v 6 and the prophet Jeremiah said, \x + \xo 28:6 \xt 1 Kgs. 1:36\x*“Amen! May the \nd Lord\nd* do so; may the \nd Lord\nd* make the words that you have prophesied come true, and bring back to this place from Babylon the vessels of the house of the \nd Lord\nd*, and all the exiles.
\v 7 Yet hear now this word that I speak in your hearing and in the hearing of all the people.
\v 8 \x + \xo 28:8 \xt [ch. 26:18]\x*The prophets who preceded you and me from ancient times prophesied war, famine, and pestilence against many countries and great kingdoms.
\v 9 \x + \xo 28:9 \xt Deut. 18:22; See ch. 6:14\x*As for the prophet who prophesies peace, when the word of that prophet comes to pass, then it will be known that the \nd Lord\nd* has truly sent the prophet.”
\p
\v 10 Then the prophet Hananiah took the \x + \xo 28:10 \xt ch. 27:2\x*yoke-bars from the neck of Jeremiah the prophet and broke them.
\v 11 And Hananiah spoke in the presence of all the people, saying, \x + \xo 28:11 \xt [1 Kgs. 22:11] \x*“Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 28:11 \xt ver. 2, 3 \x*Even so will I break the yoke of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon from the neck of \x + \xo 28:11 \xt ch. 27:7\x*all the nations within two years.” But Jeremiah the prophet went his way.
\p
\v 12 Sometime after the prophet \x + \xo 28:12 \xt ver. 1, 10\x*Hananiah had broken the yoke-bars from off the neck of Jeremiah the prophet, the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah:
\v 13 “Go, tell Hananiah, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: You have broken wooden bars, but you have made in their place bars of iron.
\v 14 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: I have put upon the neck of all these nations \x + \xo 28:14 \xt Deut. 28:48 \x*an iron yoke to serve Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, \x + \xo 28:14 \xt [ch. 25:11] \x*and they shall serve him, \x + \xo 28:14 \xt See ch. 27:6\x*for I have given to him even the beasts of the field.’”
\v 15 And Jeremiah the prophet said to the prophet Hananiah, “Listen, Hananiah, \x + \xo 28:15 \xt ch. 29:31; Deut. 18:20; [Ezek. 13:22, 23] \x*the \nd Lord\nd* has not sent you, \x + \xo 28:15 \xt See ch. 5:31\x*and you have made this people trust in a lie.
\v 16 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: ‘Behold, I will remove you from the face of the earth. This year you shall die, \x + \xo 28:16 \xt ch. 29:32; Deut. 13:5\x*because you have uttered rebellion against the \nd Lord\nd*.’”
\p
\v 17 In that same year, in the seventh month, the prophet Hananiah died.
\c 29
\s1 Jeremiah’s Letter to the Exiles
\p \v 1 These are the words of the letter that Jeremiah the prophet sent from Jerusalem to \x + \xo 29:1 \xt Ezek. 8:1 \x*the surviving elders of the exiles, and to \x + \xo 29:1 \xt [ch. 23:33]\x*the priests, \x + \xo 29:1 \xt [ch. 23:33]\x*the prophets, and \x + \xo 29:1 \xt [ch. 23:33]\x*all the people, whom Nebuchadnezzar had taken into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon.
\v 2 This was after \x + \xo 29:2 \xt ch. 24:1; 2 Kgs. 24:12, 14\x*King Jeconiah and the queen mother, the eunuchs, the officials of Judah and Jerusalem, the craftsmen, and the metal workers had departed from Jerusalem.
\v 3 The letter was sent by the hand of Elasah the son of \x + \xo 29:3 \xt 2 Chr. 34:8 \x*Shaphan and Gemariah the son of \x + \xo 29:3 \xt 1 Chr. 6:13\x*Hilkiah, whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent to Babylon to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon. It said:
\v 4 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel, to all the exiles whom I have sent into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon:
\v 5 \x + \xo 29:5 \xt ver. 28\x*Build houses and live in them; plant gardens and eat their produce.
\v 6 Take wives and have sons and daughters; take wives for your sons, and give your daughters in marriage, that they may bear sons and daughters; multiply there, and do not decrease.
\v 7 But seek the welfare of the city where I have sent you into exile, and \x + \xo 29:7 \xt [Ezra 6:10; 1 Tim. 2:1, 2]\x*pray to the \nd Lord\nd* on its behalf, for in its welfare you will find your welfare.
\v 8 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 29:8 \xt [ch. 5:31; 6:14] \x*Do not let your prophets and \x + \xo 29:8 \xt ch. 27:9, 15\x*your diviners who are among you deceive you, and do not listen to the dreams that they dream,\f + \fr 29:8 \ft Hebrew \fq your dreams, which you cause to dream\f*
\v 9 for \x + \xo 29:9 \xt See ch. 5:31 \x*it is a lie that they are prophesying to you in my name; \x + \xo 29:9 \xt ver. 31\x*I did not send them, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\p
\v 10 “For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 29:10 \xt See ch. 25:12 \x*When seventy years are completed for Babylon, \x + \xo 29:10 \xt ch. 27:22 \x*I will visit you, \x + \xo 29:10 \xt ch. 33:14; [ch. 24:6]\x*and I will fulfill to you my promise \x + \xo 29:10 \xt ch. 33:14; [ch. 24:6]\x*and bring you back to this place.
\v 11 \x + \xo 29:11 \xt [Isa. 55:8, 9] \x*For I know the plans I have for you, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, plans for welfare\f + \fr 29:11 \ft Or \fq peace\f* and not for evil, \x + \xo 29:11 \xt ch. 31:17\x*to give you a future and a hope.
\v 12 \x + \xo 29:12 \xt ch. 33:3; Dan. 9:3\x*Then you will call upon me and come and pray to me, \x + \xo 29:12 \xt ch. 33:3; Dan. 9:3\x*and I will hear you.
\v 13 \x + \xo 29:13 \xt 2 Chr. 15:2; Ps. 32:6; 78:34; Prov. 8:17; Isa. 55:6; Hos. 3:5; See Lev. 26:39-42; Deut. 30:1-3 \x*You will seek me and find me, when you seek me \x + \xo 29:13 \xt ch. 24:7; Deut. 4:29\x*with all your heart.
\v 14 I will be found by you, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 29:14 \xt ch. 30:3 \x*and I will restore your fortunes and \x + \xo 29:14 \xt See ch. 23:3 \x*gather you from all the nations and all the places \x + \xo 29:14 \xt See ch. 8:3\x*where I have driven you, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and I will bring you back to the place from which I sent you into exile.
\p
\v 15 “Because you have said, ‘The \nd Lord\nd* has raised up prophets for us in Babylon,’
\v 16 thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning \x + \xo 29:16 \xt See ch. 22:2\x*the king who sits on the throne of David, and concerning all the people who dwell in this city, your kinsmen who did not go out with you into exile:
\v 17 ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, behold, I am sending on them \x + \xo 29:17 \xt See ch. 24:10 \x*sword, famine, and pestilence, and I will make them like \x + \xo 29:17 \xt ch. 24:8\x*vile figs that are so rotten they cannot be eaten.
\v 18 I will pursue them with \x + \xo 29:18 \xt [See ver. 17 above] \x*sword, famine, and pestilence, \x + \xo 29:18 \xt See ch. 15:4 \x*and will make them a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth, \x + \xo 29:18 \xt ch. 18:16; 42:18; See ch. 24:9 \x*to be a curse, a terror, a hissing, and a reproach among all the nations \x + \xo 29:18 \xt [See ver. 14 above]\x*where I have driven them,
\v 19 because they did not pay attention to my words, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 29:19 \xt See ch. 25:4\x*that I persistently sent to you by my servants the prophets, but you would not listen, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.’
\v 20 Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, all you exiles \x + \xo 29:20 \xt ch. 24:5\x*whom I sent away from Jerusalem to Babylon:
\v 21 ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning Ahab the son of Kolaiah and Zedekiah the son of Maaseiah, \x + \xo 29:21 \xt ver. 9; See ch. 14:14\x*who are prophesying a lie to you in my name: Behold, I will deliver them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and he shall strike them down before your eyes.
\v 22 \x + \xo 29:22 \xt See Isa. 65:15 \x*Because of them \x + \xo 29:22 \xt See ch. 24:9 \x*this curse shall be used by all the exiles from Judah in Babylon: “The \nd Lord\nd* make you like Zedekiah and Ahab, \x + \xo 29:22 \xt [Dan. 3:6]\x*whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire,”
\v 23 because they have done an outrageous thing in Israel, \x + \xo 29:23 \xt ch. 23:14 \x*they have committed adultery with their neighbors’ wives, and \x + \xo 29:23 \xt ch. 23:14 \x*they have spoken in my name lying words that I did not command them. \x + \xo 29:23 \xt Mal. 3:5\x*I am the one who knows, \x + \xo 29:23 \xt Mal. 3:5\x*and I am witness, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.’”
\s1 Shemaiah’s False Prophecy
\p
\v 24 To \x + \xo 29:24 \xt ver. 31, 32\x*Shemaiah of Nehelam you shall say:
\v 25 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: You have sent letters in your name to all the people who are in Jerusalem, and to \x + \xo 29:25 \xt ch. 21:1; 2 Kgs. 25:18 \x*Zephaniah the son of \x + \xo 29:25 \xt ch. 35:4\x*Maaseiah the priest, and to all the priests, saying,
\v 26 ‘The \nd Lord\nd* has made you priest instead of Jehoiada the priest, to have \x + \xo 29:26 \xt [ch. 20:1] \x*charge in the house of the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 29:26 \xt [2 Kgs. 9:11; Acts 26:24] \x*over every madman who prophesies, to put him in \x + \xo 29:26 \xt ch. 20:2\x*the stocks and neck irons.
\v 27 Now why have you not rebuked Jeremiah \x + \xo 29:27 \xt ch. 1:1; 32:7\x*of Anathoth who is prophesying to you?
\v 28 For he has sent to us in Babylon, saying, “Your exile will be long; \x + \xo 29:28 \xt ver. 5\x*build houses and live in them, and plant gardens and eat their produce.”’”
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 29:29 \xt [See ver. 25 above]\x*Zephaniah the priest read this letter in the hearing of Jeremiah the prophet.
\v 30 \x + \xo 29:30 \xt ver. 1, 20\x*Then the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah:
\v 31 “Send to all the exiles, saying, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning \x + \xo 29:31 \xt ver. 24 \x*Shemaiah of Nehelam: Because \x + \xo 29:31 \xt ver. 24 \x*Shemaiah had prophesied to you \x + \xo 29:31 \xt ver. 9; See ch. 5:31\x*when I did not send him, and has made you trust in a lie,
\v 32 therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: Behold, I will punish \x + \xo 29:32 \xt [See ver. 31 above] \x*Shemaiah of Nehelam and his descendants. He shall not have anyone living among this people, \x + \xo 29:32 \xt See ch. 17:6 \x*and he shall not see the good that I will do to my people, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 29:32 \xt ch. 28:16\x*for he has spoken rebellion against the \nd Lord\nd*.’”
\c 30
\s1 Restoration for Israel and Judah
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*:
\v 2 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 30:2 \xt ch. 36:2; Hab. 2:2\x*Write in a book all the words that I have spoken to you.
\v 3 \x + \xo 30:3 \xt Hab. 2:3 \x*For behold, days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 30:3 \xt ver. 18; ch. 29:14; 31:23; 32:44; 33:7, 11, 26; Job 42:10; Lam. 2:14 \x*when I will restore \x + \xo 30:3 \xt Ezra 2:1 \x*the fortunes of my people, \x + \xo 30:3 \xt Isa. 11:12, 13; Hos. 1:11 \x*Israel and Judah, says the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 30:3 \xt ch. 12:15; Ezek. 20:42; See ch. 16:15; 23:3\x*and I will bring them back to the land that I gave to their fathers, and they shall take possession of it.”
\p
\v 4 These are the words that the \nd Lord\nd* spoke concerning \x + \xo 30:4 \xt [See ver. 3 above]\x*Israel and Judah:
\b
\q1
\v 5 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 We have heard a cry of panic,
\q2 of terror, and no peace.
\q1
\v 6 Ask now, and see,
\q2 can a man bear a child?
\q1 \x + \xo 30:6 \xt See Isa. 13:8 \x*Why then do I see every man
\q2 with his hands on his stomach \x + \xo 30:6 \xt See Isa. 13:8 \x*like a woman in labor?
\q2 \x + \xo 30:6 \xt Nah. 2:10; [Joel 2:6]\x*Why has every face turned pale?
\q1
\v 7 Alas! \x + \xo 30:7 \xt Joel 2:11; Zeph. 1:14 \x*That day is so great
\q2 \x + \xo 30:7 \xt Dan. 12:1\x*there is none like it;
\q1 it is a time of distress for Jacob;
\q2 yet he shall be saved out of it.
\b
\p
\v 8 “And it shall come to pass in that day, declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, that I will \x + \xo 30:8 \xt ch. 2:20; Nah. 1:13 \x*break his \x + \xo 30:8 \xt See ch. 27:2 \x*yoke from off your neck, and I will \x + \xo 30:8 \xt ch. 2:20; Nah. 1:13 \x*burst your bonds, \x + \xo 30:8 \xt Ezek. 34:27\x*and foreigners shall no more make a servant of him.\f + \fr 30:8 \ft Or \fq serve him\f*
\v 9 But they shall serve the \nd Lord\nd* their God and \x + \xo 30:9 \xt Isa. 55:3, 4; Ezek. 34:23; 37:24; Hos. 3:5; [Luke 1:69, 70; Acts 13:22, 23]; See ch. 23:5\x*David their king, whom I will raise up for them.
\b
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 30:10 \xt ch. 42:11; 46:27, 28; See Isa. 43:5 \x*“Then fear not, \x + \xo 30:10 \xt Isa. 41:8 \x*O Jacob my servant, declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 nor be dismayed, O Israel;
\q1 for behold, \x + \xo 30:10 \xt ch. 42:11; 46:27, 28; See Isa. 43:5 \x*I will save you from far away,
\q2 \x + \xo 30:10 \xt See ch. 3:18\x*and your offspring from the land of their captivity.
\q1 \x + \xo 30:10 \xt ch. 42:11; 46:27, 28; See Isa. 43:5 \x*Jacob shall return and have quiet and ease,
\q2 and none shall make him afraid.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 30:11 \xt ch. 46:28 \x*For I am with you to save you,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q1 \x + \xo 30:11 \xt ch. 46:28 \x*I will make a full end of all the nations
\q2 among whom I scattered you,
\q2 but of you I will not make a full end.
\q1 \x + \xo 30:11 \xt ch. 46:28 \x*I will \x + \xo 30:11 \xt See ch. 10:24\x*discipline you in just measure,
\q2 and I will by no means leave you unpunished.
\b
\q1
\v 12 “For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 \x + \xo 30:12 \xt See ch. 15:18 \x*Your hurt is incurable,
\q2 \x + \xo 30:12 \xt ch. 10:19; 14:17\x*and your wound is grievous.
\q1
\v 13 There is none to uphold your cause,
\q2 no medicine for your wound,
\q2 \x + \xo 30:13 \xt ch. 46:11\x*no healing for you.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 30:14 \xt Lam. 1:2; [ch. 4:30] \x*All your lovers have forgotten you;
\q2 they care nothing for you;
\q1 for I have dealt you the blow of \x + \xo 30:14 \xt Job 13:24; 19:11; Isa. 63:10; Lam. 2:4 \x*an enemy,
\q2 the punishment \x + \xo 30:14 \xt Job 30:21; [ch. 6:23] \x*of a merciless foe,
\q1 because your guilt is great,
\q2 \x + \xo 30:14 \xt ch. 5:6\x*because your sins are flagrant.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 30:15 \xt [See ver. 12 above] \x*Why do you cry out over your hurt?
\q2 \x + \xo 30:15 \xt [See ver. 12 above] \x*Your pain is incurable.
\q1 Because your guilt is great,
\q2 \x + \xo 30:15 \xt [See ver. 14 above]\x*because your sins are flagrant,
\q2 I have done these things to you.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 30:16 \xt [ver. 11; ch. 10:25; Isa. 41:11] \x*Therefore all who devour you shall be devoured,
\q2 and \x + \xo 30:16 \xt [Ex. 23:22] \x*all your foes, every one of them, shall go into captivity;
\q1 \x + \xo 30:16 \xt [Isa. 33:1] \x*those who plunder you shall be plundered,
\q2 \x + \xo 30:16 \xt ch. 2:14\x*and all who prey on you I will make a prey.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 30:17 \xt ch. 33:6 \x*For I will restore \x + \xo 30:17 \xt ch. 8:22 \x*health to you,
\q2 and \x + \xo 30:17 \xt Ps. 6:2; Hos. 6:1 \x*your wounds I will heal,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 because \x + \xo 30:17 \xt [Mic. 4:6, 7; Zeph. 3:19]\x*they have called you an outcast:
\q2 \x + \xo 30:17 \xt [Mic. 4:6, 7; Zeph. 3:19]\x*‘It is Zion, for whom no one cares!’
\b
\q1
\v 18 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 Behold, \x + \xo 30:18 \xt [Amos 9:11]; See ver. 3 \x*I will restore the fortunes of the tents of Jacob
\q2 and have compassion on his dwellings;
\q1 the city shall be rebuilt on \x + \xo 30:18 \xt Deut. 13:16\x*its mound,
\q2 and the palace shall stand where it used to be.
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 30:19 \xt ch. 31:12, 13; 33:11; Isa. 35:10; 51:11 \x*Out of them shall come songs of thanksgiving,
\q2 and the voices of those who celebrate.
\q1 \x + \xo 30:19 \xt Ezek. 36:10, 37; Zech. 10:8\x*I will multiply them, and they shall not be few;
\q2 I will make them honored, and they shall not be small.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 30:20 \xt Isa. 1:26\x*Their children shall be as they were of old,
\q2 and their congregation shall be established before me,
\q2 and I will punish all who oppress them.
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 30:21 \xt [Gen. 49:10; Deut. 18:18] \x*Their prince shall be one of themselves;
\q2 \x + \xo 30:21 \xt [Gen. 49:10; Deut. 18:18] \x*their ruler shall come out from their midst;
\q1 \x + \xo 30:21 \xt Num. 16:5 \x*I will make him draw near, and he shall approach me,
\q2 \x + \xo 30:21 \xt ch. 49:19; [Heb. 5:4]\x*for who would dare of himself to approach me?
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 30:22 \xt ch. 24:7; 31:1; 32:38; See ch. 31:33; Lev. 26:12\x*And you shall be my people,
\q2 and I will be your God.”
\b
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 30:23 \xt ch. 23:19, 20 \x*Behold \x + \xo 30:23 \xt ch. 25:32\x*the storm of the \nd Lord\nd*!
\q2 Wrath has gone forth,
\q1 a whirling tempest;
\q2 it will burst upon the head of the wicked.
\q1
\v 24 \x + \xo 30:24 \xt See ch. 12:13 \x*The fierce anger of the \nd Lord\nd* will not turn back
\q2 until he has executed and accomplished
\q2 the intentions of his mind.
\q1 \x + \xo 30:24 \xt Hos. 3:5\x*In the latter days you will understand this.
\c 31
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Will Turn Mourning to Joy
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 31:1 \xt ch. 30:24 \x*“At that time, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 31:1 \xt [2 Cor. 6:18]; See ch. 30:22\x*I will be the God of all the clans of Israel, and they shall be my people.”
\b
\q1
\v 2 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 “The people who survived the sword
\q2 found grace in the wilderness;
\q1 \x + \xo 31:2 \xt [ch. 30:10; Ps. 95:11; Isa. 63:14]\x*when Israel sought for rest,
\q2
\v 3 the \nd Lord\nd* appeared to him\f + \fr 31:3 \ft Septuagint; Hebrew \fq me\f* from far away.
\q1 \x + \xo 31:3 \xt Deut. 7:8; 10:15; Mal. 1:2; Rom. 11:28 \x*I have loved you with an everlasting love;
\q2 therefore \x + \xo 31:3 \xt Ps. 36:10 \x*I have continued \x + \xo 31:3 \xt Hos. 11:4\x*my faithfulness to you.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 31:4 \xt ver. 28; ch. 33:7 \x*Again I will build you, and you shall be built,
\q2 O virgin Israel!
\q1 \x + \xo 31:4 \xt Isa. 61:10 \x*Again you shall adorn yourself with tambourines
\q2 and shall go forth in \x + \xo 31:4 \xt ver. 13; Ex. 15:20; Judg. 11:34; 21:21; See 2 Sam. 6:14\x*the dance of the merrymakers.
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 31:5 \xt Isa. 65:21; Amos 9:14\x*Again you shall plant vineyards
\q2 on the mountains of Samaria;
\q1 the planters shall plant
\q2 and shall enjoy the fruit.
\q1
\v 6 For there shall be a day when watchmen will call
\q2 in \x + \xo 31:6 \xt See Josh. 24:33 \x*the hill country of Ephraim:
\q1 \x + \xo 31:6 \xt Isa. 2:3; 27:13\x*‘Arise, and let us go up to Zion,
\q2 to the \nd Lord\nd* our God.’”
\b
\q1
\v 7 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 \x + \xo 31:7 \xt Isa. 12:6; 65:18 \x*“Sing aloud with gladness for Jacob,
\q2 and raise shouts for \x + \xo 31:7 \xt Amos 6:1 \x*the chief of the nations;
\q1 proclaim, give praise, and say,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:7 \xt Ps. 118:25\x*‘O \nd Lord\nd*, save your people,
\q2 the remnant of Israel.’
\q1
\v 8 Behold, I will bring them \x + \xo 31:8 \xt See ch. 3:18 \x*from the north country
\q2 and \x + \xo 31:8 \xt See ch. 23:3 \x*gather them from \x + \xo 31:8 \xt See ch. 6:22 \x*the farthest parts of the earth,
\q1 among them \x + \xo 31:8 \xt Isa. 35:5, 6\x*the blind and the lame,
\q2 the pregnant woman and she who is in labor, together;
\q2 a great company, they shall return here.
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 31:9 \xt ch. 50:4; [Ezra 3:13; 10:1] \x*With weeping they shall come,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:9 \xt ch. 3:21; Zech. 12:10 \x*and with pleas for mercy I will lead them back,
\q1 I will make them \x + \xo 31:9 \xt Isa. 35:6, 7; 49:10; [Ps. 23:2] \x*walk by brooks of water,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:9 \xt Isa. 35:8; 43:19; 49:11 \x*in a straight path in which they shall not stumble,
\q1 for \x + \xo 31:9 \xt Rom. 8:15 \x*I am a father to Israel,
\q2 and Ephraim is \x + \xo 31:9 \xt [Ex. 4:22; Ps. 89:27]\x*my firstborn.
\b
\q1
\v 10 “Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, O nations,
\q2 and declare it in the coastlands far away;
\q1 say, ‘He who scattered Israel will \x + \xo 31:10 \xt [See ver. 8 above] \x*gather him,
\q2 and will keep him \x + \xo 31:10 \xt Isa. 40:11\x*as a shepherd keeps his flock.’
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 31:11 \xt Isa. 43:1; 44:23; 48:20 \x*For the \nd Lord\nd* has ransomed Jacob
\q2 and has redeemed him from \x + \xo 31:11 \xt [Isa. 49:24, 25]\x*hands too strong for him.
\q1
\v 12 They shall come and sing aloud on the height of Zion,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:12 \xt Isa. 2:2; Mic. 4:1 \x*and they shall be radiant \x + \xo 31:12 \xt Hos. 3:5 \x*over the goodness of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 \x + \xo 31:12 \xt [Deut. 12:17] \x*over the grain, the wine, and the oil,
\q2 and over the young of the flock and the herd;
\q1 \x + \xo 31:12 \xt Isa. 58:11 \x*their life shall be like a watered garden,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:12 \xt Isa. 35:10\x*and they shall languish no more.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 31:13 \xt See ver. 4 \x*Then shall the young women rejoice in the dance,
\q2 and the young men and the old shall be merry.
\q1 \x + \xo 31:13 \xt [John 16:20]\x*I will turn their mourning into joy;
\q2 I will comfort them, and give them gladness for sorrow.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 31:14 \xt [ver. 25]\x*I will feast the soul of the priests with abundance,
\q2 and my people shall be satisfied with my goodness,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\b
\q1
\v 15 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 \x + \xo 31:15 \xt Cited Matt. 2:18 \x*“A voice is heard in \x + \xo 31:15 \xt Josh. 18:25 \x*Ramah,
\q2 lamentation and bitter weeping.
\q1 \x + \xo 31:15 \xt [Gen. 35:19, 20; 48:7; 1 Sam. 10:2] \x*Rachel is weeping for her children;
\q2 she refuses to be comforted for her children,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:15 \xt ch. 10:20\x*because they are no more.”
\b
\q1
\v 16 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 “Keep your voice from weeping,
\q2 and your eyes from tears,
\q1 for there is a reward for your work,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and \x + \xo 31:16 \xt Ezra 1:5; Hos. 1:11\x*they shall come back from the land of the enemy.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 31:17 \xt ch. 29:11\x*There is hope for your future,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and your children shall come back to their own country.
\q1
\v 18 I have heard \x + \xo 31:18 \xt [ver. 9] \x*Ephraim grieving,
\q1 ‘You have disciplined me, and I was disciplined,
\q2 like an untrained calf;
\q1 \x + \xo 31:18 \xt Ps. 80:3; Lam. 5:21\x*bring me back that I may be restored,
\q2 for you are the \nd Lord\nd* my God.
\q1
\v 19 For after \x + \xo 31:19 \xt Deut. 30:2 \x*I had turned away, I relented,
\q2 and after I was instructed, \x + \xo 31:19 \xt Ezek. 21:12 \x*I struck my thigh;
\q1 \x + \xo 31:19 \xt [ch. 3:25]\x*I was ashamed, and I was confounded,
\q2 because I bore the disgrace of my youth.’
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 31:20 \xt [See ver. 18 above] \x*Is Ephraim my dear son?
\q2 \x + \xo 31:20 \xt [Prov. 8:30] \x*Is he my darling child?
\q1 For as often as I speak against him,
\q2 I do remember him still.
\q1 \x + \xo 31:20 \xt Song 5:4; Isa. 16:11\x*Therefore my heart\f + \fr 31:20 \ft Hebrew \fq bowels\f* yearns for him;
\q2 I will surely have mercy on him,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 31:21 \xt [Isa. 57:14; 62:10] \x*“Set up road markers for yourself;
\q2 make yourself guideposts;
\q1 \x + \xo 31:21 \xt ch. 50:4, 5\x*consider well the highway,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:21 \xt [Isa. 57:14; 62:10] \x*the road by which you went.
\q1 Return, O virgin Israel,
\q2 return to these your cities.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 31:22 \xt ch. 2:18, 23, 36 \x*How long will you waver,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:22 \xt ch. 49:4\x*O faithless daughter?
\q1 For the \nd Lord\nd* has created a new thing on the earth:
\q2 a woman encircles a man.”
\b
\p
\v 23 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: “Once more they shall use these words in the land of Judah and in its cities, \x + \xo 31:23 \xt See ch. 30:3 \x*when I restore their fortunes:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 31:23 \xt Ps. 122:6, 7 \x*“‘The \nd Lord\nd* bless you, \x + \xo 31:23 \xt ch. 50:7; Isa. 1:26 \x*O habitation of righteousness,
\q2 \x + \xo 31:23 \xt Zech. 8:3\x*O holy hill!’
\b
\m
\v 24 \x + \xo 31:24 \xt ch. 33:13\x*And Judah and all its cities shall dwell there together, and \x + \xo 31:24 \xt ch. 33:13\x*the farmers and those who wander with their flocks.
\v 25 For I will \x + \xo 31:25 \xt Ps. 36:8; [ver. 14]\x*satisfy the weary soul, and every languishing soul I will replenish.”
\p
\v 26 At this I awoke and looked, and my sleep was pleasant to me.
\p
\v 27 \x + \xo 31:27 \xt ch. 9:25 \x*“Behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when \x + \xo 31:27 \xt Ezek. 36:11; Hos. 2:23; Zech. 10:9 \x*I will sow the house of Israel and the house of Judah with \x + \xo 31:27 \xt [Ps. 22:30; Isa. 53:10]\x*the seed of man and the seed of beast.
\v 28 And it shall come to pass that \x + \xo 31:28 \xt ch. 44:27; [ch. 32:42] \x*as I have watched over them \x + \xo 31:28 \xt [ver. 40]; See ch. 1:10 \x*to pluck up and break down, to overthrow, destroy, and bring harm, \x + \xo 31:28 \xt ch. 44:27; [ch. 32:42] \x*so I will watch over them \x + \xo 31:28 \xt See ch. 24:6\x*to build and to plant, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 29 In those days they shall no longer say:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 31:29 \xt Ezek. 18:2, 3; [Lam. 5:7]\x*“‘The fathers have eaten sour grapes,
\q2 and the children’s teeth are set on edge.’
\b
\m
\v 30 \x + \xo 31:30 \xt Ezek. 18:4\x*But everyone shall die for his own iniquity. Each man who eats sour grapes, his teeth shall be set on edge.
\s1 The New Covenant
\p
\v 31 \x + \xo 31:31 \xt ver. 31-34, cited Heb. 8:8-12 \x*“Behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when I will make \x + \xo 31:31 \xt Luke 22:20; 2 Cor. 3:6\x*a new covenant with the house of Israel and the house of Judah,
\v 32 not like the covenant that I made with their fathers on the day when \x + \xo 31:32 \xt [Deut. 1:31] \x*I took them by the hand to bring them out of the land of Egypt, my covenant that they broke, \x + \xo 31:32 \xt See ch. 3:14\x*though I was their husband, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 33 \x + \xo 31:33 \xt ch. 32:40; Ezek. 37:26; Cited Heb. 10:16 \x*For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, declares the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 31:33 \xt ch. 32:40; Ezek. 37:26; Cited Heb. 10:16 \x*I will put my law within them, and I will write it \x + \xo 31:33 \xt Ps. 37:31; 2 Cor. 3:3 \x*on their hearts. \x + \xo 31:33 \xt Hos. 2:23; Zech. 8:8; 13:9; Rev. 21:7; See ch. 30:22\x*And I will be their God, and they shall be my people.
\v 34 And no longer shall each one teach his neighbor and each his brother, saying, ‘Know the \nd Lord\nd*,’ \x + \xo 31:34 \xt Isa. 54:13 \x*for they shall all know me, \x + \xo 31:34 \xt See ch. 6:13 \x*from the least of them to the greatest, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. For \x + \xo 31:34 \xt ch. 33:8; 36:3; 50:20; Mic. 7:18; Acts 10:43; Rom. 11:27; Cited Heb. 10:17 \x*I will forgive their iniquity, and \x + \xo 31:34 \xt Isa. 43:25\x*I will remember their sin no more.”
\b
\q1
\v 35 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 who \x + \xo 31:35 \xt Gen. 1:16 \x*gives the sun for light by day
\q2 and \x + \xo 31:35 \xt See ver. 36 \x*the fixed order of the moon and the stars for light by night,
\q1 who stirs up the sea so that its waves roar—
\q2 \x + \xo 31:35 \xt See ch. 10:16\x*the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts is his name:
\q1
\v 36 \x + \xo 31:36 \xt [Ps. 148:6; Isa. 54:9, 10]; For ver. 36, 37, see ch. 33:20-26\x*“If this fixed order departs
\q2 from before me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 then shall the offspring of Israel cease
\q2 from being a nation before me forever.”
\b
\q1
\v 37 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 “If the heavens above can be measured,
\q2 and the foundations of the earth below can be explored,
\q1 \x + \xo 31:37 \xt Rom. 11:1\x*then I will cast off all the offspring of Israel
\q2 for all that they have done,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\b
\p
\v 38 \x + \xo 31:38 \xt ver. 27, 31 \x*“Behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when the city shall be rebuilt for the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 31:38 \xt Neh. 3:1; 12:39; Zech. 14:10 \x*from the Tower of Hananel to \x + \xo 31:38 \xt 2 Kgs. 14:13\x*the Corner Gate.
\v 39 \x + \xo 31:39 \xt Ezek. 40:3; Zech. 1:16; 2:1, 2; [Rev. 11:1]\x*And the measuring line shall go out farther, straight to the hill Gareb, and shall then turn to Goah.
\v 40 \x + \xo 31:40 \xt [ch. 7:31, 32] \x*The whole valley of the dead bodies and the ashes, and all the fields as far as the \x + \xo 31:40 \xt See 2 Sam. 15:23 \x*brook Kidron, to the corner of \x + \xo 31:40 \xt 2 Chr. 23:15 \x*the Horse Gate toward the east, \x + \xo 31:40 \xt Isa. 52:1; Joel 3:17 \x*shall be sacred to the \nd Lord\nd*. \x + \xo 31:40 \xt [ver. 28]\x*It shall not be plucked up or overthrown anymore forever.”
\c 32
\s1 Jeremiah Buys a Field During the Siege
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 32:1 \xt [ch. 37:5, 11; 39:1, 2; 52:4; 2 Kgs. 25:2] \x*in the tenth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, \x + \xo 32:1 \xt [ch. 52:12; 2 Kgs. 25:8]\x*which was the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar.
\v 2 At that time the army of the king of Babylon was besieging Jerusalem, and Jeremiah the prophet \x + \xo 32:2 \xt Ps. 88:8 \x*was shut up in \x + \xo 32:2 \xt ver. 8, 12; ch. 33:1; 37:21; 38:6, 13; 39:14; [Neh. 3:25]\x*the court of the guard that was in the palace of the king of Judah.
\v 3 For Zedekiah king of Judah had imprisoned him, saying, “Why do you prophesy and say, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 32:3 \xt ver. 25, 36, 43; ch. 21:10; 34:2; 37:17; 38:3\x*Behold, I am giving this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall capture it;
\v 4 \x + \xo 32:4 \xt ch. 34:3 \x*Zedekiah king of Judah shall not escape out of the hand of the Chaldeans, \x + \xo 32:4 \xt [See ver. 3 above]\x*but shall surely be given into the hand of the king of Babylon, and shall speak with him face to face and see him eye to eye.
\v 5 And \x + \xo 32:5 \xt ch. 39:7; 52:11 \x*he shall take Zedekiah to Babylon, and there he shall remain until I visit him, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. \x + \xo 32:5 \xt [ch. 21:4; 33:5]\x*Though you fight against the Chaldeans, you shall not succeed’?”
\p
\v 6 Jeremiah said, “The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to me:
\v 7 Behold, Hanamel the son of Shallum your uncle will come to you and say, \x + \xo 32:7 \xt ver. 25 \x*‘Buy my field that is at \x + \xo 32:7 \xt ch. 1:1; 29:27; Josh. 21:18 \x*Anathoth, \x + \xo 32:7 \xt Lev. 25:25; [Ruth 4:4]\x*for the right of redemption by purchase is yours.’
\v 8 Then Hanamel my cousin came to me in \x + \xo 32:8 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*the court of the guard, in accordance with the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, and said to me, ‘Buy my field that is at \x + \xo 32:8 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*Anathoth in the land of Benjamin, for the right of possession and redemption is yours; buy it for yourself.’ Then I knew that this was the word of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\p
\v 9 “And I bought the field at \x + \xo 32:9 \xt [See ver. 7 above] \x*Anathoth from Hanamel my cousin, and \x + \xo 32:9 \xt Gen. 23:16; Zech. 11:12; [Matt. 26:15]\x*weighed out the money to him, seventeen shekels of silver.
\v 10 \x + \xo 32:10 \xt ver. 44 \x*I signed the deed, \x + \xo 32:10 \xt Esth. 3:12 \x*sealed it, \x + \xo 32:10 \xt ver. 25 \x*got witnesses, and \x + \xo 32:10 \xt [See ver. 9 above]\x*weighed the money on scales.
\v 11 Then I took the sealed deed of purchase, containing the terms and conditions and the open copy.
\v 12 And I gave the deed of purchase to \x + \xo 32:12 \xt ch. 36:4, 8, 10, 14, 26, 32; 43:3, 6; 45:1-3 \x*Baruch the son of Neriah son of Mahseiah, in the presence of Hanamel my cousin, in the presence of \x + \xo 32:12 \xt [Isa. 8:2] \x*the witnesses who signed the deed of purchase, and in the presence of all the Judeans who were sitting in \x + \xo 32:12 \xt [See ver. 2 above]\x*the court of the guard.
\v 13 I charged \x + \xo 32:13 \xt [See ver. 12 above]\x*Baruch in their presence, saying,
\v 14 ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Take these deeds, both this sealed deed of purchase and this open deed, and put them in an earthenware vessel, that they may last for a long time.
\v 15 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Houses and \x + \xo 32:15 \xt ver. 43\x*fields and vineyards shall again be bought in this land.’
\s1 Jeremiah Prays for Understanding
\p
\v 16 “After I had given the deed of purchase to \x + \xo 32:16 \xt See ver. 12\x*Baruch the son of Neriah, I prayed to the \nd Lord\nd*, saying:
\v 17 ‘Ah, Lord \nd God\nd*! It is \x + \xo 32:17 \xt Isa. 37:16 \x*you who have made the heavens and the earth by your great power and by \x + \xo 32:17 \xt See ch. 21:5 \x*your outstretched arm! \x + \xo 32:17 \xt ver. 27; See Gen. 18:14\x*Nothing is too hard for you.
\v 18 \x + \xo 32:18 \xt Ex. 20:6; 34:7; Deut. 5:9, 10 \x*You show steadfast love to thousands, \x + \xo 32:18 \xt Ex. 20:6; 34:7; Deut. 5:9, 10 \x*but you repay the guilt of fathers \x + \xo 32:18 \xt [Ps. 79:12; Isa. 65:6-7] \x*to their children after them, O great and \x + \xo 32:18 \xt Isa. 9:6 \x*mighty God, whose name is the \x + \xo 32:18 \xt See ch. 10:16\x*\nd Lord\nd* of hosts,
\v 19 \x + \xo 32:19 \xt Isa. 28:29 \x*great in counsel and \x + \xo 32:19 \xt [Ps. 66:3, 5] \x*mighty in deed, \x + \xo 32:19 \xt See ch. 16:17 \x*whose eyes are open to all the ways of the children of man, \x + \xo 32:19 \xt See ch. 17:10\x*rewarding each one according to his ways and according to the fruit of his deeds.
\v 20 You have shown \x + \xo 32:20 \xt Ps. 135:9 \x*signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, and to this day in Israel and among all mankind, \x + \xo 32:20 \xt 2 Sam. 7:23; See Neh. 9:10\x*and have made a name for yourself, as at this day.
\v 21 \x + \xo 32:21 \xt Ex. 6:6; Deut. 4:34; 1 Chr. 17:21 \x*You brought your people Israel out of the land of Egypt with signs and wonders, with a strong hand and \x + \xo 32:21 \xt See ch. 21:5\x*outstretched arm, \x + \xo 32:21 \xt Ex. 6:6; Deut. 4:34; 1 Chr. 17:21 \x*and with great terror.
\v 22 And you gave them this land, \x + \xo 32:22 \xt Deut. 26:15; See Ex. 3:8\x*which you swore to their fathers to give them, \x + \xo 32:22 \xt Deut. 26:15; See Ex. 3:8\x*a land flowing with milk and honey.
\v 23 And they entered and took possession of it. \x + \xo 32:23 \xt Neh. 9:26, 27; See ch. 11:8; Dan. 9:10-14\x*But they did not obey your voice or walk in your law. They did nothing of all you commanded them to do. Therefore you have made all this disaster come upon them.
\v 24 Behold, \x + \xo 32:24 \xt ch. 33:4; See ch. 6:6 \x*the siege mounds have come up to the city to take it, and \x + \xo 32:24 \xt ver. 36; See ch. 14:12 \x*because of sword and famine and pestilence \x + \xo 32:24 \xt See ver. 3\x*the city is given into the hands of the Chaldeans who are fighting against it. What you spoke has come to pass, and behold, you see it.
\v 25 Yet you, O Lord \nd God\nd*, have said to me, \x + \xo 32:25 \xt ver. 7 \x*“Buy the field for money \x + \xo 32:25 \xt ver. 10 \x*and get witnesses”—though \x + \xo 32:25 \xt [See ver. 24 above]\x*the city is given into the hands of the Chaldeans.’”
\p
\v 26 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah:
\v 27 “Behold, I am the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 32:27 \xt Num. 16:22 \x*the God of all flesh. \x + \xo 32:27 \xt See Gen. 18:14\x*Is anything too hard for me?
\v 28 Therefore, thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 32:28 \xt ver. 3\x*Behold, I am giving this city into the hands of the Chaldeans and into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and he shall capture it.
\v 29 The Chaldeans who are fighting against this city \x + \xo 32:29 \xt See ch. 21:10 \x*shall come and set this city on fire and burn it, \x + \xo 32:29 \xt See ch. 19:13 \x*with the houses on whose roofs offerings have been made to Baal \x + \xo 32:29 \xt See ch. 19:13 \x*and drink offerings have been poured out to other gods, \x + \xo 32:29 \xt See ch. 7:18\x*to provoke me to anger.
\v 30 For the children of Israel and the children of Judah have done nothing but evil in my sight \x + \xo 32:30 \xt ch. 3:25 \x*from their youth. The children of Israel have done nothing but \x + \xo 32:30 \xt [See ver. 29 above] \x*provoke me to anger \x + \xo 32:30 \xt ch. 25:6, 7\x*by the work of their hands, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 31 This city has aroused my anger and wrath, from the day it was built to this day, \x + \xo 32:31 \xt 2 Kgs. 23:27; 24:3\x*so that I will remove it from my sight
\v 32 because of all the evil of the children of Israel and the children of Judah that they did to provoke me to anger—\x + \xo 32:32 \xt ch. 2:26\x*their kings and their officials, their priests and their prophets, the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
\v 33 \x + \xo 32:33 \xt ch. 2:27; [Ezek. 8:16]; See ch. 7:24 \x*They have turned to me their back and not their face. And though I have taught them \x + \xo 32:33 \xt See ch. 25:3 \x*persistently, they have not listened \x + \xo 32:33 \xt See ch. 5:3\x*to receive instruction.
\v 34 They set up \x + \xo 32:34 \xt See ch. 7:30; 23:11\x*their abominations in the house that is called by my name, to defile it.
\v 35 They built the high places of Baal \x + \xo 32:35 \xt ch. 7:31; See Josh. 18:16 \x*in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, \x + \xo 32:35 \xt Lev. 18:21 \x*to offer up their sons and daughters to Molech, \x + \xo 32:35 \xt ch. 7:31 \x*though I did not command them, nor did it enter into my mind, that they should do \x + \xo 32:35 \xt [See ver. 34 above] \x*this abomination, \x + \xo 32:35 \xt [1 Kgs. 16:19]\x*to cause Judah to sin.
\s1 They Shall Be My People; I Will Be Their God
\p
\v 36 “Now therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, concerning this city of which you say, \x + \xo 32:36 \xt See ver. 3\x*‘It is given into the hand of the king of Babylon by sword, by famine, and by pestilence’:
\v 37 \x + \xo 32:37 \xt See ch. 23:3 \x*Behold, I will gather them from all the countries \x + \xo 32:37 \xt See ch. 8:3 \x*to which I drove them in \x + \xo 32:37 \xt ch. 21:5; Deut. 29:28 \x*my anger and my wrath and in great indignation. I will bring them back to this place, \x + \xo 32:37 \xt ch. 23:6; 33:16; Ezek. 34:25\x*and I will make them dwell in safety.
\v 38 \x + \xo 32:38 \xt See ch. 30:22; 31:33\x*And they shall be my people, and I will be their God.
\v 39 \x + \xo 32:39 \xt Ezek. 11:19, 20 \x*I will give them one heart and one way, that they may fear me forever, \x + \xo 32:39 \xt Deut. 6:24\x*for their own good and the good of their children after them.
\v 40 \x + \xo 32:40 \xt ch. 50:5; Ps. 89:34; Isa. 55:3; Ezek. 16:60 \x*I will make with them an everlasting covenant, that I will not turn away from doing good to them. \x + \xo 32:40 \xt See ch. 31:33\x*And I will put the fear of me in their hearts, that they may not turn from me.
\v 41 \x + \xo 32:41 \xt [Deut. 28:63] \x*I will rejoice in doing them good, \x + \xo 32:41 \xt See ch. 24:6\x*and I will plant them in this land in faithfulness, with all my heart and all my soul.
\p
\v 42 “For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 32:42 \xt [ch. 31:28]\x*Just as I have brought all this great disaster upon this people, so I will bring upon them all the good that I promise them.
\v 43 \x + \xo 32:43 \xt ver. 15 \x*Fields shall be bought in this land \x + \xo 32:43 \xt ch. 33:10 \x*of which you are saying, ‘It is a desolation, without man or beast; \x + \xo 32:43 \xt See ver. 3\x*it is given into the hand of the Chaldeans.’
\v 44 Fields shall be bought for money, and \x + \xo 32:44 \xt ver. 10 \x*deeds shall be signed and \x + \xo 32:44 \xt ver. 10 \x*sealed and \x + \xo 32:44 \xt ver. 10 \x*witnessed, \x + \xo 32:44 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*in the land of Benjamin, \x + \xo 32:44 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*in the places about Jerusalem, \x + \xo 32:44 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*and in the cities of Judah, \x + \xo 32:44 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*in the cities of the hill country, \x + \xo 32:44 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*in the cities of the Shephelah, and in the cities of the Negeb; for \x + \xo 32:44 \xt See ch. 30:3\x*I will restore their fortunes, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\c 33
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Promises Peace
\p \v 1 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah a second time, while he was still \x + \xo 33:1 \xt See ch. 32:2\x*shut up in the court of the guard:
\v 2 “Thus says \x + \xo 33:2 \xt [Isa. 37:26] \x*the \nd Lord\nd* who made the earth,\f + \fr 33:2 \ft Septuagint; Hebrew \fq it\f* the \nd Lord\nd* who formed it to establish it—\x + \xo 33:2 \xt [ch. 16:21; Ex. 6:3; Ps. 83:18; Amos 4:13]\x*the \nd Lord\nd* is his name:
\v 3 \x + \xo 33:3 \xt ch. 29:12; Ps. 91:15 \x*Call to me and I will answer you, \x + \xo 33:3 \xt Isa. 48:6\x*and will tell you great and hidden things that you have not known.
\v 4 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, concerning the houses of this city and the houses of the kings of Judah that were torn down to make a defense against \x + \xo 33:4 \xt ch. 32:24\x*the siege mounds and against the sword:
\v 5 They are coming in \x + \xo 33:5 \xt [ch. 32:5] \x*to fight against the Chaldeans and to fill them\f + \fr 33:5 \ft That is, the torn-down houses\f* with the dead bodies of men whom I shall strike down \x + \xo 33:5 \xt Ezek. 22:20 \x*in my anger and my wrath, \x + \xo 33:5 \xt Deut. 31:17, 18\x*for I have hidden my face from this city because of all their evil.
\v 6 \x + \xo 33:6 \xt ch. 30:17\x*Behold, I will bring to it health and healing, and I will heal them and reveal to them abundance of prosperity and security.
\v 7 \x + \xo 33:7 \xt See ch. 30:3 \x*I will restore the fortunes of Judah and the fortunes of Israel, \x + \xo 33:7 \xt See ch. 24:6 \x*and rebuild them as they were \x + \xo 33:7 \xt Isa. 1:26\x*at first.
\v 8 \x + \xo 33:8 \xt Ezek. 36:25; [Ps. 51:2, 7; Heb. 9:13, 14] \x*I will cleanse them from all the guilt of their sin against me, \x + \xo 33:8 \xt See ch. 31:34\x*and I will forgive all the guilt of their sin and rebellion against me.
\v 9 \x + \xo 33:9 \xt See ch. 13:11 \x*And this city\f + \fr 33:9 \ft Hebrew \fq And it\f* shall be to me a name of joy, a praise and a glory before all the nations of the earth who shall hear of all the good that I do for them. They shall \x + \xo 33:9 \xt [Ps. 130:4; Isa. 60:5]\x*fear and tremble because of all the good and all the prosperity I provide for it.
\p
\v 10 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: In this place \x + \xo 33:10 \xt ch. 32:43\x*of which you say, ‘It is a waste without man or beast,’ in the cities of Judah and the streets of Jerusalem that are desolate, without man or inhabitant or beast, there shall be heard again
\v 11 \x + \xo 33:11 \xt See ch. 7:34 \x*the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, the voices of those who sing, as they bring \x + \xo 33:11 \xt 1 Chr. 16:34; Ps. 106:1; 107:1; Isa. 12:4 \x*thank offerings to the house of the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 33:11 \xt ch. 30:19; Lev. 7:12; Ps. 107:22 \x*“‘Give thanks to the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts,
\q2 for the \nd Lord\nd* is good,
\q2 for his steadfast love endures forever!’
\b
\m \x + \xo 33:11 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*For I will restore the fortunes of the land as at first, says the \nd Lord\nd*.
\p
\v 12 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts: \x + \xo 33:12 \xt [Ezek. 36:11] \x*In this place that is waste, without man or beast, and in all of its cities, there shall again be \x + \xo 33:12 \xt [ch. 31:24; 50:19; Isa. 65:10; Ezek. 34:14, 15] \x*habitations of shepherds \x + \xo 33:12 \xt Song 1:7\x*resting their flocks.
\v 13 \x + \xo 33:13 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*In the cities of the hill country, \x + \xo 33:13 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*in the cities of the Shephelah, \x + \xo 33:13 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*and in the cities of the Negeb, in the land of Benjamin, \x + \xo 33:13 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*the places about Jerusalem, \x + \xo 33:13 \xt See ch. 17:26 \x*and in the cities of Judah, \x + \xo 33:13 \xt [Lev. 27:32] \x*flocks shall again pass under the hands \x + \xo 33:13 \xt [John 10:3]\x*of the one who counts them, says the \nd Lord\nd*.
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd*’s Eternal Covenant with David
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 33:14 \xt For ver. 14-16, see ch. 23:5, 6 \x*“Behold, the days are coming, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, when \x + \xo 33:14 \xt ch. 29:10\x*I will fulfill the promise I made to the house of Israel and the house of Judah.
\v 15 In those days and at that time I will cause a righteous \x + \xo 33:15 \xt ch. 23:5; [Isa. 4:2; 11:1]\x*Branch to spring up for David, and he shall execute justice and righteousness in the land.
\v 16 In those days Judah will be saved, \x + \xo 33:16 \xt ch. 23:6; 32:37 \x*and Jerusalem will dwell securely. And this is the name by which it will be called: \x + \xo 33:16 \xt ch. 23:6\x*‘The \nd Lord\nd* is our righteousness.’
\p
\v 17 “For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 33:17 \xt 2 Sam. 7:16; 1 Kgs. 2:4; Ps. 89:3, 4\x*David shall never lack a man to sit on the throne of the house of Israel,
\v 18 \x + \xo 33:18 \xt [Isa. 66:21]\x*and the Levitical priests shall never lack a man in my presence to offer burnt offerings, to burn grain offerings, and to make sacrifices forever.”
\p
\v 19 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah:
\v 20 \x + \xo 33:20 \xt For ver. 20-26, see ch. 31:36, 37 \x*“Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 33:20 \xt ver. 25; [Isa. 54:9] \x*If you can break my covenant with the day and my covenant with the night, \x + \xo 33:20 \xt Gen. 8:22; Ps. 72:5\x*so that day and night will not come at their appointed time,
\v 21 \x + \xo 33:21 \xt Ps. 89:34\x*then also my covenant with David my servant may be broken, so that he shall not have a son to reign on his throne, and my covenant with the Levitical priests my ministers.
\v 22 As \x + \xo 33:22 \xt Gen. 22:17\x*the host of heaven cannot be numbered and \x + \xo 33:22 \xt Gen. 22:17\x*the sands of the sea cannot be measured, so I will multiply the offspring of David my servant, and the Levitical priests who minister to me.”
\p
\v 23 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah:
\v 24 “Have you not observed that these people are saying, ‘The \nd Lord\nd* has rejected the two clans that he chose’? Thus they have despised my people so that they are no longer a nation in their sight.
\v 25 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 33:25 \xt Ps. 74:16, 17; 104:19\x*If I have not established my covenant with day and night and the fixed order of heaven and earth,
\v 26 then I will reject the offspring of Jacob and David my servant and will not choose one of his offspring to rule over the offspring of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. \x + \xo 33:26 \xt ver. 7, 11; See ch. 30:3\x*For I will restore their fortunes and will have mercy on them.”
\c 34
\s1 Zedekiah to Die in Babylon
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*, when \x + \xo 34:1 \xt ch. 39:1; 52:4; 2 Kgs. 25:1 \x*Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and all his army \x + \xo 34:1 \xt ch. 1:15; [ch. 51:28]\x*and all the kingdoms of the earth under his dominion and all the peoples were fighting against Jerusalem and all of its cities:
\v 2 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel: Go and speak to \x + \xo 34:2 \xt 2 Kgs. 25:2 \x*Zedekiah king of Judah and say to him, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 34:2 \xt See ch. 21:10\x*Behold, I am giving this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall burn it with fire.
\v 3 \x + \xo 34:3 \xt See ch. 32:4\x*You shall not escape from his hand but shall surely be captured and delivered into his hand. \x + \xo 34:3 \xt See ch. 32:4\x*You shall see the king of Babylon eye to eye and speak with him face to face. And you shall go to Babylon.’
\v 4 Yet hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, O Zedekiah king of Judah! \x + \xo 34:4 \xt [ch. 38:17, 20; 39:4, 7]\x*Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning you: \x + \xo 34:4 \xt [ch. 38:17, 20; 39:4, 7]\x*‘You shall not die by the sword.
\v 5 You shall die in peace. \x + \xo 34:5 \xt 1 Sam. 31:12; 2 Chr. 21:19 \x*And as spices were burned for your fathers, the former kings who were before you, so people shall \x + \xo 34:5 \xt 2 Chr. 16:14 \x*burn spices for you \x + \xo 34:5 \xt [ch. 22:18]\x*and lament for you, saying, “Alas, lord!”’ For I have spoken the word, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\p
\v 6 Then Jeremiah the prophet spoke all these words to Zedekiah king of Judah, in Jerusalem,
\v 7 when the army of the king of Babylon was fighting against Jerusalem and against all the cities of Judah that were left, \x + \xo 34:7 \xt Josh. 10:3 \x*Lachish and \x + \xo 34:7 \xt Josh. 10:10; 15:35 \x*Azekah, \x + \xo 34:7 \xt 2 Kgs. 18:13 \x*for these were the only \x + \xo 34:7 \xt ch. 4:5\x*fortified cities of Judah that remained.
\p
\v 8 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*, after King Zedekiah \x + \xo 34:8 \xt ver. 15 \x*had made a covenant with all the people in Jerusalem \x + \xo 34:8 \xt ver. 15, 17; Ex. 21:2; Lev. 25:10; [Isa. 61:1]\x*to make a proclamation of liberty to them,
\v 9 \x + \xo 34:9 \xt See Lev. 25:39-46 \x*that everyone should set free his Hebrew slaves, male and female, \x + \xo 34:9 \xt [Neh. 5:8]\x*so that no one should enslave a Jew, his brother.
\v 10 And they obeyed, all the officials and all the people who had entered into the covenant that everyone would set free his slave, male or female, so that they would not be enslaved again. They obeyed and set them free.
\v 11 But afterward they turned around and took back the male and female slaves \x + \xo 34:11 \xt [See ver. 9 above]\x*they had set free, and brought them into subjection as slaves.
\v 12 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*:
\v 13 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel: I myself made a covenant with your fathers when \x + \xo 34:13 \xt Ex. 20:2\x*I brought them out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery, saying,
\v 14 \x + \xo 34:14 \xt Ex. 21:2; Deut. 15:12 \x*‘At the end of seven years each of you must set free the fellow Hebrew who has been sold to you and has served you six years; \x + \xo 34:14 \xt [See ver. 9 above] \x*you must set him free from your service.’ But \x + \xo 34:14 \xt ch. 7:24, 26; 11:8; 17:23; 25:4; 35:15; 44:5\x*your fathers did not listen to me or incline their ears to me.
\v 15 You recently repented and did what was right in my eyes \x + \xo 34:15 \xt [See ver. 8 above] \x*by proclaiming liberty, each to his neighbor, and \x + \xo 34:15 \xt ver. 8; [2 Kgs. 23:3] \x*you made a covenant before me in the \x + \xo 34:15 \xt See ch. 7:10\x*house that is called by my name,
\v 16 but then you turned around \x + \xo 34:16 \xt Lev. 18:21; 19:12 \x*and profaned my name when each of you took back his male and female slaves, \x + \xo 34:16 \xt ver. 11\x*whom you had set free according to their desire, and you brought them into subjection to be your slaves.
\p
\v 17 “Therefore, thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: You have not obeyed me \x + \xo 34:17 \xt [See ver. 8 above] \x*by proclaiming liberty, every one to his brother and to his neighbor; \x + \xo 34:17 \xt [Matt. 7:2; Gal. 6:7; James 2:13] \x*behold, I proclaim to you liberty \x + \xo 34:17 \xt See ch. 14:12 \x*to the sword, to pestilence, and to famine, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. \x + \xo 34:17 \xt See ch. 15:4\x*I will make you a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth.
\v 18 And the men who transgressed my covenant and did not keep the terms of \x + \xo 34:18 \xt [See ver. 15 above] \x*the covenant that they made before me, I will make them like\f + \fr 34:18 \ft Hebrew lacks \fq them like\f* \x + \xo 34:18 \xt [Gen. 15:10]\x*the calf that they cut in two and passed between its parts—
\v 19 the officials of Judah, the officials of Jerusalem, \x + \xo 34:19 \xt ch. 29:2\x*the eunuchs, the priests, and all the people of the land who passed between the parts of the calf.
\v 20 And I will give them into the hand of their enemies \x + \xo 34:20 \xt See ch. 22:25 \x*and into the hand of those who seek their lives. \x + \xo 34:20 \xt See ch. 7:33\x*Their dead bodies shall be food for the birds of the air and the beasts of the earth.
\v 21 And \x + \xo 34:21 \xt [ver. 2, 4, 8] \x*Zedekiah king of Judah and his officials I will give into the hand of their enemies and into the hand of those who seek their lives, into the hand of the army of the king of Babylon \x + \xo 34:21 \xt ch. 37:5, 11\x*which has withdrawn from you.
\v 22 Behold, \x + \xo 34:22 \xt Isa. 10:6 \x*I will command, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and will \x + \xo 34:22 \xt ch. 37:8; 38:3 \x*bring them back to this city. \x + \xo 34:22 \xt ch. 37:8; 38:3 \x*And they will fight against it and take it and burn it with fire. \x + \xo 34:22 \xt ch. 9:11 \x*I will make the cities of Judah a desolation \x + \xo 34:22 \xt See ch. 4:7\x*without inhabitant.”
\c 35
\s1 The Obedience of the Rechabites
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd* in the days of \x + \xo 35:1 \xt ch. 25:1\x*Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah:
\v 2 “Go to the house of the \x + \xo 35:2 \xt 1 Chr. 2:55 \x*Rechabites and speak with them and bring them to the house of the \nd Lord\nd*, into one of \x + \xo 35:2 \xt 1 Kgs. 6:5, 6; 1 Chr. 9:26, 33\x*the chambers; then offer them wine to drink.”
\v 3 So I took Jaazaniah the son of Jeremiah, son of Habazziniah and his brothers and all his sons and the whole house of the Rechabites.
\v 4 I brought them to the house of the \nd Lord\nd* into \x + \xo 35:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*the chamber of the sons of Hanan the son of Igdaliah, \x + \xo 35:4 \xt [Deut. 33:1] \x*the man of God, which was near \x + \xo 35:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*the chamber of the officials, above \x + \xo 35:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*the chamber of \x + \xo 35:4 \xt ch. 21:1; 29:25; 37:3 \x*Maaseiah the son of Shallum, \x + \xo 35:4 \xt 2 Kgs. 12:9; 25:18\x*keeper of the threshold.
\v 5 Then I set before the Rechabites pitchers full of wine, and cups, and I said to them, “Drink wine.”
\v 6 But they answered, “We will drink no wine, for \x + \xo 35:6 \xt 2 Kgs. 10:15, 23\x*Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father, commanded us, ‘You shall not drink wine, neither you nor your sons forever.
\v 7 You shall not build a house; you shall not sow seed; you shall not plant or have a vineyard; but you shall live in tents all your days, \x + \xo 35:7 \xt [Ex. 20:12; Eph. 6:2, 3]\x*that you may live many days in the land where you sojourn.’
\v 8 We have obeyed the voice of Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father, in all that he commanded us, to drink no wine all our days, ourselves, our wives, our sons, or our daughters,
\v 9 and not to build houses to dwell in. We have no vineyard or field or seed,
\v 10 but we have lived in tents and have obeyed and done all that Jonadab our father commanded us.
\v 11 But \x + \xo 35:11 \xt ch. 46:2; 2 Kgs. 24:1; [ver. 1] \x*when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against the land, we said, ‘Come, and let us go to Jerusalem for fear of \x + \xo 35:11 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:2 \x*the army of the Chaldeans and \x + \xo 35:11 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:2 \x*the army of the Syrians.’ \x + \xo 35:11 \xt [ver. 7]\x*So we are living in Jerusalem.”
\p
\v 12 Then the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah:
\v 13 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Go and say to the people of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, \x + \xo 35:13 \xt See ch. 5:3\x*Will you not receive instruction and listen to my words? declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 14 The command that Jonadab the son of Rechab gave to his sons, to drink no wine, has been kept, and they drink none to this day, for they have obeyed their father’s command. I have spoken to you \x + \xo 35:14 \xt See ch. 25:3\x*persistently, but you have not listened to me.
\v 15 I have sent to you all my servants the prophets, sending them \x + \xo 35:15 \xt [See ver. 14 above] \x*persistently, saying, \x + \xo 35:15 \xt 2 Kgs. 17:13; See ch. 18:11 \x*‘Turn now every one of you from his evil way, and amend your deeds, and \x + \xo 35:15 \xt See ch. 7:6 \x*do not go after other gods to serve them, and then you shall dwell in the land that I gave to you and your fathers.’ \x + \xo 35:15 \xt See ch. 34:14\x*But you did not incline your ear or listen to me.
\v 16 The sons of Jonadab the son of Rechab have kept the command that their father gave them, but this people has not obeyed me.
\v 17 Therefore, thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, I am bringing upon Judah and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem all the disaster that I have pronounced against them, \x + \xo 35:17 \xt [Isa. 50:2]\x*because I have spoken to them and they have not listened, \x + \xo 35:17 \xt [Isa. 50:2]\x*I have called to them and they have not answered.”
\p
\v 18 But to the house of the Rechabites Jeremiah said, “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Because you have obeyed the command of Jonadab your father and kept all his precepts and done all that he commanded you,
\v 19 therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Jonadab the son of Rechab shall never lack a man \x + \xo 35:19 \xt See ch. 15:1\x*to stand before me.”
\c 36
\s1 Jehoiakim Burns Jeremiah’s Scroll
\p \v 1 In the \x + \xo 36:1 \xt ch. 25:1; 45:1; [ver. 9]\x*fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd*:
\v 2 “Take \x + \xo 36:2 \xt Ezra 6:2; Ps. 40:7; Ezek. 2:9; Zech. 5:1, 2 \x*a scroll and \x + \xo 36:2 \xt ch. 30:2; [ch. 51:60] \x*write on it all the words that I have spoken to you against Israel and \x + \xo 36:2 \xt ch. 25:2 \x*Judah \x + \xo 36:2 \xt See ch. 25:15-26; 46–51 \x*and all the nations, \x + \xo 36:2 \xt ch. 1:2; 25:3\x*from the day I spoke to you, from the days of Josiah until today.
\v 3 \x + \xo 36:3 \xt ch. 26:3; Ezek. 12:3; Zeph. 2:3; [Amos 5:15] \x*It may be that the house of Judah will hear all the disaster that I intend to do to them, \x + \xo 36:3 \xt [ch. 18:8] \x*so that every one may turn from his evil way, and \x + \xo 36:3 \xt See ch. 31:34\x*that I may forgive their iniquity and their sin.”
\p
\v 4 Then Jeremiah called \x + \xo 36:4 \xt See ch. 32:12 \x*Baruch the son of Neriah, and \x + \xo 36:4 \xt See ch. 32:12 \x*Baruch wrote on \x + \xo 36:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above]\x*a scroll at the dictation of Jeremiah all the words of the \nd Lord\nd* that he had spoken to him.
\v 5 And Jeremiah ordered \x + \xo 36:5 \xt [See ver. 4 above] \x*Baruch, saying, \x + \xo 36:5 \xt ch. 32:2; 33:1; 39:15\x*“I am banned from going to the house of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\v 6 so you are to go, and \x + \xo 36:6 \xt [ver. 9]\x*on a day of fasting in the hearing of all the people in the \nd Lord\nd*’s house you shall read the words of the \nd Lord\nd* from the scroll that you have written at my dictation. You shall read them also in the hearing of all the men of Judah who come out of their cities.
\v 7 \x + \xo 36:7 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*It may be that their plea for mercy will come before the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 36:7 \xt [See ver. 3 above]\x*and that every one will turn from his evil way, for great is the anger and wrath that the \nd Lord\nd* has pronounced against this people.”
\v 8 And Baruch the son of Neriah did all that Jeremiah the prophet ordered him about reading from the scroll the words of the \nd Lord\nd* in the \nd Lord\nd*’s house.
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 36:9 \xt [ver. 1] \x*In the fifth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, \x + \xo 36:9 \xt ver. 22 \x*in the ninth month, all the people in Jerusalem and all the people who came from the cities of Judah to Jerusalem \x + \xo 36:9 \xt [2 Chr. 20:3]\x*proclaimed a fast before the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 10 Then, in the hearing of all the people, Baruch read the words of Jeremiah from the scroll, in the house of the \nd Lord\nd*, in \x + \xo 36:10 \xt [ch. 35:2]\x*the chamber of Gemariah the son of Shaphan the secretary, which was in the upper court, at the entry of the New Gate of the \nd Lord\nd*’s house.
\p
\v 11 When Micaiah the son of Gemariah, son of \x + \xo 36:11 \xt ch. 26:24; 40:5; 2 Chr. 34:8, 15, 18\x*Shaphan, heard all the words of the \nd Lord\nd* from the scroll,
\v 12 he went down to the king’s house, into the secretary’s chamber, and \x + \xo 36:12 \xt ch. 26:10 \x*all the officials were sitting there: \x + \xo 36:12 \xt ver. 20; ch. 41:1; 2 Kgs. 25:25 \x*Elishama the secretary, \x + \xo 36:12 \xt ver. 25 \x*Delaiah the son of Shemaiah, \x + \xo 36:12 \xt ver. 25 \x*Elnathan \x + \xo 36:12 \xt ch. 26:22\x*the son of Achbor, \x + \xo 36:12 \xt ver. 25 \x*Gemariah the son of \x + \xo 36:12 \xt ch. 26:22\x*Shaphan, Zedekiah the son of Hananiah, and all the officials.
\v 13 And Micaiah told them all the words that he had heard, when Baruch read the scroll in the hearing of the people.
\v 14 Then all the officials sent Jehudi the son of Nethaniah, son of \x + \xo 36:14 \xt ver. 26; ch. 37:3, 13; 38:1\x*Shelemiah, son of Cushi, to say to Baruch, “Take in your hand the scroll that you read in the hearing of the people, and come.” So Baruch the son of Neriah took the scroll in his hand and came to them.
\v 15 And they said to him, “Sit down and read it.” So Baruch read it to them.
\v 16 When they heard all the words, they turned one to another in fear. And they said to Baruch, \x + \xo 36:16 \xt ver. 20\x*“We must report all these words to the king.”
\v 17 Then they asked Baruch, “Tell us, please, how did you write all these words? Was it at his dictation?”
\v 18 Baruch answered them, “He dictated all these words to me, \x + \xo 36:18 \xt ver. 32; [Rom. 16:22]\x*while I wrote them with ink on the scroll.”
\v 19 Then the officials said to Baruch, “Go and hide, you and Jeremiah, and let no one know where you are.”
\p
\v 20 So they went into the court to the king, having put the scroll in \x + \xo 36:20 \xt ver. 12\x*the chamber of Elishama the secretary, and they reported all the words to the king.
\v 21 Then the king sent Jehudi to get the scroll, and he took it from the chamber of Elishama the secretary. And Jehudi read it to the king and all the officials who stood beside the king.
\v 22 It was \x + \xo 36:22 \xt ver. 9; [John 10:22] \x*the ninth month, and the king was sitting in \x + \xo 36:22 \xt Amos 3:15\x*the winter house, and there was a fire burning in the fire pot before him.
\v 23 As Jehudi read three or four columns, the king would cut them off with a knife and throw them into the fire in the fire pot, until the entire scroll was consumed in the fire that was in the fire pot.
\v 24 Yet \x + \xo 36:24 \xt [ver. 16] \x*neither the king nor any of his servants who heard all these words was afraid, \x + \xo 36:24 \xt See Josh. 7:6\x*nor did they tear their garments.
\v 25 Even when \x + \xo 36:25 \xt ver. 12 \x*Elnathan and Delaiah and Gemariah \x + \xo 36:25 \xt [Isa. 59:16]\x*urged the king not to burn the scroll, he would not listen to them.
\v 26 And the king commanded Jerahmeel the \x + \xo 36:26 \xt [1 Kgs. 22:26; Zeph. 1:8] \x*king’s son and Seraiah the son of Azriel and \x + \xo 36:26 \xt ver. 14 \x*Shelemiah the son of Abdeel to seize \x + \xo 36:26 \xt See ch. 45:1-3\x*Baruch the secretary and Jeremiah the prophet, but the \nd Lord\nd* hid them.
\p
\v 27 Now after the king had burned the scroll with the words that Baruch wrote at Jeremiah’s dictation, the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah:
\v 28 “Take another scroll and write on it all the former words that were in the first scroll, which Jehoiakim the king of Judah has burned.
\v 29 And concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah you shall say, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, You have burned this scroll, saying, \x + \xo 36:29 \xt See ch. 26:9\x*“Why have you written in it that the king of Babylon will certainly come and destroy this land, and will cut off from it man and beast?”
\v 30 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah: \x + \xo 36:30 \xt [ch. 22:30] \x*He shall have none \x + \xo 36:30 \xt [ch. 22:2, 4] \x*to sit on the throne of David, \x + \xo 36:30 \xt [ch. 22:19]\x*and his dead body shall be cast out to the heat by day and the frost by night.
\v 31 \x + \xo 36:31 \xt [ch. 1:16]\x*And I will punish him and his offspring and his servants for their iniquity. I will bring upon them and upon the inhabitants of Jerusalem and upon the people of Judah all the disaster that I have pronounced against them, but they would not hear.’”
\p
\v 32 Then Jeremiah took another scroll and gave it to \x + \xo 36:32 \xt See ver. 4 \x*Baruch the scribe, the son of Neriah, who \x + \xo 36:32 \xt ver. 18\x*wrote on it at the dictation of Jeremiah all the words of the scroll that Jehoiakim king of Judah had burned in the fire. And many similar words were added to them.
\c 37
\s1 Jeremiah Warns Zedekiah
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 37:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:17; 2 Chr. 36:10 \x*Zedekiah the son of Josiah, \x + \xo 37:1 \xt [Ezek. 17:13] \x*whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon made king in the land of Judah, reigned instead of \x + \xo 37:1 \xt ch. 22:24\x*Coniah the son of Jehoiakim.
\v 2 \x + \xo 37:2 \xt See 2 Chr. 36:12-14\x*But neither he nor his servants nor the people of the land listened to the words of the \nd Lord\nd* that he spoke through Jeremiah the prophet.
\p
\v 3 King Zedekiah sent \x + \xo 37:3 \xt [ch. 38:1] \x*Jehucal the son of \x + \xo 37:3 \xt ver. 13; ch. 38:1 \x*Shelemiah, and \x + \xo 37:3 \xt See ch. 21:1 \x*Zephaniah the priest, the son of \x + \xo 37:3 \xt See ch. 35:4 \x*Maaseiah, to Jeremiah the prophet, saying, “Please \x + \xo 37:3 \xt [ch. 21:2]\x*pray for us to the \nd Lord\nd* our God.”
\v 4 \x + \xo 37:4 \xt [Num. 27:17] \x*Now Jeremiah was still going in and out among the people, \x + \xo 37:4 \xt [ch. 32:2; 33:1]\x*for he had not yet been put in prison.
\v 5 \x + \xo 37:5 \xt [Ezek. 17:15] \x*The army of Pharaoh had come out of Egypt. And when \x + \xo 37:5 \xt ch. 32:2 \x*the Chaldeans who were besieging Jerusalem heard news about them, \x + \xo 37:5 \xt ver. 11; ch. 34:21\x*they withdrew from Jerusalem.
\p
\v 6 Then the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah the prophet:
\v 7 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, God of Israel: Thus shall you say to the king of Judah who \x + \xo 37:7 \xt [ch. 21:2] \x*sent you to me to inquire of me, ‘Behold, \x + \xo 37:7 \xt [Ezek. 29:2, 6] \x*Pharaoh’s army that came to help you is about to \x + \xo 37:7 \xt [ch. 46:17; 2 Kgs. 24:7; Lam. 4:17]\x*return to Egypt, to its own land.
\v 8 And \x + \xo 37:8 \xt ch. 34:22\x*the Chaldeans shall come back and fight against this city. \x + \xo 37:8 \xt ch. 34:22\x*They shall capture it and burn it with fire.
\v 9 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, Do not deceive yourselves, saying, “The Chaldeans will surely go away from us,” for they will not go away.
\v 10 \x + \xo 37:10 \xt [ch. 21:4] \x*For even if you should defeat the whole army of Chaldeans who are fighting against you, and there remained of them only wounded men, every man in his tent, they would rise up and \x + \xo 37:10 \xt [See ver. 8 above]\x*burn this city with fire.’”
\s1 Jeremiah Imprisoned
\p
\v 11 Now when \x + \xo 37:11 \xt ver. 5\x*the Chaldean army had withdrawn from Jerusalem at the approach of Pharaoh’s army,
\v 12 Jeremiah set out from Jerusalem to go to \x + \xo 37:12 \xt ch. 1:1; 32:8 \x*the land of Benjamin \x + \xo 37:12 \xt [ch. 32:9] \x*to receive his portion there \x + \xo 37:12 \xt ver. 4; ch. 39:14\x*among the people.
\v 13 When he was at \x + \xo 37:13 \xt ch. 38:7; Zech. 14:10 \x*the Benjamin Gate, a sentry there named Irijah the son of \x + \xo 37:13 \xt ver. 3; ch. 38:1 \x*Shelemiah, son of Hananiah, seized Jeremiah the prophet, saying, \x + \xo 37:13 \xt [ch. 21:9; 38:19; 39:9; 52:15]\x*“You are deserting to the Chaldeans.”
\v 14 And Jeremiah said, “It is a lie; I am not deserting to the Chaldeans.” But Irijah would not listen to him, and seized Jeremiah and brought him to \x + \xo 37:14 \xt ch. 36:12\x*the officials.
\v 15 And the officials were enraged at Jeremiah, and they beat him \x + \xo 37:15 \xt [Heb. 11:36]\x*and imprisoned him in the house of Jonathan the secretary, for it had been made a prison.
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 37:16 \xt See ch. 38:6-14\x*When Jeremiah had come to the dungeon cells and remained there many days,
\v 17 King Zedekiah sent for him and received him. The king questioned him \x + \xo 37:17 \xt ch. 38:16 \x*secretly in his house and said, “Is there any word from the \nd Lord\nd*?” Jeremiah said, “There is.” Then he said, \x + \xo 37:17 \xt See ch. 21:7\x*“You shall be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon.”
\v 18 Jeremiah also said to King Zedekiah, “What wrong have I done to you or your servants or this people, \x + \xo 37:18 \xt [See ver. 15 above]\x*that you have put me in prison?
\v 19 \x + \xo 37:19 \xt [ch. 28:2, 11, 17]\x*Where are your prophets who prophesied to you, saying, ‘The king of Babylon will not come against you and against this land’?
\v 20 Now hear, please, O my lord the king: \x + \xo 37:20 \xt [ch. 38:26] \x*let my humble plea come before you and \x + \xo 37:20 \xt [ch. 38:28]\x*do not send me back to the house of Jonathan the secretary, lest I die there.”
\v 21 So King Zedekiah gave orders, and they committed Jeremiah to \x + \xo 37:21 \xt See ch. 32:2 \x*the court of the guard. And a loaf of bread was given him daily from the bakers’ street, \x + \xo 37:21 \xt ch. 38:9; 52:6; Ezek. 4:10, 16\x*until all the bread of the city was gone. So Jeremiah remained in \x + \xo 37:21 \xt See ch. 32:2 \x*the court of the guard.
\c 38
\s1 Jeremiah Cast into the Cistern
\p \v 1 Now Shephatiah the son of Mattan, Gedaliah the son of Pashhur, \x + \xo 38:1 \xt [ch. 37:3] \x*Jucal the son of Shelemiah, and \x + \xo 38:1 \xt See ch. 20:1\x*Pashhur the son of Malchiah heard the words that Jeremiah was saying to all the people,
\v 2 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 38:2 \xt ch. 21:9; [ver. 17, 18]\x*He who stays in this city shall die by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence, \x + \xo 38:2 \xt ch. 21:9; [ver. 17, 18]\x*but he who goes out to the Chaldeans shall live. He shall have his life as a prize of war, and live.
\v 3 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 38:3 \xt See ch. 32:3\x*This city shall surely be given into the hand of the army of the king of Babylon and be taken.”
\v 4 Then the officials said to the king, \x + \xo 38:4 \xt ch. 26:11 \x*“Let this man be put to death, \x + \xo 38:4 \xt See ch. 6:24 \x*for he is weakening the hands of the soldiers who are left in this city, and the hands of all the people, by speaking such words to them. For this man is not seeking \x + \xo 38:4 \xt [ch. 33:9]\x*the welfare of this people, but their harm.”
\v 5 King Zedekiah said, “Behold, he is in your hands, \x + \xo 38:5 \xt See ver. 24-28\x*for the king can do nothing against you.”
\v 6 So they took Jeremiah \x + \xo 38:6 \xt ch. 37:16 \x*and cast him into the cistern of Malchiah, the king’s son, which was in \x + \xo 38:6 \xt See ch. 32:2 \x*the court of the guard, letting Jeremiah down \x + \xo 38:6 \xt ver. 11, 13 \x*by ropes. \x + \xo 38:6 \xt [Gen. 37:24; Zech. 9:11] \x*And there was no water in the cistern, but only mud, and \x + \xo 38:6 \xt [Ps. 69:14]\x*Jeremiah sank in the mud.
\s1 Jeremiah Rescued from the Cistern
\p
\v 7 When \x + \xo 38:7 \xt ch. 39:16 \x*Ebed-melech \x + \xo 38:7 \xt [Acts 8:27] \x*the Ethiopian, \x + \xo 38:7 \xt ch. 29:2; Isa. 56:3, 4 \x*a eunuch who was in the king’s house, heard that they had put Jeremiah into the cistern—the king was sitting \x + \xo 38:7 \xt See ch. 37:13\x*in the Benjamin Gate—
\v 8 \x + \xo 38:8 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*Ebed-melech went from the king’s house and said to the king,
\v 9 “My lord the king, these men have done evil in all that they did to Jeremiah the prophet by casting him into the cistern, and he will die there of \x + \xo 38:9 \xt ch. 11:22; [ch. 14:16, 18; 19:9] \x*hunger, \x + \xo 38:9 \xt [ch. 37:21]\x*for there is no bread left in the city.”
\v 10 Then the king commanded \x + \xo 38:10 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, “Take thirty men with you from here, and lift Jeremiah the prophet out of the cistern before he dies.”
\v 11 So \x + \xo 38:11 \xt [See ver. 7 above] \x*Ebed-melech took the men with him and went to the house of the king, to a wardrobe in the storehouse, and took from there old rags and worn-out clothes, which he let down to Jeremiah in the cistern \x + \xo 38:11 \xt ver. 6\x*by ropes.
\v 12 Then \x + \xo 38:12 \xt [See ver. 7 above] \x*Ebed-melech the Ethiopian said to Jeremiah, “Put the rags and clothes between your armpits and \x + \xo 38:12 \xt [See ver. 11 above]\x*the ropes.” Jeremiah did so.
\v 13 Then they drew Jeremiah up with \x + \xo 38:13 \xt [See ver. 11 above] \x*ropes and lifted him out of the cistern. And Jeremiah remained in the \x + \xo 38:13 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*court of the guard.
\s1 Jeremiah Warns Zedekiah Again
\p
\v 14 King Zedekiah sent for Jeremiah the prophet and received him at the third entrance of the temple of the \nd Lord\nd*. The king said to Jeremiah, “I will ask you a question; hide nothing from me.”
\v 15 Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, “If I tell you, will you not surely put me to death? And if I give you counsel, you will not listen to me.”
\v 16 Then King Zedekiah swore \x + \xo 38:16 \xt ch. 37:17 \x*secretly to Jeremiah, \x + \xo 38:16 \xt See Ruth 3:13 \x*“As the \nd Lord\nd* lives, \x + \xo 38:16 \xt [Isa. 57:16] \x*who made our souls, I will not put you to death or deliver you into the hand of \x + \xo 38:16 \xt See ver. 1-9\x*these men who seek your life.”
\p
\v 17 Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 38:17 \xt ver. 2, 21; [ch. 27:12, 13; 2 Kgs. 24:12] \x*If you will surrender to \x + \xo 38:17 \xt ch. 39:3 \x*the officials of the king of Babylon, \x + \xo 38:17 \xt [ch. 34:4, 5]\x*then your life shall be spared, and this city shall not be burned with fire, and you and your house shall live.
\v 18 But if you do not surrender to \x + \xo 38:18 \xt [See ver. 17 above] \x*the officials of the king of Babylon, \x + \xo 38:18 \xt See ch. 21:10\x*then this city shall be given into the hand of the Chaldeans, \x + \xo 38:18 \xt See ch. 21:10\x*and they shall burn it with fire, and you shall not escape from their hand.”
\v 19 King Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, “I am afraid of the Judeans \x + \xo 38:19 \xt See ch. 37:13\x*who have deserted to the Chaldeans, lest I be handed over to them and they deal cruelly with me.”
\v 20 Jeremiah said, “You shall not be given to them. Obey now the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* in what I say to you, \x + \xo 38:20 \xt ch. 40:9\x*and it shall be well with you, and your life shall be spared.
\v 21 But if you refuse to \x + \xo 38:21 \xt [See ver. 17 above]\x*surrender, this is the vision which the \nd Lord\nd* has shown to me:
\v 22 Behold, all the women left in the house of the king of Judah were being led out to the officials of the king of Babylon and were saying,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 38:22 \xt See ch. 20:10\x*“‘Your trusted friends have deceived you
\q2 and prevailed against you;
\q1 now that your feet are sunk in the mud,
\q2 they turn away from you.’
\b
\m
\v 23 All your wives and \x + \xo 38:23 \xt ch. 39:6; 41:10; 43:6\x*your sons shall be led out to the Chaldeans, and you yourself shall not escape from their hand, but shall be seized by the king of Babylon, and this city shall be burned with fire.”
\p
\v 24 Then Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, “Let no one know of these words, and you shall not die.
\v 25 If \x + \xo 38:25 \xt [ver. 5]\x*the officials hear that I have spoken with you and come to you and say to you, ‘Tell us what you said to the king and what the king said to you; hide nothing from us and we will not put you to death,’
\v 26 then you shall say to them, \x + \xo 38:26 \xt [ch. 37:20]\x*‘I made a humble plea to the king that he would not send me back to the house of Jonathan to die there.’”
\v 27 Then all the officials came to Jeremiah and asked him, and he answered them as the king had instructed him. So they stopped speaking with him, for the conversation had not been overheard.
\v 28 And Jeremiah remained \x + \xo 38:28 \xt See ch. 32:2\x*in the court of the guard until the day that Jerusalem was taken.
\c 39
\s1 The Fall of Jerusalem
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 39:1 \xt For ver. 1-10, see ch. 52:4-16; 2 Kgs. 25:1-12\x*In the ninth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and all his army came against Jerusalem and besieged it.
\v 2 In the eleventh year of Zedekiah, in the fourth month, on the ninth day of the month, a breach was made in the city.
\v 3 Then all \x + \xo 39:3 \xt ch. 38:17, 18, 22 \x*the officials of the king of Babylon came \x + \xo 39:3 \xt [ch. 1:15] \x*and sat in the middle gate: Nergal-sar-ezer of Samgar, Nebu-sar-sekim \x + \xo 39:3 \xt ver. 13; 2 Kgs. 18:17\x*the Rab-saris, Nergal-sar-ezer the Rab-mag, with all the rest of the officers of the king of Babylon.
\v 4 When Zedekiah king of Judah and all the soldiers saw them, they fled, going out of the city at night by way of the king’s garden through the gate between the two walls; and they went toward \x + \xo 39:4 \xt See Deut. 1:1\x*the Arabah.
\v 5 But the army of the Chaldeans pursued them and overtook Zedekiah in \x + \xo 39:5 \xt Josh. 5:10 \x*the plains of Jericho. And when they had taken him, they brought him up to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, at \x + \xo 39:5 \xt See 2 Kgs. 23:33 \x*Riblah, in the land of Hamath; \x + \xo 39:5 \xt [Ezek. 17:15]\x*and he passed sentence on him.
\v 6 The king of Babylon \x + \xo 39:6 \xt ch. 52:10 \x*slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah at \x + \xo 39:6 \xt [See ver. 5 above]\x*Riblah before his eyes, and the king of Babylon \x + \xo 39:6 \xt ch. 52:10 \x*slaughtered all the nobles of Judah.
\v 7 \x + \xo 39:7 \xt [ch. 32:4; Ezek. 12:13]\x*He put out the eyes of Zedekiah and bound him in chains to take him to Babylon.
\v 8 \x + \xo 39:8 \xt See ch. 21:10 \x*The Chaldeans burned the king’s house and the house of the people, \x + \xo 39:8 \xt Neh. 1:3; [Ps. 80:12; Isa. 5:5]\x*and broke down the walls of Jerusalem.
\v 9 Then \x + \xo 39:9 \xt ch. 40:1; 52:12; 2 Kgs. 25:8 \x*Nebuzaradan, the \x + \xo 39:9 \xt Gen. 37:36 \x*captain of the guard, carried into exile to Babylon the rest of the people who were left in the city, \x + \xo 39:9 \xt See ch. 37:13\x*those who had deserted to him, and the people who remained.
\v 10 Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, \x + \xo 39:10 \xt ch. 40:7; 2 Kgs. 25:12\x*left in the land of Judah some of the poor people who owned nothing, and gave them vineyards and fields at the same time.
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Delivers Jeremiah
\p
\v 11 Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon gave command concerning Jeremiah through Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, saying,
\v 12 \x + \xo 39:12 \xt ch. 40:4\x*“Take him, look after him well, and do him no harm, but deal with him as he tells you.”
\v 13 So \x + \xo 39:13 \xt [ver. 3]\x*Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard, Nebushazban the Rab-saris, Nergal-sar-ezer the Rab-mag, \x + \xo 39:13 \xt [ver. 3]\x*and all the chief officers of the king of Babylon
\v 14 sent and took Jeremiah from \x + \xo 39:14 \xt ch. 38:28; See ch. 32:2 \x*the court of the guard. They entrusted him to \x + \xo 39:14 \xt ch. 43:6; See ch. 40:5-9, 11-16; 41:1-4, 6; 2 Kgs. 25:22-25 \x*Gedaliah the son of \x + \xo 39:14 \xt 2 Kgs. 22:12 \x*Ahikam, son of \x + \xo 39:14 \xt 2 Kgs. 22:3 \x*Shaphan, that he should take him home. So \x + \xo 39:14 \xt ch. 37:12\x*he lived among the people.
\p
\v 15 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah \x + \xo 39:15 \xt ch. 36:5; 38:13\x*while he was shut up in the court of the guard:
\v 16 “Go, and say to \x + \xo 39:16 \xt See ch. 38:7 \x*Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 39:16 \xt Dan. 9:12 \x*Behold, I will fulfill my words against this city for harm and \x + \xo 39:16 \xt ch. 21:10; [ch. 14:11]\x*not for good, and they shall be accomplished before you on that day.
\v 17 But I will deliver you on that day, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, and you shall not be given into the hand of the men \x + \xo 39:17 \xt ch. 22:25\x*of whom you are afraid.
\v 18 For I will surely save you, and you shall not fall by the sword, but you shall have your \x + \xo 39:18 \xt ch. 21:9; 45:5 \x*life as a prize of war, \x + \xo 39:18 \xt Ps. 25:2; 37:40\x*because you have put your trust in me, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.’”
\c 40
\s1 Jeremiah Remains in Judah
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah from the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 40:1 \xt [ch. 39:14] \x*after Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had let him go from \x + \xo 40:1 \xt Josh. 18:25 \x*Ramah, when he took him \x + \xo 40:1 \xt [Ps. 149:8]\x*bound in chains along with all the captives of Jerusalem and Judah who were being exiled to Babylon.
\v 2 The captain of the guard took Jeremiah and said to him, \x + \xo 40:2 \xt [Deut. 29:24, 28]\x*“The \nd Lord\nd* your God pronounced this disaster against this place.
\v 3 The \nd Lord\nd* has brought it about, and has done as he said. \x + \xo 40:3 \xt ch. 44:3, 23; Deut. 29:25; See Dan. 9:10-12\x*Because you sinned against the \nd Lord\nd* and did not obey his voice, this thing has come upon you.
\v 4 Now, behold, I release you today from \x + \xo 40:4 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*the chains on your hands. \x + \xo 40:4 \xt [ch. 39:12] \x*If it seems good to you to come with me to Babylon, come, and I will look after you well, \x + \xo 40:4 \xt [ch. 39:12] \x*but if it seems wrong to you to come with me to Babylon, do not come. \x + \xo 40:4 \xt [Gen. 20:15]\x*See, the whole land is before you; go wherever you think it good and right to go.
\v 5 If you remain,\f + \fr 40:5 \ft Syriac; the meaning of the Hebrew phrase is uncertain\f* then return to \x + \xo 40:5 \xt See ch. 39:14 \x*Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan, \x + \xo 40:5 \xt ch. 41:2\x*whom the king of Babylon appointed governor of the cities of Judah, and dwell with him among the people. Or go wherever you think it right to go.” So the captain of the guard gave him an allowance of food and a present, and let him go.
\v 6 Then Jeremiah went to \x + \xo 40:6 \xt [See ver. 5 above] \x*Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, at \x + \xo 40:6 \xt ch. 41:6; Josh. 18:26 \x*Mizpah, and lived with him \x + \xo 40:6 \xt ch. 37:12; 39:14 \x*among the people \x + \xo 40:6 \xt ch. 39:10\x*who were left in the land.
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 40:7 \xt For ver. 7-9, see 2 Kgs. 25:23, 24 \x*When all the captains of the forces in the open country and their men heard that \x + \xo 40:7 \xt ver. 5 \x*the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam governor in the land and had committed to him men, women, and children, those of \x + \xo 40:7 \xt ch. 39:10; 2 Kgs. 25:12\x*the poorest of the land who had not been taken into exile to Babylon,
\v 8 they went to Gedaliah at \x + \xo 40:8 \xt [See ver. 6 above] \x*Mizpah—\x + \xo 40:8 \xt ver. 14, 15, 16; See ch. 41:1-3 \x*Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, \x + \xo 40:8 \xt ver. 13, 15, 16; ch. 42:1, 8 \x*Johanan the son of Kareah, Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth, the sons of Ephai the Netophathite, \x + \xo 40:8 \xt ch. 42:1\x*Jezaniah the son of the Maacathite, they and their men.
\v 9 Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan, swore to them and their men, saying, “Do not be afraid to serve the Chaldeans. Dwell in the land and serve the king of Babylon, \x + \xo 40:9 \xt ch. 38:20\x*and it shall be well with you.
\v 10 As for me, I will dwell at \x + \xo 40:10 \xt [See ver. 6 above] \x*Mizpah, to represent you before the Chaldeans who will come to us. But as for you, \x + \xo 40:10 \xt [ver. 12]\x*gather wine and summer fruits and oil, and store them in your vessels, and dwell in your cities that you have taken.”
\v 11 Likewise, when all the Judeans who were in \x + \xo 40:11 \xt [Num. 22:1; 2 Sam. 8:2] \x*Moab and among \x + \xo 40:11 \xt 1 Sam. 11:1; 12:12 \x*the Ammonites and in \x + \xo 40:11 \xt Gen. 36:8\x*Edom and in other lands heard that the king of Babylon had left a remnant in Judah and had appointed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan, as governor over them,
\v 12 \x + \xo 40:12 \xt [ch. 43:5] \x*then all the Judeans returned from all the places to which they had been driven and came to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah at Mizpah. And they \x + \xo 40:12 \xt [ver. 10]\x*gathered wine and summer fruits in great abundance.
\p
\v 13 Now \x + \xo 40:13 \xt ver. 8, 15, 16; ch. 42:1, 8 \x*Johanan the son of Kareah and \x + \xo 40:13 \xt ch. 41:11; 42:1\x*all the leaders of the forces in the open country came to Gedaliah at Mizpah
\v 14 and said to him, “Do you know that Baalis the king of \x + \xo 40:14 \xt [ch. 41:10]\x*the Ammonites has sent Ishmael the son of Nethaniah to take your life?” But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam would not believe them.
\v 15 Then Johanan the son of Kareah spoke secretly to Gedaliah at Mizpah, “Please let me go and strike down Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and no one will know it. Why should he take your life, so that all the Judeans who are gathered about you would be scattered, \x + \xo 40:15 \xt [ch. 42:2]\x*and the remnant of Judah would perish?”
\v 16 But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam said to Johanan the son of Kareah, “You shall not do this thing, for you are speaking falsely of Ishmael.”
\c 41
\s1 Gedaliah Murdered
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 41:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 25:25 \x*In the seventh month, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, son of Elishama, of the royal family, one of the chief officers of the king, came with ten men to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, at \x + \xo 41:1 \xt See ch. 40:6, 8, 10 \x*Mizpah. As they \x + \xo 41:1 \xt [Ps. 41:9]\x*ate bread together there at Mizpah,
\v 2 \x + \xo 41:2 \xt [2 Sam. 13:28, 29] \x*Ishmael the son of Nethaniah and the ten men with him rose up and struck down Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan, with the sword, and killed him, \x + \xo 41:2 \xt ch. 40:5\x*whom the king of Babylon had appointed governor in the land.
\v 3 Ishmael also struck down all the Judeans who were with Gedaliah at \x + \xo 41:3 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*Mizpah, and the Chaldean soldiers who happened to be there.
\p
\v 4 On the day after the murder of Gedaliah, before anyone knew of it,
\v 5 eighty men arrived from \x + \xo 41:5 \xt Josh. 17:7 \x*Shechem and \x + \xo 41:5 \xt Josh. 18:1 \x*Shiloh and \x + \xo 41:5 \xt 1 Kgs. 16:24; See ch. 23:13 \x*Samaria, with \x + \xo 41:5 \xt [ch. 48:37; Deut. 14:1; Isa. 15:2] \x*their beards shaved and \x + \xo 41:5 \xt ch. 36:24 \x*their clothes torn, and \x + \xo 41:5 \xt [ch. 48:37; Deut. 14:1; Isa. 15:2] \x*their bodies gashed, \x + \xo 41:5 \xt [2 Kgs. 25:9]\x*bringing grain offerings and incense to present at the temple of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 6 And Ishmael the son of Nethaniah came out from \x + \xo 41:6 \xt ch. 40:6, 8, 10\x*Mizpah to meet them, weeping as he came. As he met them, he said to them, “Come in to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam.”
\v 7 When they came into the city, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah and the men with him slaughtered them and cast them into a cistern.
\v 8 But there were ten men among them who said to Ishmael, “Do not put us to death, for we have \x + \xo 41:8 \xt [Judg. 6:11]\x*stores of wheat, barley, oil, and honey hidden in the fields.” So he refrained and did not put them to death with their companions.
\p
\v 9 Now the cistern into which Ishmael had thrown all the bodies of the men whom he had struck down along with\f + \fr 41:9 \ft Hebrew \fq by the hand of\f* Gedaliah was the large cistern that \x + \xo 41:9 \xt [1 Kgs. 15:22; 2 Chr. 16:6]\x*King Asa had made for defense against \x + \xo 41:9 \xt [1 Kgs. 15:22; 2 Chr. 16:6]\x*Baasha king of Israel; Ishmael the son of Nethaniah filled it with the slain.
\v 10 Then Ishmael took captive all the rest of the people who were in Mizpah, \x + \xo 41:10 \xt See ch. 38:23 \x*the king’s daughters and all the people who were left at Mizpah, whom \x + \xo 41:10 \xt [ch. 40:7] \x*Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, had committed to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam. Ishmael the son of Nethaniah took them captive and set out to cross over to \x + \xo 41:10 \xt [ch. 40:14]\x*the Ammonites.
\p
\v 11 But when \x + \xo 41:11 \xt See ch. 40:8 \x*Johanan the son of Kareah and \x + \xo 41:11 \xt ch. 40:13\x*all the leaders of the forces with him heard of all the evil that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah had done,
\v 12 they took all their men and went to fight against Ishmael the son of Nethaniah. They came upon him at \x + \xo 41:12 \xt [2 Sam. 2:13] \x*the great pool that is in \x + \xo 41:12 \xt Josh. 9:3, 17\x*Gibeon.
\v 13 And when all the people who were with Ishmael saw Johanan the son of Kareah and \x + \xo 41:13 \xt ch. 40:13\x*all the leaders of the forces with him, they rejoiced.
\v 14 \x + \xo 41:14 \xt ver. 10, 16\x*So all the people whom Ishmael had carried away captive from Mizpah turned around and came back, and went to Johanan the son of Kareah.
\v 15 But Ishmael the son of Nethaniah escaped from Johanan with eight men, and went to \x + \xo 41:15 \xt [ch. 40:14]\x*the Ammonites.
\v 16 Then Johanan the son of Kareah and \x + \xo 41:16 \xt [See ver. 13 above] \x*all the leaders of the forces with him took from Mizpah all the rest of the people whom he had recovered from Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, after he had struck down Gedaliah the son of Ahikam—soldiers, \x + \xo 41:16 \xt ch. 40:7 \x*women, children, and eunuchs, whom Johanan brought back from \x + \xo 41:16 \xt Josh. 9:3, 17\x*Gibeon.
\v 17 And they went and stayed at Geruth \x + \xo 41:17 \xt [2 Sam. 19:37, 38] \x*Chimham near \x + \xo 41:17 \xt [Matt. 2:1, 14]; See Gen. 35:19\x*Bethlehem, intending to go to Egypt
\v 18 because of the Chaldeans. For they were afraid of them, because Ishmael the son of Nethaniah had struck down Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, \x + \xo 41:18 \xt ver. 2; ch. 40:5\x*whom the king of Babylon had made governor over the land.
\c 42
\s1 Warning Against Going to Egypt
\p \v 1 Then \x + \xo 42:1 \xt ch. 40:13; 41:11 \x*all the commanders of the forces, and \x + \xo 42:1 \xt See ch. 40:8 \x*Johanan the son of Kareah and Jezaniah the son of \x + \xo 42:1 \xt ch. 43:2 \x*Hoshaiah, and all the people \x + \xo 42:1 \xt [ch. 6:13]\x*from the least to the greatest, came near
\v 2 and said to Jeremiah the prophet, “Let \x + \xo 42:2 \xt See ch. 36:7 \x*our plea for mercy come before you, and \x + \xo 42:2 \xt ver. 20; [1 Sam. 7:8; 12:19] \x*pray to the \nd Lord\nd* your God for us, for all \x + \xo 42:2 \xt [ch. 40:15; Isa. 37:4] \x*this remnant—\x + \xo 42:2 \xt [Lev. 26:22]\x*because we are left with but a few, as your eyes see us—
\v 3 that \x + \xo 42:3 \xt [ch. 37:17; Ezra 8:21]\x*the \nd Lord\nd* your God may show us the way we should go, and the thing that we should do.”
\v 4 Jeremiah the prophet said to them, “I have heard you. Behold, I will pray to the \nd Lord\nd* your God according to your request, and \x + \xo 42:4 \xt 1 Sam. 3:18; [Num. 22:18]\x*whatever the \nd Lord\nd* answers you I will tell you. \x + \xo 42:4 \xt 1 Sam. 3:18; [Num. 22:18]\x*I will keep nothing back from you.”
\v 5 Then they said to Jeremiah, \x + \xo 42:5 \xt [Gen. 31:50] \x*“May the \nd Lord\nd* be a true and \x + \xo 42:5 \xt [Rev. 1:5; 3:14] \x*faithful witness against us \x + \xo 42:5 \xt Judg. 11:10 \x*if we do not act according to all the word \x + \xo 42:5 \xt ver. 21\x*with which the \nd Lord\nd* your God sends you to us.
\v 6 Whether it is good or bad, we will obey the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* our God to whom we are sending you, \x + \xo 42:6 \xt ch. 7:23\x*that it may be well with us when we obey the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* our God.”
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 42:7 \xt [Ezek. 3:16]\x*At the end of ten days the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah.
\v 8 Then he summoned \x + \xo 42:8 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*Johanan the son of Kareah and \x + \xo 42:8 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*all the commanders of the forces who were with him, and all the people \x + \xo 42:8 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*from the least to the greatest,
\v 9 and said to them, “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, \x + \xo 42:9 \xt ver. 2, 3\x*to whom you sent me to present your plea for mercy before him:
\v 10 If you will remain in this land, \x + \xo 42:10 \xt See ch. 24:6 \x*then I will build you up and not pull you down; I will plant you, and not pluck you up; \x + \xo 42:10 \xt ch. 18:8; Gen. 6:6; [Deut. 32:36]\x*for I relent of the disaster that I did to you.
\v 11 \x + \xo 42:11 \xt [ch. 22:25; 41:18] \x*Do not fear the king of Babylon, \x + \xo 42:11 \xt [ch. 22:25; 41:18] \x*of whom you are afraid. \x + \xo 42:11 \xt ch. 30:10, 11; [Rom. 8:31]\x*Do not fear him, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 42:11 \xt ch. 30:10, 11; [Rom. 8:31]\x*for I am with you, to save you and to deliver you from his hand.
\v 12 \x + \xo 42:12 \xt [Neh. 1:11]\x*I will grant you mercy, that he may have mercy on you and let you remain in your own land.
\v 13 \x + \xo 42:13 \xt ch. 43:4; [ch. 44:16, 17]\x*But if you say, ‘We will not remain in this land,’ disobeying the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* your God
\v 14 and saying, ‘No, \x + \xo 42:14 \xt [ch. 41:17] \x*we will go to the land of Egypt, where we shall not see war or \x + \xo 42:14 \xt ch. 4:19 \x*hear the sound of the trumpet or \x + \xo 42:14 \xt [ch. 37:21]\x*be hungry for bread, and we will dwell there,’
\v 15 then hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, O remnant of Judah. Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 42:15 \xt ch. 44:12; [ver. 19; Deut. 17:16] \x*If you set your faces to enter Egypt \x + \xo 42:15 \xt ch. 44:27; See ch. 44:1, 12-14\x*and go to live there,
\v 16 then the sword \x + \xo 42:16 \xt Ezek. 11:8 \x*that you fear shall overtake you there in the land of Egypt, and the famine of which you are afraid shall follow close after you to Egypt, \x + \xo 42:16 \xt ver. 22; ch. 44:12\x*and there you shall die.
\v 17 All the men who set their faces to go to Egypt to live there shall die by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence. They shall have \x + \xo 42:17 \xt Lam. 2:22\x*no remnant or survivor from the disaster that I will bring upon them.
\p
\v 18 “For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 42:18 \xt See ch. 7:20 \x*As my anger and my wrath were poured out on the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so my wrath will be poured out on you when you go to Egypt. \x + \xo 42:18 \xt See ch. 18:16\x*You shall become an execration, a horror, a curse, and a taunt. You shall see this place no more.
\v 19 The \nd Lord\nd* has said to you, O remnant of Judah, \x + \xo 42:19 \xt ch. 43:2; [ver. 14-16] \x*‘Do not go to Egypt.’ \x + \xo 42:19 \xt [Ezek. 2:5]\x*Know for a certainty that I have warned you this day
\v 20 that you have gone astray at the cost of your lives. \x + \xo 42:20 \xt ver. 2 \x*For you sent me to the \nd Lord\nd* your God, saying, \x + \xo 42:20 \xt ver. 2 \x*‘Pray for us to the \nd Lord\nd* our God, and \x + \xo 42:20 \xt ver. 3\x*whatever the \nd Lord\nd* our God says declare to us and we will do it.’
\v 21 And I have this day declared it to you, but you have not obeyed the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* your God in anything \x + \xo 42:21 \xt ver. 5\x*that he sent me to tell you.
\v 22 \x + \xo 42:22 \xt ver. 16, 17\x*Now therefore know for a certainty that you shall die by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence in the place where you desire to go to live.”
\c 43
\s1 Jeremiah Taken to Egypt
\p \v 1 When Jeremiah finished speaking to all the people all these words of the \nd Lord\nd* their God, with which the \nd Lord\nd* their God had sent him to them,
\v 2 Azariah the son of \x + \xo 43:2 \xt ch. 42:1 \x*Hoshaiah and \x + \xo 43:2 \xt See ch. 40:8 \x*Johanan the son of Kareah and \x + \xo 43:2 \xt Ps. 86:14; Isa. 13:11; Mal. 4:1 \x*all the insolent men said to Jeremiah, “You are telling a lie. The \nd Lord\nd* our God did not send you to say, \x + \xo 43:2 \xt ch. 42:19\x*‘Do not go to Egypt to live there,’
\v 3 but \x + \xo 43:3 \xt See ch. 32:12 \x*Baruch the son of Neriah \x + \xo 43:3 \xt [ch. 38:22] \x*has set you against us, \x + \xo 43:3 \xt [ch. 37:13]\x*to deliver us into the hand of the Chaldeans, that they may kill us or take us into exile in Babylon.”
\v 4 So \x + \xo 43:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*Johanan the son of Kareah and all \x + \xo 43:4 \xt ch. 40:13\x*the commanders of the forces and all the people did not obey the voice of the \nd Lord\nd*, to remain in the land of Judah.
\v 5 But Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces took \x + \xo 43:5 \xt [ch. 40:11, 12]\x*all the remnant of Judah who had returned to live in the land of Judah from all the nations to which they had been driven—
\v 6 \x + \xo 43:6 \xt ch. 44:20 \x*the men, the women, the children, \x + \xo 43:6 \xt See ch. 38:23 \x*the princesses, and every person whom \x + \xo 43:6 \xt ch. 39:10; 40:7 \x*Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had left with \x + \xo 43:6 \xt See ch. 39:14\x*Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan; also Jeremiah the prophet and Baruch the son of Neriah.
\v 7 And they came into the land of Egypt, for they did not obey the voice of the \nd Lord\nd*. And they arrived at \x + \xo 43:7 \xt ch. 2:16; 44:1; 46:14; [Isa. 30:4]\x*Tahpanhes.
\p
\v 8 Then the word of the \nd Lord\nd* came to Jeremiah in \x + \xo 43:8 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*Tahpanhes:
\v 9 “Take in your hands large stones and hide them in the mortar in the pavement that is at the entrance to Pharaoh’s palace in \x + \xo 43:9 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*Tahpanhes, in the sight of the men of Judah,
\v 10 and say to them, ‘Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, I will send and take Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, \x + \xo 43:10 \xt See ch. 25:9 \x*my servant, \x + \xo 43:10 \xt ch. 1:15\x*and I will set his throne above these stones that I have hidden, and he will spread his royal canopy over them.
\v 11 He shall come \x + \xo 43:11 \xt ch. 44:13; 46:13 \x*and strike the land of Egypt, \x + \xo 43:11 \xt See ch. 15:2\x*giving over to the pestilence those who are doomed to the pestilence, to captivity those who are doomed to captivity, and to the sword those who are doomed to the sword.
\v 12 \x + \xo 43:12 \xt See ch. 17:27 \x*I shall kindle a fire \x + \xo 43:12 \xt ch. 46:25; Ezek. 30:13; [Ex. 12:12; Isa. 19:1] \x*in the temples of the gods of Egypt, and he shall burn them \x + \xo 43:12 \xt [ch. 48:7] \x*and carry them away captive. \x + \xo 43:12 \xt [Ps. 104:2; Isa. 49:18]\x*And he shall clean the land of Egypt \x + \xo 43:12 \xt [Ps. 104:2; Isa. 49:18]\x*as a shepherd cleans his cloak of vermin, and he shall go away from there in peace.
\v 13 He shall break the \x + \xo 43:13 \xt [Ex. 23:24] \x*obelisks of Heliopolis, which is in the land of Egypt, \x + \xo 43:13 \xt [See ver. 12 above]\x*and the temples of the gods of Egypt he shall burn with fire.’”
\c 44
\s1 Judgment for Idolatry
\p \v 1 The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the Judeans who lived in the land of Egypt, at \x + \xo 44:1 \xt ch. 46:14; Ex. 14:2 \x*Migdol, at \x + \xo 44:1 \xt See ch. 43:7-9 \x*Tahpanhes, at Memphis, and in the land of \x + \xo 44:1 \xt ver. 15; See Isa. 11:11\x*Pathros,
\v 2 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: You have seen all the disaster that I brought upon Jerusalem and upon all the cities of Judah. Behold, this day \x + \xo 44:2 \xt ver. 6\x*they are a desolation, and no one dwells in them,
\v 3 because of the evil that they committed, \x + \xo 44:3 \xt ver. 8; See ch. 7:18, 19 \x*provoking me to anger, \x + \xo 44:3 \xt See ch. 1:16 \x*in that they went to make offerings \x + \xo 44:3 \xt ch. 19:4; Deut. 6:14\x*and serve other gods that they knew not, neither they, nor you, nor your fathers.
\v 4 \x + \xo 44:4 \xt See 2 Chr. 36:15\x*Yet I persistently sent to you all my servants the prophets, saying, ‘Oh, do not do this abomination that I hate!’
\v 5 \x + \xo 44:5 \xt See ch. 34:14\x*But they did not listen \x + \xo 44:5 \xt See ch. 34:14\x*or incline their ear, to turn from their evil and make no offerings to other gods.
\v 6 \x + \xo 44:6 \xt See ch. 7:20 \x*Therefore my wrath and my anger were poured out and kindled in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, \x + \xo 44:6 \xt See ch. 7:34; 9:11\x*and they became a waste and a desolation, as at this day.
\v 7 And now thus says the \nd Lord\nd* God of hosts, the God of Israel: Why do you commit this great evil \x + \xo 44:7 \xt Hab. 2:10; [Num. 16:38; Prov. 20:2] \x*against yourselves, to cut off from you \x + \xo 44:7 \xt [ch. 38:23; Lam. 2:11]\x*man and woman, \x + \xo 44:7 \xt [ch. 38:23; Lam. 2:11]\x*infant and child, from the midst of Judah, leaving you no remnant?
\v 8 \x + \xo 44:8 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*Why do you provoke me to anger with the works of your hands, \x + \xo 44:8 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*making offerings to other gods in the land of Egypt where you have come to live, so that you may be cut off and become \x + \xo 44:8 \xt ch. 42:18; See ch. 18:16\x*a curse and a taunt among all the nations of the earth?
\v 9 Have you forgotten the evil of your fathers, \x + \xo 44:9 \xt [ch. 15:4] \x*the evil of the kings of Judah, \x + \xo 44:9 \xt 1 Kgs. 11:1, 8; 15:13; 2 Kgs. 11:1 \x*the evil of their\f + \fr 44:9 \ft Hebrew \fq his\f* wives, your own evil, \x + \xo 44:9 \xt ver. 15, 25\x*and the evil of your wives, which they committed in the land of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem?
\v 10 They have not humbled themselves even to this day, \x + \xo 44:10 \xt [Prov. 28:14]\x*nor have they feared, nor walked in my law and my statutes that I set before you and before your fathers.
\p
\v 11 “Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 44:11 \xt See ch. 21:10\x*Behold, I will set my face against you for harm, to cut off all Judah.
\v 12 I will take the remnant of Judah who have \x + \xo 44:12 \xt ch. 42:15 \x*set their faces to come to the land of Egypt to live, and they shall all be consumed. \x + \xo 44:12 \xt ch. 42:16 \x*In the land of Egypt they shall fall; by the sword and by famine \x + \xo 44:12 \xt ch. 42:16 \x*they shall be consumed. \x + \xo 44:12 \xt See ch. 6:13 \x*From the least to the greatest, they shall die by the sword and by famine, \x + \xo 44:12 \xt See ch. 18:16 \x*and they shall become an oath, a horror, \x + \xo 44:12 \xt [See ver. 8 above]\x*a curse, and a taunt.
\v 13 \x + \xo 44:13 \xt ch. 43:11\x*I will punish those who dwell in the land of Egypt, as I have punished Jerusalem, with the sword, with famine, and with pestilence,
\v 14 \x + \xo 44:14 \xt ch. 42:17 \x*so that none of the remnant of Judah who have come to live in the land of Egypt shall escape or survive \x + \xo 44:14 \xt [ch. 22:27] \x*or return to the land of Judah, to which they desire to return to dwell there. For they shall not return, \x + \xo 44:14 \xt [ver. 28]\x*except some fugitives.”
\p
\v 15 Then all the men who knew that \x + \xo 44:15 \xt ver. 9, 25 \x*their wives had made offerings to other gods, and all the women who stood by, a great assembly, all the people who lived in \x + \xo 44:15 \xt See ver. 1\x*Pathros in the land of Egypt, answered Jeremiah:
\v 16 “As for the word that you have spoken to us in the name of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 44:16 \xt ch. 6:16; 42:13\x*we will not listen to you.
\v 17 \x + \xo 44:17 \xt [Judg. 11:36] \x*But we will do everything that we have vowed, make offerings to \x + \xo 44:17 \xt ch. 7:18 \x*the queen of heaven \x + \xo 44:17 \xt ch. 19:13 \x*and pour out drink offerings to her, \x + \xo 44:17 \xt [1 Kgs. 11:33; 2 Kgs. 21:3]\x*as we did, both we and our fathers, our kings and our officials, in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem. For then we had plenty of food, and prospered, and saw no disaster.
\v 18 But since we left off making offerings to \x + \xo 44:18 \xt [See ver. 17 above] \x*the queen of heaven and pouring out drink offerings to her, we have lacked everything \x + \xo 44:18 \xt [Lam. 3:22]\x*and have been consumed by the sword and by famine.”
\v 19 And the women said,\f + \fr 44:19 \ft Compare Syriac; Hebrew lacks \fq And the women said\f* “When we made offerings to the queen of heaven \x + \xo 44:19 \xt ch. 7:18 \x*and poured out drink offerings to her, was it \x + \xo 44:19 \xt [Num. 30:6, 7]\x*without our husbands’ approval that we made cakes for her bearing her image and poured out drink offerings to her?”
\p
\v 20 Then Jeremiah said to all the people, \x + \xo 44:20 \xt ch. 43:6\x*men and women, all the people who had given him this answer:
\v 21 \x + \xo 44:21 \xt ver. 17; [Ezek. 8:10, 11] \x*“As for the offerings that you offered in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, you and your fathers, your kings and your officials, and the people of the land, \x + \xo 44:21 \xt [Ezek. 21:24]\x*did not the \nd Lord\nd* remember them? Did it not come into his mind?
\v 22 \x + \xo 44:22 \xt ch. 5:9, 29 \x*The \nd Lord\nd* could no longer bear your evil deeds and \x + \xo 44:22 \xt Ezek. 8:6 \x*the abominations that you committed. \x + \xo 44:22 \xt See ch. 7:34 \x*Therefore your land has become \x + \xo 44:22 \xt See ch. 18:16 \x*a desolation and a waste and a curse, \x + \xo 44:22 \xt See ch. 4:7\x*without inhabitant, as it is this day.
\v 23 It is because you made offerings \x + \xo 44:23 \xt See ch. 40:3 \x*and because you sinned against the \nd Lord\nd* and did not obey the voice of the \nd Lord\nd* or walk in his law and in his statutes and in his testimonies \x + \xo 44:23 \xt [Deut. 31:29]\x*that this disaster has happened to you, as at this day.”
\p
\v 24 Jeremiah said to all the people and all the women, “Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 44:24 \xt ver. 15; See ch. 43:5-7\x*all you of Judah who are in the land of Egypt.
\v 25 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: \x + \xo 44:25 \xt ver. 16 \x*You and your wives have declared with your mouths, and have fulfilled it with your hands, saying, ‘We will surely perform our vows that we have made, \x + \xo 44:25 \xt ver. 17\x*to make offerings to the queen of heaven and to pour out drink offerings to her.’ Then confirm your vows and perform your vows!
\v 26 Therefore hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 44:26 \xt [See ver. 24 above] \x*all you of Judah who dwell in the land of Egypt: \x + \xo 44:26 \xt See ch. 22:5 \x*Behold, I have sworn by my great name, says the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 44:26 \xt [Ezek. 20:39] \x*that my name shall no more be invoked by the mouth of any man of Judah in all the land of Egypt, \x + \xo 44:26 \xt [ch. 4:2]\x*saying, ‘As the Lord \nd God\nd* lives.’
\v 27 \x + \xo 44:27 \xt ch. 31:28 \x*Behold, I am watching over them for disaster and not for good. \x + \xo 44:27 \xt ch. 42:16\x*All the men of Judah who are in the land of Egypt shall be consumed by the sword and by famine, until there is an end of them.
\v 28 \x + \xo 44:28 \xt [ver. 14; Isa. 27:13] \x*And those who escape the sword shall return from the land of Egypt to the land of Judah, \x + \xo 44:28 \xt Ezek. 6:8 \x*few in number; and all the remnant of Judah, who came to the land of Egypt to live, \x + \xo 44:28 \xt ver. 17, 25, 26\x*shall know whose word will stand, mine or theirs.
\v 29 This shall be the sign to you, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, that I will punish you in this place, in order that you may know that \x + \xo 44:29 \xt Prov. 19:21\x*my words will surely stand against you for harm:
\v 30 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, Behold, I will give \x + \xo 44:30 \xt ch. 46:17; See Ezek. 29:2-5; 30:21-24 \x*Pharaoh Hophra king of Egypt into the hand of his enemies \x + \xo 44:30 \xt ch. 46:26 \x*and into the hand of those who seek his life, as I gave \x + \xo 44:30 \xt [ch. 39:5]\x*Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, who was his enemy and sought his life.”
\c 45
\s1 Message to Baruch
\p \v 1 The word that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to \x + \xo 45:1 \xt See ch. 32:12 \x*Baruch the son of Neriah, \x + \xo 45:1 \xt See ch. 36:4, 18 \x*when he wrote these words in a book at the dictation of Jeremiah, \x + \xo 45:1 \xt ch. 36:1\x*in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah:
\v 2 “Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, to you, O Baruch:
\v 3 You said, \x + \xo 45:3 \xt [ch. 36:26] \x*‘Woe is me! For the \nd Lord\nd* has added sorrow to my pain. \x + \xo 45:3 \xt Ps. 6:6 \x*I am weary with my groaning, \x + \xo 45:3 \xt Lam. 1:3; 5:5\x*and I find no rest.’
\v 4 Thus shall you say to him, Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 45:4 \xt ch. 31:28; [Isa. 5:5]\x*Behold, what I have built I am breaking down, and what I have planted I am plucking up—that is, the whole land.
\v 5 And \x + \xo 45:5 \xt [Ps. 131:1, 2; Rom. 12:16] \x*do you seek great things for yourself? Seek them not, for behold, \x + \xo 45:5 \xt [ch. 25:26, 29] \x*I am bringing disaster upon all flesh, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. But I will give you \x + \xo 45:5 \xt ch. 21:9; 39:18\x*your life as a prize of war in all places to which you may go.”
\c 46
\s1 Judgment on Egypt
\p \v 1 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* that came to Jeremiah the prophet \x + \xo 46:1 \xt [ch. 1:5; 25:13]; See ch. 25:15-26\x*concerning the nations.
\p
\v 2 About Egypt. \x + \xo 46:2 \xt 2 Kgs. 23:29; 2 Chr. 35:20 \x*Concerning the army of Pharaoh Neco, king of Egypt, which was by the river Euphrates at Carchemish and which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon defeated in \x + \xo 46:2 \xt ch. 25:1; 36:1; 45:1\x*the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah:
\b
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 46:3 \xt [ch. 51:11]\x*“Prepare buckler and shield,
\q2 and advance for battle!
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 46:4 \xt [Nah. 3:2] \x*Harness the horses;
\q2 mount, O horsemen!
\q1 Take your stations with your helmets,
\q2 \x + \xo 46:4 \xt [See ver. 3 above]\x*polish your spears,
\q2 put on your armor!
\q1
\v 5 Why have I seen it?
\q1 They are dismayed
\q2 and have turned backward.
\q1 Their \x + \xo 46:5 \xt [2 Sam. 1:19, 25] \x*warriors are beaten down
\q2 and have fled in haste;
\q1 \x + \xo 46:5 \xt ver. 21; ch. 47:3 \x*they look not back—
\q2 \x + \xo 46:5 \xt See ch. 6:25\x*terror on every side!
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 6 “The swift cannot flee away,
\q2 nor the warrior escape;
\q1 \x + \xo 46:6 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*in the north by the river Euphrates
\q2 \x + \xo 46:6 \xt [Dan. 11:19]\x*they have stumbled and fallen.
\b
\q1
\v 7 “Who is this, \x + \xo 46:7 \xt [ch. 47:2; Isa. 8:7, 8; Dan. 11:22] \x*rising like the Nile,
