\q2 and your daughters into captivity.
\q1
\v 47 \x + \xo 48:47 \xt [ch. 46:27; 49:39]\x*Yet I will restore the fortunes of Moab
\q2 in the latter days, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\q1 Thus far is the judgment on Moab.
\c 49
\s1 Judgment on Ammon
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 49:1 \xt ch. 25:21; [Ezek. 21:28; 25:2] \x*Concerning the Ammonites.
\p Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 “Has Israel no sons?
\q2 Has he no heir?
\q1 Why then has \x + \xo 49:1 \xt [1 Kgs. 11:5, 33; 2 Kgs. 23:13] \x*Milcom \x + \xo 49:1 \xt [Amos 1:13]\x*dispossessed Gad,
\q2 and his people settled in its cities?
\q1
\v 2 Therefore, behold, the days are coming,
\q2 declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 when I will cause \x + \xo 49:2 \xt ch. 4:19 \x*the battle cry to be heard
\q2 against \x + \xo 49:2 \xt Ezek. 21:20; 25:5; Amos 1:14 \x*Rabbah of the Ammonites;
\q1 it shall become a desolate \x + \xo 49:2 \xt ch. 30:18\x*mound,
\q2 and its villages shall be burned with fire;
\q1 then Israel shall dispossess those who dispossessed him,
\q2 says the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 3 “Wail, O \x + \xo 49:3 \xt ch. 48:2 \x*Heshbon, for Ai is laid waste!
\q2 Cry out, O daughters of \x + \xo 49:3 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*Rabbah!
\q1 \x + \xo 49:3 \xt ch. 48:37; See ch. 4:8 \x*Put on sackcloth,
\q2 lament, and run to and fro among the hedges!
\q1 For \x + \xo 49:3 \xt [1 Kgs. 11:5, 33; 2 Kgs. 23:13] \x*Milcom shall go into exile,
\q2 \x + \xo 49:3 \xt ch. 48:7\x*with his priests and his officials.
\q1
\v 4 Why do you boast of your valleys,\f + \fr 49:4 \ft Hebrew \fq boast of your valleys, your valley flows\f*
\q2 \x + \xo 49:4 \xt ch. 3:14 \x*O faithless daughter,
\q1 \x + \xo 49:4 \xt ch. 48:7\x*who trusted in her treasures, saying,
\q2 ‘Who will come against me?’
\q1
\v 5 Behold, \x + \xo 49:5 \xt [ch. 48:43]\x*I will bring terror upon you,
\q2 declares the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts,
\q2 from all who are around you,
\q1 and you shall be driven out, every man straight before him,
\q2 with none to gather the fugitives.
\b
\p
\v 6 “But \x + \xo 49:6 \xt [ver. 39; ch. 48:47]\x*afterward I will restore the fortunes of the Ammonites, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\s1 Judgment on Edom
\p
\v 7 Concerning \x + \xo 49:7 \xt ch. 25:21; Isa. 34:5; Amos 1:11; Obad. 1; [Mal. 1:2]; See Ezek. 25:12-14 \x*Edom.
\p Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 49:7 \xt ver. 20; Obad. 9 \x*“Is wisdom no more in \x + \xo 49:7 \xt ver. 20; Obad. 9 \x*Teman?
\q2 \x + \xo 49:7 \xt [Isa. 19:11, 12]\x*Has counsel perished from the prudent?
\q2 \x + \xo 49:7 \xt [Isa. 19:11, 12]\x*Has their wisdom vanished?
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 49:8 \xt ver. 30 \x*Flee, turn back, dwell in the depths,
\q2 O inhabitants of \x + \xo 49:8 \xt ch. 25:23; Gen. 25:3 \x*Dedan!
\q1 For I will bring the calamity of Esau upon him,
\q2 \x + \xo 49:8 \xt ch. 50:27, 31; [ch. 46:21; 50:27]\x*the time when I punish him.
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 49:9 \xt Obad. 5, 6 \x*If grape gatherers came to you,
\q2 would they not leave \x + \xo 49:9 \xt [Judg. 8:2]\x*gleanings?
\q1 \x + \xo 49:9 \xt Obad. 5, 6 \x*If thieves came by night,
\q2 would they not destroy only enough for themselves?
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 49:10 \xt Mal. 1:3 \x*But I have stripped Esau bare;
\q2 \x + \xo 49:10 \xt [See ver. 9 above] \x*I have uncovered his hiding places,
\q2 and he is not able to conceal himself.
\q1 His children are destroyed, and his brothers,
\q2 and his neighbors; and \x + \xo 49:10 \xt ch. 31:15; Isa. 17:14\x*he is no more.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 49:11 \xt [Ps. 10:14, 18; 68:5]\x*Leave your fatherless children; I will keep them alive;
\q2 \x + \xo 49:11 \xt [Ps. 10:14, 18; 68:5]\x*and let your widows trust in me.”
\b
\p
\v 12 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 49:12 \xt ch. 25:28; [Obad. 16] \x*“If those who did not deserve to drink the cup must drink it, \x + \xo 49:12 \xt ch. 25:29\x*will you go unpunished? You shall not go unpunished, but you must drink.
\v 13 \x + \xo 49:13 \xt See ch. 22:5 \x*For I have sworn by myself, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, that \x + \xo 49:13 \xt ver. 22; See ch. 48:24 \x*Bozrah shall become \x + \xo 49:13 \xt See ch. 24:9\x*a horror, a taunt, a waste, and a curse, and all her cities shall be perpetual wastes.”
\b
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 49:14 \xt See Obad. 1-4 \x*I have heard a message from the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and an envoy has been sent among the nations:
\q1 \x + \xo 49:14 \xt [Isa. 13:4]\x*“Gather yourselves together and come against her,
\q2 and rise up for battle!
\q1
\v 15 For behold, I will make you small among the nations,
\q2 despised among mankind.
\q1
\v 16 The horror you inspire has deceived you,
\q2 and the pride of your heart,
\q1 you who live in the clefts of the rock,\f + \fr 49:16 \ft Or \fq of Sela\f*
\q2 who hold the height of the hill.
\q1 Though you \x + \xo 49:16 \xt [ch. 48:28]\x*make your nest as high as the eagle’s,
\q2 I will bring you down from there,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\p
\v 17 \x + \xo 49:17 \xt Ezek. 35:3, 7, 9 \x*“Edom shall become a horror. \x + \xo 49:17 \xt [ch. 50:13]\x*Everyone who passes by it will be horrified \x + \xo 49:17 \xt [ch. 50:13]\x*and will hiss because of all its disasters.
\v 18 \x + \xo 49:18 \xt See Isa. 13:19 \x*As when Sodom and Gomorrah and their \x + \xo 49:18 \xt [Deut. 29:23] \x*neighboring cities were overthrown, says the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 49:18 \xt ver. 33\x*no man shall dwell there, \x + \xo 49:18 \xt ver. 33\x*no man shall sojourn in her.
\v 19 \x + \xo 49:19 \xt For ver. 19-21, see ch. 50:44-46 \x*Behold, \x + \xo 49:19 \xt See ch. 4:7 \x*like a lion coming up from \x + \xo 49:19 \xt See ch. 12:5 \x*the jungle of the Jordan against a perennial pasture, I will suddenly make him\f + \fr 49:19 \ft Septuagint, Syriac \fq them\f* run away from her. And I will appoint over her whomever I choose. \x + \xo 49:19 \xt See ch. 10:6 \x*For who is like me? \x + \xo 49:19 \xt Job 9:19 \x*Who will summon me? \x + \xo 49:19 \xt [ch. 30:21]\x*What shepherd can stand before me?
\v 20 Therefore hear the plan that the \nd Lord\nd* has made against \x + \xo 49:20 \xt Ezek. 35:3, 7, 9 \x*Edom and the purposes that he has formed against the inhabitants of \x + \xo 49:20 \xt See ver. 7 \x*Teman: \x + \xo 49:20 \xt ch. 50:45\x*Even the little ones of the flock shall be dragged away. Surely their fold shall be appalled at their fate.
\v 21 At the sound of their fall \x + \xo 49:21 \xt ch. 8:16; 50:46; [Ezek. 26:15]\x*the earth shall tremble; the sound of their cry shall be heard at the Red Sea.
\v 22 Behold, \x + \xo 49:22 \xt See ch. 48:40 \x*one shall mount up and fly swiftly like an eagle and spread his wings against \x + \xo 49:22 \xt ver. 13 \x*Bozrah, and the heart of the warriors of Edom shall be in that day like the heart \x + \xo 49:22 \xt ver. 24; See ch. 6:24\x*of a woman in her birth pains.”
\s1 Judgment on Damascus
\p
\v 23 Concerning \x + \xo 49:23 \xt Isa. 17:1; Amos 1:3 \x*Damascus:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 49:23 \xt 1 Kgs. 8:65; Zech. 9:2 \x*“Hamath and \x + \xo 49:23 \xt 2 Kgs. 18:34 \x*Arpad are confounded,
\q2 for they have heard bad news;
\q1 they melt in fear,
\q2 \x + \xo 49:23 \xt Zech. 9:4\x*they are troubled like the sea that cannot be quiet.
\q1
\v 24 \x + \xo 49:24 \xt [See ver. 23 above] \x*Damascus has become feeble, \x + \xo 49:24 \xt [ch. 46:5] \x*she turned to flee,
\q2 and panic seized her;
\q1 anguish and sorrows have taken hold of her,
\q2 as \x + \xo 49:24 \xt [See ver. 22 above]\x*of a woman in labor.
\q1
\v 25 How is \x + \xo 49:25 \xt [ch. 33:9]\x*the famous city not forsaken,
\q2 the city of my joy?
\q1
\v 26 \x + \xo 49:26 \xt ch. 50:30\x*Therefore her young men shall fall in her squares,
\q2 and all her soldiers shall be destroyed in that day,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts.
\q1
\v 27 And \x + \xo 49:27 \xt See ch. 17:27 \x*I will kindle a fire in the wall of \x + \xo 49:27 \xt [See ver. 23 above] \x*Damascus,
\q2 and it shall devour the strongholds of \x + \xo 49:27 \xt 1 Kgs. 15:18; 20:1; 2 Kgs. 6:24; 8:7; 13:3\x*Ben-hadad.”
\s1 Judgment on Kedar and Hazor
\p
\v 28 Concerning \x + \xo 49:28 \xt Isa. 21:16; 60:7 \x*Kedar and the kingdoms of Hazor that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon struck down.
\b
\q1 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 \x + \xo 49:28 \xt ver. 14, 31 \x*“Rise up, advance against \x + \xo 49:28 \xt Isa. 21:16; 60:7 \x*Kedar!
\q2 Destroy \x + \xo 49:28 \xt Isa. 11:14; Ezek. 25:4, 10; See Judg. 6:3\x*the people of the east!
\q1
\v 29 \x + \xo 49:29 \xt Ps. 120:5; Song 1:5 \x*Their tents and their flocks shall be taken,
\q2 their \x + \xo 49:29 \xt Ps. 120:5; Song 1:5 \x*curtains and all their goods;
\q1 their camels shall be led away from them,
\q2 and men shall cry to them: \x + \xo 49:29 \xt See ch. 6:25\x*‘Terror on every side!’
\q1
\v 30 \x + \xo 49:30 \xt ver. 8\x*Flee, wander far away, dwell in the depths,
\q2 O inhabitants of Hazor!
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1 For Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon
\q2 has made a plan against you
\q2 and formed a purpose against you.
\b
\q1
\v 31 \x + \xo 49:31 \xt [See ver. 28 above] \x*“Rise up, advance against a nation \x + \xo 49:31 \xt Job 16:12 \x*at ease,
\q2 \x + \xo 49:31 \xt Ezek. 38:8, 11\x*that dwells securely,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 \x + \xo 49:31 \xt Ezek. 38:8, 11\x*that has no gates or bars,
\q2 that dwells alone.
\q1
\v 32 \x + \xo 49:32 \xt [Ezek. 38:12] \x*Their camels shall become plunder,
\q2 their herds of livestock a spoil.
\q1 \x + \xo 49:32 \xt ver. 36 \x*I will scatter to every wind
\q2 \x + \xo 49:32 \xt See ch. 9:26\x*those who cut the corners of their hair,
\q1 and I will bring their calamity
\q2 from every side of them,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 33 Hazor shall become \x + \xo 49:33 \xt See ch. 9:11 \x*a haunt of jackals,
\q2 an everlasting waste;
\q1 \x + \xo 49:33 \xt ver. 18\x*no man shall dwell there;
\q2 \x + \xo 49:33 \xt ver. 18\x*no man shall sojourn in her.”
\s1 Judgment on Elam
\p
\v 34 The word of the \nd Lord\nd* that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning \x + \xo 49:34 \xt ch. 25:25; Gen. 14:1; Isa. 11:11; 21:2; Ezek. 32:24; Dan. 8:2 \x*Elam, in the beginning of the reign of \x + \xo 49:34 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:17, 18\x*Zedekiah king of Judah.
\p
\v 35 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts: “Behold, I will break \x + \xo 49:35 \xt Isa. 22:6 \x*the bow of \x + \xo 49:35 \xt [See ver. 34 above]\x*Elam, the mainstay of their might.
\v 36 And I will bring upon \x + \xo 49:36 \xt [See ver. 34 above]\x*Elam the four winds from the four quarters of heaven. And I will scatter them to all those winds, and there shall be no nation to which those driven out of \x + \xo 49:36 \xt [See ver. 34 above]\x*Elam shall not come.
\v 37 I will \x + \xo 49:37 \xt [ch. 1:17] \x*terrify \x + \xo 49:37 \xt [See ver. 34 above] \x*Elam before their enemies and before those who seek their life. I will bring disaster upon them, \x + \xo 49:37 \xt See ch. 12:13 \x*my fierce anger, declares the \nd Lord\nd*. \x + \xo 49:37 \xt See ch. 9:16\x*I will send the sword after them, until I have consumed them,
\v 38 and I will set my throne in \x + \xo 49:38 \xt [See ver. 34 above]\x*Elam and destroy their king and officials, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\p
\v 39 “But in the latter days \x + \xo 49:39 \xt [ch. 48:47] \x*I will restore the fortunes of \x + \xo 49:39 \xt [See ver. 34 above]\x*Elam, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\c 50
\s1 Judgment on Babylon
\p \v 1 The word that the \nd Lord\nd* spoke concerning \x + \xo 50:1 \xt See Isa. 13:1–14:27; 21:1-10 \x*Babylon, concerning the land of the Chaldeans, \x + \xo 50:1 \xt [ch. 51:59, 60]\x*by Jeremiah the prophet:
\b
\q1
\v 2 “Declare among the nations and proclaim,
\q2 set up a banner and proclaim,
\q2 conceal it not, and say:
\q1 \x + \xo 50:2 \xt Isa. 21:9 \x*‘Babylon is taken,
\q2 \x + \xo 50:2 \xt See Isa. 46:1\x*Bel is put to shame,
\q2 Merodach is dismayed.
\q1 \x + \xo 50:2 \xt Isa. 21:9 \x*Her images are put to shame,
\q2 her idols are dismayed.’
\b
\p
\v 3 “For \x + \xo 50:3 \xt See ch. 1:14 \x*out of the north a nation has come up against her, \x + \xo 50:3 \xt ver. 13, 23; ch. 51:29 \x*which shall make her land a desolation, and none shall dwell in it; \x + \xo 50:3 \xt ch. 51:62; [Ps. 135:8]\x*both man and beast shall flee away.
\b
\p
\v 4 \x + \xo 50:4 \xt See ch. 3:18 \x*“In those days and in that time, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 50:4 \xt See ch. 3:18 \x*the people of Israel and the people of Judah shall come together, \x + \xo 50:4 \xt ch. 31:9, 18; Ezra 8:21; Ps. 126:6 \x*weeping as they come, and they \x + \xo 50:4 \xt Hos. 3:5\x*shall seek the \nd Lord\nd* their God.
\v 5 \x + \xo 50:5 \xt [ch. 31:21] \x*They shall ask the way to Zion, with faces turned toward it, \x + \xo 50:5 \xt [Isa. 2:3] \x*saying, ‘Come, let us join ourselves to the \nd Lord\nd* in an \x + \xo 50:5 \xt See ch. 32:40\x*everlasting covenant that will never be forgotten.’
\b
\p
\v 6 \x + \xo 50:6 \xt ver. 17; Isa. 53:6; [Matt. 18:12; Luke 15:4] \x*“My people have been lost sheep. \x + \xo 50:6 \xt Zech. 10:2; See Ezek. 34:1-6\x*Their shepherds have led them astray, turning them away on the mountains. From mountain to hill they have gone. They have forgotten their fold.
\v 7 All who found them have devoured them, \x + \xo 50:7 \xt [ch. 40:2, 3] \x*and their enemies have said, ‘We are not guilty, for \x + \xo 50:7 \xt [ver. 14] \x*they have sinned against the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 50:7 \xt ch. 31:23 \x*their habitation of righteousness, the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 50:7 \xt See ch. 14:8\x*the hope of their fathers.’
\b
\p
\v 8 \x + \xo 50:8 \xt ch. 51:6, 45; See Isa. 48:20\x*“Flee from the midst of Babylon, \x + \xo 50:8 \xt ch. 51:6, 45; See Isa. 48:20\x*and go out of the land of the Chaldeans, and be as male goats before the flock.
\v 9 For behold, I am stirring up and bringing against Babylon \x + \xo 50:9 \xt See ch. 25:14\x*a gathering of great nations, from the north country. And they shall array themselves against her. From there she shall be taken. Their arrows are like a skilled warrior who does not return empty-handed.
\v 10 \x + \xo 50:10 \xt [ch. 25:12]\x*Chaldea shall be plundered; all who plunder her shall be sated, declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 50:11 \xt [Lam. 4:21]\x*“Though you rejoice, though you exult,
\q2 O plunderers of my heritage,
\q1 though you frolic like a heifer in the pasture,
\q2 and neigh like stallions,
\q1
\v 12 your mother shall be utterly shamed,
\q2 and she who bore you shall be disgraced.
\q1 Behold, she shall be the last of the nations,
\q2 \x + \xo 50:12 \xt ch. 51:43\x*a wilderness, a dry land, and a desert.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 50:13 \xt ver. 39 \x*Because of the wrath of the \nd Lord\nd* she shall not be inhabited
\q2 but shall be an utter desolation;
\q1 \x + \xo 50:13 \xt See ch. 18:16\x*everyone who passes by Babylon shall be appalled,
\q2 \x + \xo 50:13 \xt See ch. 18:16\x*and hiss because of all her wounds.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 50:14 \xt ver. 9; ch. 51:11; Isa. 21:2 \x*Set yourselves in array against Babylon all around,
\q2 \x + \xo 50:14 \xt ver. 29; [ch. 51:3] \x*all you who bend the bow;
\q1 shoot at her, spare no arrows,
\q2 \x + \xo 50:14 \xt [ver. 7]\x*for she has sinned against the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 50:15 \xt [Josh. 6:16] \x*Raise a shout against her all around;
\q2 she has surrendered;
\q1 her bulwarks have fallen;
\q2 \x + \xo 50:15 \xt ch. 51:58 \x*her walls are thrown down.
\q1 For \x + \xo 50:15 \xt ch. 46:10; 51:6, 11 \x*this is the vengeance of the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q2 take vengeance on her;
\q2 \x + \xo 50:15 \xt ver. 29; ch. 51:56\x*do to her as she has done.
\q1
\v 16 Cut off from Babylon the sower,
\q2 and the one who handles the sickle in time of harvest;
\q1 \x + \xo 50:16 \xt ch. 46:16 \x*because of the sword of the oppressor,
\q2 \x + \xo 50:16 \xt [ch. 51:9]; See Isa. 13:14\x*every one shall turn to his own people,
\q2 and every one shall flee to his own land.
\b
\p
\v 17 \x + \xo 50:17 \xt See ver. 6 \x*“Israel is a hunted sheep \x + \xo 50:17 \xt ch. 2:15; 4:7; Isa. 5:29 \x*driven away by lions. \x + \xo 50:17 \xt 2 Kgs. 17:6; 18:13 \x*First the king of Assyria \x + \xo 50:17 \xt ch. 51:34 \x*devoured him, and now at last \x + \xo 50:17 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:10, 14; See 2 Kgs. 25:1-11 \x*Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon \x + \xo 50:17 \xt [ch. 51:34]\x*has gnawed his bones.
\v 18 Therefore, thus says the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, \x + \xo 50:18 \xt Isa. 10:12; 24:21; [Ps. 76:12] \x*I am bringing punishment on the king of Babylon and his land, \x + \xo 50:18 \xt Isa. 14:24, 25\x*as I punished the king of Assyria.
\v 19 \x + \xo 50:19 \xt Ezek. 34:13, 14 \x*I will restore Israel to his pasture, and \x + \xo 50:19 \xt Ezek. 34:13, 14 \x*he shall feed on \x + \xo 50:19 \xt Mic. 7:14\x*Carmel and in \x + \xo 50:19 \xt Mic. 7:14\x*Bashan, and his desire shall be satisfied on the hills of Ephraim and in \x + \xo 50:19 \xt Mic. 7:14\x*Gilead.
\v 20 In those days and in that time, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 50:20 \xt [Isa. 40:2] \x*iniquity shall be sought in Israel, and there shall be none, and sin in Judah, and none shall be found, for \x + \xo 50:20 \xt Isa. 33:24; See ch. 31:34\x*I will pardon those whom I leave as a remnant.
\b
\q1
\v 21 “Go up against the land of Merathaim,\f + \fr 50:21 \fq Merathaim \ft means \fq double rebellion\f*
\q2 and against the inhabitants of Pekod.\f + \fr 50:21 \fq Pekod \ft means \fq punishment\f*
\q1 Kill, \x + \xo 50:21 \xt ver. 26; [ch. 51:3]\x*and devote them to destruction,\f + \fr 50:21 \ft That is, set apart (devote) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)\f*
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and do all that I have commanded you.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 50:22 \xt ch. 51:54\x*The noise of battle is in the land,
\q2 and great destruction!
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 50:23 \xt Isa. 14:6 \x*How the hammer of the whole earth
\q2 is cut down and broken!
\q1 \x + \xo 50:23 \xt [Rev. 18:19, 21] \x*How Babylon \x + \xo 50:23 \xt ver. 3, 13\x*has become
\q2 a horror among the nations!
\q1
\v 24 \x + \xo 50:24 \xt [Ps. 141:9] \x*I set a snare for you and you were taken, O Babylon,
\q2 and \x + \xo 50:24 \xt [ch. 51:31; Dan. 5:30]\x*you did not know it;
\q1 you were found and caught,
\q2 because you opposed the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 25 The \nd Lord\nd* has opened his armory
\q2 and brought out \x + \xo 50:25 \xt Isa. 13:5\x*the weapons of his wrath,
\q1 for the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts has a work to do
\q2 in the land of the Chaldeans.
\q1
\v 26 Come against her from every quarter;
\q2 open her granaries;
\q1 \x + \xo 50:26 \xt [Neh. 4:2]\x*pile her up like heaps of grain, and devote her to destruction;
\q2 let nothing be left of her.
\q1
\v 27 Kill all \x + \xo 50:27 \xt [Ps. 22:12; Isa. 34:7, 8] \x*her bulls;
\q2 let them go down to the slaughter.
\q1 Woe to them, for their day has come,
\q2 \x + \xo 50:27 \xt ch. 46:21\x*the time of their punishment.
\b
\p
\v 28 “A voice! They \x + \xo 50:28 \xt [ver. 8] \x*flee and escape from the land of Babylon, \x + \xo 50:28 \xt ch. 51:10; Ps. 64:9 \x*to declare in Zion the vengeance of the \nd Lord\nd* our God, vengeance for \x + \xo 50:28 \xt [ch. 51:11; 52:13; Dan. 5:3, 23]\x*his temple.
\b
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 50:29 \xt [ver. 14; Job 16:13] \x*“Summon archers against Babylon, all those who bend the bow. \x + \xo 50:29 \xt [ver. 14; Job 16:13] \x*Encamp around her; let no one escape. \x + \xo 50:29 \xt ch. 25:14 \x*Repay her according to her deeds; do to her according to all that she has done. For she has \x + \xo 50:29 \xt Isa. 47:10\x*proudly defied the \nd Lord\nd*, the Holy One of Israel.
