\b
\p
\v 44 \x + \xo 50:44 \xt For ver. 44-46, see ch. 49:19-21 \x*“Behold, like a lion coming up from the thicket of the Jordan against a perennial pasture, I will suddenly make them run away from her, and I will appoint over her whomever I choose. For who is like me? Who will summon me? What shepherd \x + \xo 50:44 \xt Job 41:10\x*can stand before me?
\v 45 Therefore hear \x + \xo 50:45 \xt ch. 51:11, 12, 29; Isa. 14:24 \x*the plan that the \nd Lord\nd* has made against Babylon, \x + \xo 50:45 \xt ch. 51:11, 12, 29; Isa. 14:24 \x*and the purposes that he has formed against the land of the Chaldeans: \x + \xo 50:45 \xt ch. 49:20\x*Surely the little ones of their flock shall be dragged away; surely their fold shall be appalled at their fate.
\v 46 \x + \xo 50:46 \xt See ch. 49:21\x*At the sound of the capture of Babylon the earth shall tremble, and her cry shall be heard among the nations.”
\c 51
\s1 The Utter Destruction of Babylon
